tps://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx7/cdn40@2020_3/2020/09/05/08-42-44-680_0d6834cb559ba581.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288850/best-fall-fashion-nordstrom-288850-1598549736550-main.800x0uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx3/cdn83@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-43-00-236_21236472d69fc37b.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288850/best-fall-fashion-nordstrom-288850-1598549751829-main.800x0uc.jpg":null,"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288850/best-fall-fashion-nordstrom-288850-1598551703239-main.800x0uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx29/cdn41@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-42-30-487_01e1480e24292fd6.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288850/best-fall-fashion-nordstrom-288850-1598552086258-main.800x0uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx/cdn69@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-42-28-110_edabf7541cce981c.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288850/best-fall-fashion-nordstrom-288850-1598552001129-main.800x0uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx24/cdn95@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-41-46-966_ea3987e707c593cc.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288850/best-fall-fashion-nordstrom-288850-1598549690210-main.800x0uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx3/cdn49@2020_3/2020/09/05/08-41-40-320_11f848292276d668.webp","http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~4/y9xdFa3gCSc":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx19/cdn40@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-41-35-784_2478437c840aefb1.webp"},"publishedOrCreatedDate":1599295287275},{"createdTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"This Emerging Brand Has All the Makings of an It-Girl Favorite","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/F_77wlIAHP4/tyrell-review","description":"<p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287150/lcd-shop-review-287150-1588979528759-main.1200x1200uc.gif\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><em><span>Welcome</span><span> to our newest editorial initiative, </span></em><span><a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/tags/who-what-wear-spotlight\" target=\"_blank\">Who What Wear Spotlight</a></span><em><span>, where we'll be using our editorial platform, social following, and ad inventory to turn the spotlight on small businesses that need our support now more than ever. Each week, we'll be highlighting a new fashion or beauty company. If you own a small brand and would like to be considered for the program, <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=QG403HlA1219qaeIcFklT_UPuE99t2NAjoqMJQ5RMVPDvk1HfvdR1KdmbGonh_G3ZHQ3Ol_zJ6IZZRE3HpRlGvUGLThYy_-6iMBEDqtwCuzAU-h6H9amVqESlQap_8S42elsOzLCiCV1JB6Izt18t6-VsQ\" target=\"_blank\">please apply here</a>.</span></em></p><p>These days, it seems like the younger a brand is the stronger an ethos beats at its core. The newest generation of designers who have started brands in the last few years all seem to share a sense of responsibility to the planet and whatever community they're a part of. This often means smaller brands with environmentally conscious production methods, and sometimes, it also means a mission statement aimed at deconstructing the industry as it stands. Toronto's Tyrell Harriott is no different. He launched <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=8Yk-omXEYo4S-5U_IbQoEGLWc4r_xXhWrUwuuTyqpyFI_LAk\" target=\"_blank\">his eponymous label</a> three years ago when he graduated from college and saw no space that suited him in Toronto's design world. So he made space for himself.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288860/tia-adeola-review-1-288860-1598580298021-main.1200x1718uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>In Harriott's design world, luxury is turned on its head, and feminity takes on a whole new meaning. I've seen his barely-there designs lauded for their \"heavy femininity\" and the statements they inherently make on how sensual a woman's body is typically allowed to be. Though Harriott is cutting holes and shortening hemlines to reveal the female silhouette, how much skin ultimately gets shown is up to the wearer, for his designs are often adjustable. Dresses can be made shorter, and bralette-shrug sets can be worn as separates. That versatility isn't just a tool for empowering women to have control over how much of their bodies they want to reveal. It's also multipurpose. Harriott wants his designs to take women from their day into their night.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288860/tia-adeola-review-1-288860-1598580314130-main.1200x1803uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>The bralette set is already popular among It girls like <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=15CGGLkXBQoSXcJqID-QleodqLf2fXwN6i8auBJOOmWhEJcqwlTX04vQJOyxqy6kbDKPaijNnOM\" target=\"_blank\">Amy Julliette Lefévre</a> and <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=o7gsPphIrQXLWv-WD5Rbjfv2-EJCDmWP74BZIzokBJU75cNgqiEQNG1-DkRkgwbceumgqnEfSq4\" target=\"_blank\">Anajah</a>. The six designs Harriott currently sells are all made to order from deadstock fabrics. It's a statement about production: How are luxury items produced, for whom, and with what intention? With raw hemlines, cutouts, itty-bitty straps, and see-through mesh, it's clear he's telling a younger, more radically feminine customer base that made to order is no longer a status symbol but a political message—one that encourages slowing down, paying attention to where our money is going, and dictating how the world gets to perceive us. Keep reading to hear from the man himself.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288860/tia-adeola-review-1-288860-1598580329288-main.1200x1803uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>Tell us about yourself and your business.</strong></p><p>My name is Tyrell Harriott. I studied fashion design at George Brown College here in Toronto, Canada, and wasn't very inspired by the fashion that was happening in my city, so I created Tyrell. I launched it with the intention to make sensual clothes for destinations and create our own vacations every day. I want to design clothes that are striking enough to make memories.</p><p>The core of my brand is that you can wear every piece in different ways. I feel clothes should be able to have multiple personalities, and I try to show that in my brand. An important goal for me is to keep my business as conscious as possible, and how I do that is by making each piece to order out of deadstock fabrics. It's always been really important to me to make sure my brand can operate during a time when that's something consumers think about.</p><p><strong>And if you had to sum up your business in five words or less?</strong></p><p>Girl, where we going?</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288860/tia-adeola-review-1-288860-1598580336756-main.1200x1803uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>What inspired you to start your business?</strong></p><p>I went to Paris in late 2016 and was inspired by the people, the stores, and the women! It put a vision of a specific woman in my mind that I really wanted to design for. After coming back and graduating, I was super ready to make a collection of items I loved. I did a fashion show in 2017 in Toronto that forced me to recreate what had been stuck in my head for a while. I made it to sharpen my portfolio, but when I couldn't find anything that inspired me in my city, I started my eponymous brand Tyrell. I felt it just made sense, and I got to create my own little world that felt outside of Toronto but still in it.</p><p><strong>How have social distancing and stay-at-home orders affected your business? How have your priorities shifted?</strong></p><p>Social distancing and stay-at-home orders affected my business for the better, really. I mean I had a lot on my plate pre-COVID, and it was forcibly cleared once lockdown started. Not basing off the wholesale model and being mainly e-commerce, we weren't impacted by that part of the business. We're a small team that does the job using a direct-to-consumer model, so I really didn't have any middle man in the supply chain that couldn't get the job done. I was able to put all of my focus and energy into my brand, which I wasn't able to completely do before, so it's allowed me to do a higher volume of orders since all the pieces are made to order.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288860/tia-adeola-review-1-288860-1598580345415-main.1200x800uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>What are two to three of your favorite brands you like to support and why?</strong></p><p>I Iove spotlight love! A few brands I actually love to keep track of and support are <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=RsJz9qgjwOCM8RtMEKWE7Pn9HffIyfYmMk3VL10csSE5zX4Szhy3taw\" target=\"_blank\">Mowalola</a> and <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=W9bMHEP5zBTy0GkB8qrCGs0IO9BnPxPrqwQ7sO05prKdO6MLXY6d\" target=\"_blank\">Telfar</a>! Well, I try to think of them as my peers, being black-owned businesses also, but I think what they do is really needed in this time of redefining what is luxury!</p><p><strong>What has been your proudest moment as a business owner?</strong></p><p>The proudest moment I had as a business owner was honestly getting my first stockist at a boutique I had always loved from afar and now am a part of. It's super cool. It's called <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=BX8qsYYXtkyJB0qRKsrGxsLc4wVWI4AjJN_N3nBGRP-7uW_JODPUZr0\" target=\"_blank\">The Break</a> in Brooklyn, New York.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288860/tia-adeola-review-1-288860-1598580351372-main.1200x800uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288860/tyrell-review-288860-1598905558790-main.1365x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"This top was inspired by clashing an everyday top with a bikini. I wanted it to feel spliced but simple. The drawstring can be tightened or loosened, which gives the wearer the choice that day.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288860/tyrell-review-288860-1598905568364-main.1365x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"This is my favorite dress! I feel it's super striking and sensual. I designed this piece with a cabana party in mind. I love minidresses and the energy they capture, and I think this one does just that.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288860/tyrell-review-288860-1598905576656-main.1365x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"I think this set is important to my brand's DNA in the sense that it can easily transition from day to night. I always want my clothes to be the middle point of the day for those who change more than once. It's the important outfit. The sleeves can easily be slipped on once it gets chilly during those summer nights or can be worn on their own. Or wear just the bralette with jeans or just the sleeves and the skirt. It's super fun!\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288860/tyrell-review-288860-1598905585698-main.1365x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"This dress was inspired by the little black dress but with holes. I wanted it to continue the theme of feeling beach ready or sun drenched. It can be worn different ways also: You can tie the strings tighter to make it a mini or looser to lengthen the dress! The strings allow you to tie it more than one way, also.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288860/tyrell-review-288860-1598905593734-main.1365x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"I feel this dress is the ultimate summer dress. I love tie-dye and wanted to create something modern with it! It's a dress spliced with a bikini top that is easily wearable for any summer hang without feeling too serious!\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288860/tyrell-review-288860-1598905602264-main.1365x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"This snake-mesh set is very important to my brand. It's almost a signifier for a Tyrell piece! It's the only fabric we have continued to develop throughout seasons based on how easy it is to wear, and everyone needs something green in their wardrobe.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><em>Up next, <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/tia-adeola-review\" target=\"_blank\">the bold, young NY-based brand that stars from Gigi Hadid to Lizzo love</a>.</em></p><img 33.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/289010/best-fall-items-from-mango-289010-1599251489043-main.800x0uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx25/cdn43@2020_6/2020/09/05/08-42-05-880_3abe40b818f3f8e1.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/289010/best-fall-items-from-mango-289010-1599251517678-main.1001x1400uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx29/cdn91@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-42-07-302_17b85d747a52da5b.webp","http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~4/S_f8u-Gd2NE":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx13/cdn61@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-43-06-531_be6a25da41c4dd2f.webp"},"publishedOrCreatedDate":1599295287274},{"createdTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"The Best Youth-Enhancing Skin Regimens Include These 8 Strategic Ingredients","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/a-bi1_3BvHA/best-anti-aging-ingredients","description":"<p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597252952568-main.800x0uc.gif\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>When it comes <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-drugstore-makeup-for-mature-skin\" target=\"_blank\">to aging</a>, I'm definitely not an expert. I'm 27 with nary a line or wrinkle on my face, and while I harness a sponge-like talent for absorbing any and all skincare intel, (and I obviously proceed to share every single vetted tidbit I soak-up with you all!), I leave the serious advice to the experts—especially concerning topics like skincare chemistry or the most efficacious ingredients to treat certain <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/how-to-treat-common-skincare-concerns\" target=\"_blank\">skin conditions</a> or benefit <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-skincare-products-for-every-skin-type/slide2\" target=\"_blank\">certain skin types</a>. One such example? The best ingredients to incorporate into <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-anti-aging-skincare-lines\" target=\"_blank\">an anti-aging skincare routine</a>.</p><p>Sure, hot and buzzy ingredients like <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/guide-to-retinols\" target=\"_blank\">retinol</a>, vitamin C, and <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-hyaluronic-acid-serums\" target=\"_blank\">hyaluronic acid</a> are thrown around with frisbee-level speed, but the hoopla surrounding such ingredients can create equally intense whiplash and confusion. Are these popular ingredients <em>truly</em> the most beneficial for those looking to slow or at least lessen the visible natural aging process? To set the record straight, I reached out to five amazing experts to advise on the most effective, youth-enhancing ingredients for maturing skin. (You know, <em>if</em> you're into that kind of thing.)</p><p>So, who's on our expert panel? Board-certified dermatologists <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=Z_CMu1m0h_yHXaULMCI6dNk6x0ebCKwCbcMgiSL1lI84lHCH8HoEPHE9TmM7Nz1DAT9eUj2I8Mm0\" target=\"_blank\">Candace Thornton Spann</a>, MD, FAAD and <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=bbDVclaA19WODufne4jLLeB-XYZNndvmtoy9A8lUmHbeSbAdtVHVnsEvJCJiJhHfUfB-YMAr9g\" target=\"_blank\">Tiffany J. Libby</a>, MD FAAD, cosmetic chemist and CEO of <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=1RlaQGGTm_W3cd9PD0MUaUULeXztxcdKb18HsFi83mf4bafzH8YdrrGm4g\" target=\"_blank\">BeautyStat Cosmetics</a> <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=aqou3t1-f6p15B_L9BaTK2WvDuJGRf8TZdSerMGg5KG5Bg9j9cP1k4YzF_cfS2-kZv5YwkolxJ-yzITPxs4oE-herX8r\" target=\"_blank\">Ron Robinson</a>, board-certified plastic surgeon <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=1ACMA8C99HvYID2Dlg2KEfhORitZ5x_pBRy_R8Hyols2Ca9id6IB3DpwQLV4JO5pbs8J-YVCoQ\" target=\"_blank\">Lara Devgan</a>, MD, MPH, FACS, and celebrity facialist <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=OmdTh_w1Kig5vB9CQHgmHiXGsUwCJrK9N1Ujmv8llqxuHNPlRX0m4Mlmum0gcVuTP8csw-Q-hQ\" target=\"_blank\">Renée Rouleau</a>, who's also CEO of her eponymous skincare line. Keep scrolling! Below, our experts spill everything you've ever wanted to know about the best ingredients for anti-aging. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597252964152-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>Why it's an anti-aging superstar:</strong> \"Retinol is derived from pure, bioactive vitamin A and is a cell-communicating ingredient that can increase cell thickness, affect gene expression, increase the production of collagen from within, and thin the stratum corneum (the outermost layer of skin consisting mostly of dead cells),\" Rouleau explains. \"<strong>With continued use, retinol can dramatically improve the appearance of the skin and encourage a healthy maturation process. It helps smooth out the skin while also reducing visible wrinkles, lines, enlarged pores, brown spots, and even scarring from acne</strong>.\" </p><p><strong>How to use it like a pro:</strong> Always use retinol at night and apply a thin layer to your face after you cleanse and tone and before you add your moisturizer. Since retinol can trigger irritation (especially if you have sensitive skin), skin professionals recommend starting with a twice-per-week usage, gradually increasing to three or four days a week as your skin grows more tolerant. \"<strong>Patients with darker skin tend to be more prone to skin discoloration, so retinol needs to be introduced into their regimen slowly to allow the skin to accommodate to avoid irritation</strong>,\" Spann clarifies.</p><p>Additionally, Libby suggests opting for a \"retinol sandwich\" for anyone who is especially concerned about irritation or sensitivity. First, apply moisturizer, followed by your retinol, and then your moisturizer again. </p><p><strong>Helpful hint:</strong> \"Some initial dryness can occur in formulas with concentrations of 1% or higher, but not all formulas are made equally,\" Rouleau clarifies. If you notice sensitivity or irritation, she recommends looking for a gentler formula and also reminds us that <strong>retinol is not recommended if you're nursing or pregnant</strong>. (For more helpful tips regarding retinol, check out Rouleau's blog post <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=bnjvNZItfb1cogXYlw4hI5Is-K8nof9xLWOMuuNC0k1Rv--CYQFJhOzOZZJ07p73tWx_7Ubmv7AdbK4NCA-ErlLcChZIw_TTCp8gvqw\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.) </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597252984455-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>What the derm says: \"I recommend any of PCA Skin's retinol solutions based on skin type, condition and Fitzpatrick type to minimize fine lines and wrinkles, improve skin surface, reduce discoloration, and even help clear breakouts,\" says Spann. \"This formula for sensitive skin is a great entry point for new retinol users.\" </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597252993613-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253001305-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253008881-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>Why it's an anti-aging superstar:</strong> \"Hyaluronic acid is a major component of the body’s collagen, and it's a complex sugar molecule that can absorb 1000 times its weight in water,\" shares Devgan. \"Used regularly in your skincare routine, it results in a dewy, hydrated, flawless-looking complexion reminiscent of that coveted 'glass skin' look.\" </p><p><strong>How to use it like a pro:</strong> Hyaluronic acid is safe to use daily, is well-tolerated, and while you can use it both morning and night, Devgan says it's especially strategic in the morning as it adequately hydrates your skin for the day, and other products like SPF and/or makeup can be effortlessly layered ontop. </p><p><strong>Helpful hint:</strong> \"There are so many hyaluronic serums on the market, and one thing I always say is that not all hyaluronic acids are created equally,\" warns Devgan. \"<strong>A mixed molecular weight hyaluronic has small fragments that will <em>more effectively</em> penetrate into the dermis to hydrate from within while the larger fragments reside on top of the skin to create a beautiful finish</strong>.\"</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253014428-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>What the derm says: \"This is my go-to for plumping and hydration maintenance for all my patients,\" notes Spann. \"It effectively plumps, hydrates, and soothes all skin types, conditions, and types,\" says Fitzpatrick.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253021605-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253027410-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253037764-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>Why it's an anti-aging superstar:</strong> \"Astaxanthin is a powerful, carotenoid antioxidant derived from microalgae,\" Rouleau tells us. \"It helps rebuild collagen and protects tissues, cells, and membranes from destructive, free radicals which in effect, helps to reduce the look of wrinkles by encouraging smoother, youthful-looking skin. <strong>Astaxanthin is known to be one of the best active ingredients for preventative aging and is particularly beneficial for those who spend a lot of time outdoors and are regularly exposed to the elements</strong>.\"</p><p><strong>How to use it like a pro:</strong> A powerful antioxidant, astaxanthin is usually found within serums and creams, and according to Rouleau, it's especially useful to apply it at nighttime before you log your beauty sleep. Apply your product as directed on the packaging, following your cleansing and toning ritual. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253046775-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>What the celeb facialist says: \"I'm a big fan of incorporating astaxanthin as a nighttime serum to renew and replenish your skin while you sleep,\" says Rouleau. \"After cleansing and toning, apply one pump to the entire face and follow with a nighttime moisturizer.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253055953-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253061234-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253069180-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>Why it's an anti-aging superstar:</strong> \"Niacinamide is a water-soluble form of vitamin B3 that boosts ceramide levels in the skin, improving the skin's ability to hold on to moisture,\" says Rouleau. \"<strong>It works by stimulating circulation in the dermis through a process known as vasodilation, and it can reduce the yellow-ish look to the face caused by the glycation of proteins, which is a common visible effect of aging due to environmental damage</strong>. Niacinamide also serves as an antioxidant to protect cells, membranes, and tissues from free radical attacks and can even reduce discoloration (brown spots and post-breakout scars) by preventing the transfer of melanosomes from melanocytes to the keratinocytes. Lastly, niacinamide offers anti-breakout and anti-bacterial benefits to reduce blemish activity.\"</p><p><strong>How to use it like a pro:</strong> Since niacinamide can be found in a variety of products (and you can safely apply it any time of the day), it's best to use your product as instructed. </p><p><strong>Helpful hint:</strong> \"While there are no known side effects associated with niacinamide, some people can experience some redness when using the ingredient in high percentages,\" notes Rouleau. She explains this is likely due to niacinamide's vasodilation process, therefore, you'll want to tread carefully and monitor your skin during the first few applications as you would with any other new addition to your routine. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253118206-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>What the celeb facialist says: \"I love this moisturizing toner with niacinamide,\" Rouleau explains. \"After cleansing, wipe it over your face and leave it damp before proceeding with the next product in your routine. By leaving it damp on your face, it delivers moisture into the skin, and because the formula is water-based, it can act as a carrier for a serum applied afterward to be delivered deeper and more effectively to the skin.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253084296-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253091517-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253096740-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>Why it's an anti-aging superstar:</strong> \"Peptides are long or short chains of amino acids, which are the building blocks of protein that send signals to your cells to make more collagen and thicken the support structure of the skin,\" Rouleau explains. \"Peptides are able to remain intact as they enter the skin's cells and they primarily function as moisture-binding agents. <strong>Plus, nearly all types of peptides have cell-communicating capabilities that send signals to the skin to repair itself. It's an especially strategic ingredient to incorporate if you're looking for firmer, more refined-looking skin</strong>.\"</p><p>According to Rouleau, the most beneficial types of peptides to look for within your products include palmitoyl tripeptide-38 (one of the most well-researched peptides on the market), palmitoyl oligopeptide, palmitoyl tetrapeptide-7, acetyl hexapeptide, palmitoyl pentapeptide, dipeptide-2, and caprooyl tetrapeptide.\"</p><p><strong>How to use it like a pro:</strong> Peptides can be used safely at any time of the day, so it's best to follow the directions your product provides. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253105851-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>What the celeb facialist says: \"Peptides are especially great for the eye area, and eye creams can be used both day or night,\" Rouleau shares. \"Apply a thin layer around the outer corners of the eyes known as the 'crow’s feet' and be careful not to get it too close to the lashes, as you don’t want it to seep into your eyes.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253128603-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253137654-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253143230-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>Why it's an anti-aging superstar:</strong> \"Vitamin C is an important antioxidant that scavenges free radical and environmental damage that has compromised the skin,\" notes Devgan. <strong>\"It helps to even out discoloration, fade brown spots, and improve lines.\"</strong></p><p><strong>How to use it like a pro:</strong> Citing data that suggests vitamin C may improve the absorption of retinol, Devgan recommends saving your daily dose of this potent anti-aging ingredient for the evening. Additionally, Robinson notes that while vitamin C is one of the best anti-aging ingredients for most skin types, those who are sensitive (again) should apply their formula at night and should start with lower concentrations. Then, once your skin has acclimated, or you know you're not having any reactions, he suggests graduating to twice-per-day (morning and night) applications and testing higher-dose formulas.</p><p><strong>Helpful hint:</strong> \"Vitamin C is an unstable ingredient, so look for stabilized versions,\" Robinson warns. BeautyStat's <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=K8PZp4q8Vp1Kc6g5zV8jj69xYnBOq1lGbB-f6NHbb4BiSWYcpKOQilSmulhDZozstK3GptmXa-qB\" target=\"_blank\">Universal C Skin Refiner</a> has three patents due to its ability to stabilize pure vitamin C in a way where it won't oxidize—it stays pure and potent from the first drop to the last. You can use it morning and/or night, just be sure to follow it up with SPF if you opt for a morning application.\"</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253152653-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>What the derm says: \"One product I particularly like for my patients is PCA Skin's C&E Advanced,\" Spann shares. \"It also provides additional antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and discoloration-fighting ingredients silymarin and hexylresorcinol, and it's highly stable, effective, and contains calming ingredients that make it appropriate for a wide variety of patients to build collagen and even out skin tone.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253159155-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253166761-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253175269-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>Why it's an anti-aging superstar:</strong> \"When it comes to the best ingredients for anti-aging, number one always should be sun protection,\" clarifies Libby. \"As a skin cancer surgeon, I love the saying, 'An ounce of prevention is worth a pound of cure.' I am seeing more and more young patients come in with skin cancers, either from a history of tanning bed use or an increase in recreational sun exposure. We are lucky that we now know how important and beneficial SPF is for both protection against UV damage (which can lead to skin cancers) as well as prevention against premature aging and unwanted pigmentation. <strong>Mineral-based sunscreens are my go-to, and the AAD recommends using a formula that has an SPF 30 or higher, is water-resistant, and boasts broad-spectrum protection against both UVA and UVB</strong>.\"</p><p><strong>How to use it like a pro:</strong> According to Libby, a good rule of thumb is to apply your skincare products from thinnest to thickest. In the morning, after you cleanse, start with your serum, follow that with a moisturizer, and lastly, add your SPF. </p><p><strong>Helpful hint:</strong> Even though any kind of SPF is better than nothing, Libby says she typically prefers <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-zinc-oxide-sunscreens\" target=\"_blank\">mineral sunscreens</a> as they are especially helpful for those who have sensitive skin, are pregnant, or who <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/how-to-treat-common-skincare-concerns\" target=\"_blank\">conditions like melasma</a>. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253191710-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>What the derm says: \"One product I have been loving is Glytone's Hydra Lipid UV Mineral SPF 40+,\" Libby tells us. \"It's formulated using a powerful antioxidant complex with vitamins C and E, as well as moisturizers like hyaluronic acid and squalane. It's the ultimate multitasking SPF.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253196642-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253211319-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253216794-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>Why it's an anti-aging superstar:</strong> \"Ceramides are key components of the skin barrier, and when there aren't enough, skin conditions like eczema, dryness, and irritation can occur,\" Libby explains. \"<strong>As we age, ceramide levels in our skin naturally decrease, and by the time we are 30, almost 40% of our skin’s ceramides are depleted, and by the time we are 40, that number increases to 60%. That said, we can help counteract this by adding them back into our skin to help re-fortify our skin's moisture barrier</strong>. When our skin is adequately moisturized and hydrated, it appears firmer, healthier, plumper, and overall less lined and wrinkled.\"</p><p><strong>How to use it like a pro:</strong> Just like other ingredients like antioxidants, hyaluronic acid, etc., ceramides are safe to use for all and can be added to your regimen to help promote healthy skin and reverse any damage that has been done. You can find them in plenty of different formulas (typically creams) and it's recommended you follow the product's specific application protocol for best results. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253223639-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>What the derm says: \"I love using Cetaphil's Ultra-Healing Lotion which is packed with ceramides and other nourishing ingredients for my face and body,\" Libby shares. \"I apply this immediately after the shower to help seal in moisture, and I find that it is rich enough to hydrate my skin in the winter while still being lightweight to use year-round as well.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253229090-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288584/best-anti-aging-ingredients-288584-1597253234754-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>Super-expensive moisturizers:</strong> According to Libby, there are plenty of affordably priced moisturizers on the market and there is actually little need to splurge. Of course, you can ultimately decide where you choose to invest within your skincare routine, but she recommends using your hard-earned dollars for antioxidant-containing formulas like your vitamin C products. (She notes that stable—aka, the most effective—vitamin C products, are harder to formulate and are therefore more expensive. Skinceuticals <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=FhEwfUI8Nigb4pXnqAVheq6vFtMIlU1bKWWyss-ERcwug4bSdS2fv4Uaz8QEayVPS8Gr1H6_6XN5\" target=\"_blank\">Phloretin CF</a> $166 is her top recommendation.) </p><p><strong>Products with ineffective ingredient proportions</strong>: Spann reveals that many skincare companies will tout that a product contains a particular ingredient, when in fact, there is a very small percentage of that ingredient in their formula. \"It is important to be certain that key anti-aging ingredients are used at the levels at which they were tested for efficacy,\" she heeds. \"Also, more isn't always better. There are ingredients—like peptides and hyaluronic acid—that are used at low percentages to achieve amazing results. Using more of something does not always indicate better outcomes.\"</p><p><strong>Overexaggerated claims:</strong> As we talk about quite often on Who What Wear, it's always important to take marketing, product, and specific ingredient claims with a grain of salt. Because, as Devgan confirms, a lot of ingredients have overstated claims. She cites <strong>creams targeted toward stretch marks</strong> as one of the most likely offenders, and she's also wary of <strong>facial oils</strong> because while they <em>may</em> improve the barrier of the skin, their molecules are too large to truly hydrate the skin from within. Plus, she notes, they can also clog pores and lead to congestion. Last but not least, Devgan says <strong>large-fragment facial scrubs</strong> can be extremely rough and damaging to the skin texture, and <strong>chemical peels</strong> should be left to the professionals and not executed at home.</p><p><em>Next: <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-anti-aging-skincare-lines\" target=\"_blank\">Experts Reveal the 18 Best Skincare Brands to Unlock Plump,Youthful Skin</a></em></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~4/a-bi1_3BvHA\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>","descriptionType":"html","publishedDate":"Thu, 03 Sep 2020 seems appropriate to start planning those autumn wardrobes and noting outfit ideas to test out for the season. One timeless pairing that just always works? Yep, you guessed it—the <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/cute-outfits-with-jeans\" target=\"_blank\">skinny jean</a> and <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ankle-boot-trends\" target=\"_blank\">ankle boots</a> duo. Sure, skinny jeans can be polarizing in nature for some, but the denim silhouette is more or less timeless at this point, and looks A+ with booties. As a result, fashion people continue to embrace the look on the regular.</p><p>On that note, we scrolled through the feeds of some of our favorite follows to uncover a smattering of solid outfits featuring skinny jeans and ankle boots. Below you’ll find the seven standouts, including everything from a chic ‘fit with an of-the-moment trench coat to a cozy sweater ensemble. Intrigued? Keep scrolling for more, complete with a range of shopping inspiration as well. </p><p><figure><img 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"I Tried the New \"Ribcage\" Jeans NYC Girls Are Obsessing Over","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/OVvBqKeheTA/levis-ribcage-jeans","description":"<p>We've already shared the magic of the <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-affordable-jeans-for-women\" target=\"_blank\">$98 jeans a stylist always suggests to celebs</a>, but there's a brand-new shape that launched in recent years, and it's already a hit among the stylish NYC crowd (and this L.A. editor).</p><p>Aptly dubbed the Ribcage style, the jeans offer the highest rise on any Levi's to date—and at 12 1/8 inches, the ribcage-grazing waistline puts other high-waisted jeans on the market to shame. The name makes them a bit daunting, I realize, but once threw on my pair and buttoned them up past belly button, it became immediately clear that these were the most flattering (and affordable!) jeans I had ever thrown on.</p><p>It turns out they were designed to fit that way, according to Global Chief Product Officer Karyn Hillman. \"Authentic look and feel inspired by a '90s Levi's 501 with the modern amplified rise is so flattering—perfectly styled high or low,\" she says. Now that the dark-wash pair are a permanent part of my wardrobe (scroll down to see them on), I can't stop telling my friends to add them to their own personal wardrobes.</p><p>Scroll down to see how I'm wearing the jeans, along with the NYC girls who adore them, too, and then shop the current Ribcage styles to add to your closet.</p><p><figure><img 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"8 Beauty Products I'm Saying Bye to Because Fall Will Be Here in 5 Seconds","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/iQMNSNKMn9s/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps","description":"<p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599072741311-main.1200x900uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Is it just me, or are the final days of <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/tags/summer-beauty\" target=\"_blank\">summer</a> slipping by faster than usual? As a beauty editor, my spidey senses start tingling at the onset of any <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/summer-beauty-products\" target=\"_blank\">seasonal shift</a> because it signals the need to purge my vanity of any products that no longer serve my <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/natural-makeup-looks\" target=\"_blank\">makeup</a>, skincare, and <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-body-care-products\" target=\"_blank\">bodycare</a> needs in exchange for ones that will ride with me in the months to come. But the transition from summer to fall is probably the most drastic course correction I make all year since environmental conditions make the most dramatic leap from hot and balmy to cold and dry.</p><p>With fall on the horizon, there's more to consider than which <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-fall-sweaters-on-amazon\" target=\"_blank\">cozy layers</a> we'll add to our wardrobes. We have to start thinking about which swaps we'll be making in our beauty wardrobes, too. Cooler temperatures mean the oil-sopping ingredients we held close all summer will take a back seat to ultra-hydrating formulas that will support us through snowstorms (I've heard from my colleagues in New York that those are a thing), hot showers, and an overall dip in moisture in the air. This time can bring on some major <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/dry-skin-in-winter\" target=\"_blank\">dry-skin woes</a>, but with the right fall beauty products in tow, we can get through it looking and feeling moisturized and unbothered.</p><p>Ahead, check out the eight beauty products I'll be packing away with my swimsuits and sandals and the eight fall-ready picks I'm boosting to the top of my routine.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599091829008-image.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>F is for fall… and full coverage. Summertime always feels like the perfect season to let our skin shine through sheer formulas, but as the weather cools, I tend to start leaning into more-corrective makeup to help smooth out my complexion. Since we're moving out of vacation season, luminous foundations that offer that lit-from-within glow are just perfect for looking glowy, not greasy. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599157113213-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>There's a reason this foundation has a cult following all over the world. When it comes to glowy foundations that have a soft, natural finish but still cover up blemishes and imperfections, this one is a winner. It offers medium coverage, but it can certainly be built upon if you need a bit more. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599107900642-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This drugstore foundation is one of my favorites across all price points. The name tells you everything you need to know about what to expect: glowy, natural-looking, and radiant skin. I love that my face feels comfortable and hydrated under this formula and that it doesn't break down into a greasy mess, even when I've loaded up on my favorite fall moisturizers underneath.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599108649400-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>I'm a lip-gloss lover year round, but once fall hits I'm always ready to amp it up in the color department. A muted, diffused finish is cute for summer, but it's all about vinylic shine and high-impact color once we hit the -ber months. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599157123543-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>The time has come to officially crown this as my favorite prestige gloss of all time. Yeah, I said it! It is so good. It covers the lips completely in an opaque varnish but doesn't feel overly sticky or oppressively thick. This shade, in particular, is such a beautiful nude for those with darker skin tones. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599157131134-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This silky lip gloss is a dream to wear. It's deceptively soft, and based on how it feels, you really wouldn't think it would deliver the level of pigment that it does. This might be the one and only scenario where being fooled is totally fine with me.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599092699174-image.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Don't get me wrong, I love colorful eyeliner. It's so fun and really adds a lot to a look. That said, fall is the time when richer lip colors come out to play, so eyeliner needs to stay a little more neutral so it doesn't compete. Lip liner can help to create a more polished and precise lip, especially when working with a bold color.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599157140725-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>I never loved a lip liner until I met this one. It glides on so beautifully and makes a huge difference when carrying out beauty adventures like overlining. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599157183222-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>It's officially time to dust off our red lippies, and I already know this new liner from Patrick Ta is going to be a fall staple. Ta says you can layer this soft, matte liner on a bit thicker and cover more surface area than you normally would to give your look more staying power.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599091834624-image.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>There isn't anything I love more than a popping highlight. During the summer, I go all out with it since a near-florescent jolt across my cheekbones gels super well with dewy, glossy makeup. But as the leaves change, I like to turn down the dial on my highlighter from a 10 to a nice little five. To compensate, I start adding way more shimmer onto my eyelids. It can create such a nice contrast with matte lips, or even glossy ones.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599157196324-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>If you haven't tried Rituel de Fille yet, I need you to do so right away. This witchy clean-beauty brand makes such cool products, and my favorite one is this Eye Soot. It's a tightly packed, impossibly versatile cream-powder hybrid that can be worn as a soft shimmer or built all the way up to an ultra-pigmented, almost iridescent pop.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599157201212-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This bouncy eye shadow is perfect in every way. It might look over-the-top in the pan, but it really is one of those shadows I could tap into my lids with varying intensity on any day and for any occasion.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599095908686-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Hydration is the name of the game this season. In addition to skipping harsh cleansers that strip too many natural oils out of my skin, I'll be slathering on more overnight hydrating masks to cocoon my skin in nourishing and reparative ingredients while I sleep.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599114411535-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This luxe mask comes with a high price tag, but its combination of saffron flowers, shea butter, and thyme honey infuses so much moisture into the skin. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599157290209-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>I'm still a huge fan of this OG Summer Fridays mask. I used it the other night and was instantly reminded of how lovely it is. If you want to feed your face the skincare equivalent of a gourmet meal, then heed these instructions: Spritz your face with your favorite nourishing essence, pat in three or four drops of your favorite face oil, and top the whole mixture off with the Jet Lag Mask. Thank me later.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599096020752-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Okay so, I'm not doing away with all my skincare picks tailored to achieving my baby-smooth skin goals. But as the season turns and moisture in the air begins to drop, I'm hyper-focused on keeping inflammation caused by severe dryness at bay. After all, inflammation on the face (and body) can cause a whole host of problems such as itching, swelling, breakouts, and more.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599146765007-main.800x0uc.png\"><figcaption>Astringents have no place in my routine these days. Instead, I'm reaching for this moisturizing toner from Renée Rouleau that contains hydration-boosting ingredients like omega-3, 6, and 9 and niacinamide to improve skin-barrier function and hold moisture inside.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599159632982-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This gadget isn't an ingredient, but I have to mention it because it's one of the best skincare purchases I've made in the last few years. I know that fall brings on a desire to warm up, but this soothing facial massager brings on an epic big chill that helps to calm the skin immediately.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599091841281-image.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Over-exfoliation is certainly a concern once dry-skin season creeps in, but that doesn't mean I'll be shying away from the full-body exfoliators that keep my skin smooth, glowy, and primed to absorb all my favorite moisturizers.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599150750480-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This tingly scrub brings in both physical and chemical exfoliation with pumice scrubbers and glycolic, lactic, and salicylic acids. It's pH optimized, meaning it won't disrupt the skin's delicate microbiome. It also infuses marula oil into the skin for lasting moisture.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599151649841-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Super hard isn't a term I'm typically drawn to when it comes to skincare, but in this case, it works. This no-frills nylon towel allows you to carry out spa-level skin exfoliation using just your favorite oil or hydrating bodywash and a bit of elbow grease. When I tell you my skin feels like a straight-up seal after every use, I mean that.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599092701356-image.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Capturing the aroma of spooky season always involves a dismissal of the light, fruity notes of summer and the embrace of sensual, spicy smells that mingle so beautifully with the crisp fall air. Fragrance inhabits a top spot on my beauty checklist these days, so I'm putting a lot of emphasis on transitioning my scent wardrobe to meet the mood of the new season.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599154864359-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This scent is just perfect. It smells nostalgic and familiar but also super chic and unique. I love how the spicy black pepper in the top notes mixes with the warm, creamy base. It's sultry and complex and earns me tons of compliments.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288962/summer-to-fall-beauty-swaps-288962-1599157438216-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>I'll be switching up the fragrance story throughout my entire home this season, too. Everyone talks about pumpkin- or cinnamon-scented candles as soon as fall hits, but can I tempt you with this heavenly offering from Diptyque that smells just like a crackling fireplace, instead? It's woody and not spicy, but it totally evokes the moody, cozy theme of the chillier days ahead. href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/venice-film-festival-2019\" target=\"_blank\">Venice Film Festival</a> looks a little different this year, but the point is that it's actually happening. In-person and with a red carpet. Strict <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=wDx8J_YaMVYCa2XgPxj_LFo1RrPQXFsRRYVen7l2z5t4eVJNqPEtzJnPn-HZO0LaAG8IEwaoshhYGwGJbKalMZHiEhcOwJ42Y_7rk275hHWzLT8wrjdoFqQ3W8Ugh2h_YZazc1QksZu2kA8IRoenKj4tdIO6kDg2mqkz_0rVzOXamNNrzVlpDSrzKcKeYI-nQmFkwOkMQw\" target=\"_blank\">testing and quarantine guidelines</a> for the attendees, restrictions on international travel due to the pandemic, and fewer American festival entries than usual means that attendees are mostly European this year. But among them <em>are</em> some well-known faces such as jury president Cate Blanchett, Tilda Swinton, and model Taylor Hill. </p><p>Scrolling through the red carpet photos from the festival is a reminder that the COVID-19 pandemic certainly hasn't gone anywhere, as masks are required except when attendees are being photographed (but luckily, the red carpet is huge and outdoors). Perhaps the potential success of this festival is an indicator of how future similar events (i.e. awards shows and movie premieres) will go, but in the meantime, this is the only red carpet eye candy we have at the moment, and it doesn't disappoint.</p><p>Keep scrolling to see the best looks from the 2020 Venice Film Festival, and be sure to check back as we'll be adding more through September 12 when the festival concludes.</p><p><em>Opening image: Daniele Venturelli/WireImage</em></p><p><figure><img 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"My Podiatrist Told Me a Secret: These Surprising Shoes Cause Foot Pain","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/QLXxPRDVMG0/sneakers-and-foot-pain","description":"<p>Last autumn, there was a period of about a month or two when merely walking from my apartment to my office (about a mile in New York) was causing chronic, searing pain in my right foot. Really, walking anywhere was painful—to the grocery store, to the park, to the subway. In other words, it was a huge pain in a literal and metaphorical sense. Finally, I decided to seek help <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/podiatrist-approved-house-shoes\" target=\"_blank\">by way of a podiatrist</a>, Joseph Alencherry, DPM, and what I learned from that visit has not only enlightened the way I view footwear but also subsequently caused these shooting pains to dissipate. Yes, there's a happy ending here.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/266099/undefined-266099-1536270359866-image.0x800uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>By the time I got to Alencherry’s office, I already knew we’d be talking about the elephant in the room: bunions. I did <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/kate-moss-ballet-flats\" target=\"_blank\">ballet</a> for over 15 years, so I have small(ish) bunions. If you don’t know what these are, you’re one of the lucky ones. As explained on Alencherry’s website, bunions are “an enlargement on the big toe … and misalignment of the joint at that location.” What happens, the site goes on to explain, is that the deformity reshapes the big toe inward, causing inflammation and—bluntly—pain.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/266099/undefined-266099-1536270361462-image.0x800uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Inflammation and pain… sounds about right. They're not caused strictly by ballet, of course. The <strong>major causes of bunions are genetics, r</strong><strong>heumatoid arthritis, and </strong><strong>i</strong><strong>mproperly fitting shoes.</strong></p><p>That last one is typically what people like myself associate with bunions. <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-pumps\" target=\"_blank\">Wear high heels </a>too often? Bunions. Wear pointe shoes for an excess of years? Bunions. Well, it turns out there’s a surprising twist to this story…</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/266099/undefined-266099-1536270364250-image.0x800uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>When I arrived at my appointment, he did, in fact, call me out on said bunions, but his follow-up shocked me a bit. In fact, I may or may not have expected a high-five when he asked me what shoes I wore and I quickly and confidently proclaimed that I don’t really wear heels anymore. Instead, he stopped me and explained that heels aren’t the only shoe culprits behind foot pain, pointed to my sneakers (a pair of Supergas), and said that even low-to-the-ground shoes—sneakers or flats—can create legitimate foot pain if they push your toes together. <em>Say what?</em></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/266099/undefined-266099-1536270365314-image.0x800uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p class=\"p1\">Sure, I knew that wearing heels causes your toes to slide forward and squish together. But the notion that even <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/emily-ratajkowski-sneakers\" target=\"_blank\">a pair of sneakers</a> could be unsafe was mindblowing to me. After some X-rays, my rejecting a cortisone shot because I hate needles, and a painful walk back to the office, I got to thinking about my shoe closet.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/266099/undefined-266099-1536270365699-image.0x800uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>What I found was an assortment of shoes meant for people with narrow feet. Sneakers, loafers,<a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/section/ankle-boots\" target=\"_blank\"> ankle boots</a>, a few high heels I refuse to part ways with—all, for the most part, narrow. Now knowing that I had to make a change and that surgery wasn’t going to be it, I started investing in and wearing footwear that offers different widths, and it reversed my pain.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/266099/undefined-266099-1536270825997-main.0x800uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Moral of the story: Shoes are fun and not to be avoided, but wear any one style in moderation, and make sure you have a handful of pairs that let your toes spread out and chill out.</span></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Any of the above sound familiar? <em>Scroll down for some pain-free footwear picks including options with wide fits.</em></span></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/266099/sneakers-and-foot-pain-266099-1596577182646-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>There's a reason nearly everyone on our team owns these cool and comfortable sandals.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/266099/sneakers-and-foot-pain-266099-1596576894119-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Yup, Tevas are still elegant.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/266099/sneakers-and-foot-pain-266099-1596577328416-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Get some height without sacrificing comfort.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/266099/sneakers-and-foot-pain-266099-1596577613049-main.1660x1783uc.jpg\"><figcaption>The reviews on Photogenic","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/DvA-EaMZ97I/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s","description":"<p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998662970-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>If you've been reading our beauty content for a while now on Who What Wear, you're likely already familiar with one of our favorite lifestyle, beauty, and fashion bloggers, <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=l0lNuWS-mmg4MM1wAWXyTPMSBlid5j1La7xnf5gvxX0K2-QTQHSj1LWG-HiUH_mxqXUjMQ3TUpk\" target=\"_blank\">Melissa Meyers</a> (also known as <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=c1L-Mr7JNUEk7CFx0i5smEgiE412jjn5_7CIZqYWcHckjKEhL5GYxe3DkKA\" target=\"_blank\">The Glow Girl</a>). Not only is Meyers practically a savant when it comes to navigating clean, nontoxic beauty, but she also loves to routinely share her best tips and tricks when it comes to aging. Refreshingly, Meyers is all about <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/clean-beauty-products-for-mature-skin\" target=\"_blank\">embracing the aging process</a> and empowering women to be the best version of themselves—whether that's taking the leap and experimenting with <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/hair-products-for-women-over-50\" target=\"_blank\">clean beauty products</a>, <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-nontoxic-self-tanners\" target=\"_blank\">embracing self-tanners</a> (instead of the sun), or just knowing the best and most effective makeup hacks. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998670792-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Being the font of knowledge that she is and in light of the COVID-19 outbreak, we reached out to Meyers for her best makeup and skin tips—quarantine edition. Now that everyone is under strict stay-at-home orders and taking video calls at all hours is the new normal, we asked Meyers to share her best skincare and makeup tips. In other words, what can we do to look as photogenic and bright-eyed as possible? Keep scrolling for 10 beauty tricks Meyers always abides by before jumping in front of her screen.</p><p>Yes, that's plural! According to Meyers, one of her best-kept secrets for looking refreshed and keeping her skin plump and hydrated is prepping her skin pre-camera with a face mask catered to her main skin concerns and using a separate masking formula to address the delicate eye area. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998678239-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998804093-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"This certified-organic treatment mask uses rose-hip seeds and quartz to polish and refine the skin,\" she explains to me, noting it's a great way to prep the complexion before tackling a day filled with Zoom calls.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998681324-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998800391-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"These award-winning eye masks are a quick, easy fix for de-puffing and reducing dark under-eye circles,\" says Meyers. \"I pop them on for 15 minutes in the morning to help brighten my eyes for the day.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p>Even though video calls aren't the highest-quality (aka you probably can't see every line and pore as you would IRL), the goal is still to have radiant and dewy skin with coverage that mimics the health of your natural skin. The best way to accomplish this? Seasoning your canvas with a luxe oil to aid in hydration. To boost your glow even further, Meyers likes to work the oil into her complexion using a rose quartz gua sha tool. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998690053-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998793558-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"Hydrating and anti-aging, this natural, collagen-boosting face oil creates a perfect canvas to prime skin for that no-makeup makeup look,\" says Meyers who co-created this specific formula with Olie. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998696310-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998790022-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"This must-have tool from Miranda Kerr’s clean beauty line helps massage any face oil into the skin while getting out all the TMJ kinks—it's a daily ritual that keeps me glowing,\" Meyers swears. </figcaption></figure></p><p>Yep—your skin can still reap damage from the sun or from the blue light emitted from your laptop and phone. Meyers tells me she likes to multitask with coverage and SPF protection by opting for lightweight BB creams or tinted moisturizers that soften and diffuse the look of her skin for video calls while staving off any potentially damaging light. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998785995-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"This unique formula is my go-to for tinted coverage and sun protection—it’s so lightweight and leaves skin with a velvety texture,\" shares Meyers.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998780856-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>She's also a huge fan of Ilia's latest skin wonder, a weightless, light-coverage tinted serum containing hyaluronic acid and SPF. \"This new multitasker leaves skin with a dewy finish and comes in 18 shades,\" she praises.</figcaption></figure></p><p>Meyers tells me she loves to play up her eyes when she's preparing for a full day of video calls or photos. Her secret? Creamy, bronze-hued eye shadow and some concealer for a dose of strategic camouflage. She also recommends sticking with clean formulas, which can be less irritating to the sensitive eye area discouraging any pesky redness. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998777730-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"I love how this shade of bronze helps eyes pop on the Zoom screen and also nurtures the sensitive skin around the eyes,\" says Meyers.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998773102-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>If your goal is to look more bright-eyed (especially for those early morning video calls), Meyers says this is the perfect opportunity to add a light, hydrating concealer to your get-ready mix. Simply tap a bit of the formula wherever you have shadows and circles, and then dab and blend it out to diffuse so you don't end up with buildup or annoying creasing. </figcaption></figure></p><p>Sure, pretty much any mascara will draw attention to your eyes and enhance your lash line, but for those looking to beef up your natural lashes (which thin as we age), Meyers recommends choosing a clean formula that's enhanced with growth- and thickness-boosting conditioners and ingredients. Not only will your lashes receive instant gratification, but they may get stronger and healthier over time as well. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998761056-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"This conditioning mascara has the perfect applicator—the formula nourishes lashes and gives them lots of thickness and length,\" shares Meyers.</figcaption></figure></p><p>Makeup artists always wax poetic about the importance of maintaining, shaping, and caring for your brows. (Like our lashes, brows can thin and lose their shade and luster as we get older.) Luckily, that's nothing a great eyebrow pencil can't handle.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998754885-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"This universal-colored pencil beautifully blends eyebrow hair so that they look thicker and darker,\" Meyers tells me. </figcaption></figure></p><p>Adding a pop of creamy color to your cheeks can make all the difference when it comes to looking well-rested, youthful, and vibrant. In fact, you'll want to go a little more heavy-handed with your application than you would for face-to-face encounters since the color translates less intensely over your video calls. (Same goes for your mascara application!) </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998748846-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"Dab this organic blush on the apples of your cheeks to stay looking vibrant and rosy even after hours and hours of video calls,\" suggests Meyers.</figcaption></figure></p><p>By now we all know that sitting out in the sun (especially sans SPF) is one of the worst things you can do for your skin as we get older. If you are going to be outside for hours, please douse yourself in sunscreen to keep skin damage at bay. Or do like Meyers and feign the look of a sun-kissed glow with a nontoxic bronzer instead. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998745447-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"This perfect bronzing powder creates the illusion of sun-kissed skin to look refreshed and healthy when your face is front and center on the screen,\" Meyers shares.</figcaption></figure></p><p>Youthful skin is often attributed to bright and radiant skin, but that's just not always attainable—even for those of us in our 20s or 30s! Therefore, wrinkle-, line-, and spot-diffusing highlighters can be a game-changing addition to your routine, and they can add a touch of warmth and luminosity to your complexion. Just make sure you don't choose a formula that's too glittery or disco ball–esque in its finish. This can actually draw more attention to fines lines, texture issues, and the like.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998709023-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998740226-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>A best seller, this hydrating and calming luminizer is one of Meyers's favorites. She says it helps soften and brighten the skin to give her complexion a bit of shimmery highlight that translates beautifully on-screen.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998737528-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"This is a multipurpose polish delivering luminous warmth for eyes, cheeks, and face,\" says Meyers. \"The bronze-gold color, especially, looks gorgeous on all skin tones.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998733347-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Last but not least, this natural highlighter comes in a stick form and delivers light-reflecting radiance to highlight your favorite features. \"I keep it in my desk drawer and swipe it on my cheekbones right before Zooming,\" adds Meyers.</figcaption></figure></p><p>Lips (like our hands, necks, even our brows) are one of the features that can easily be forgotten but can be a dead giveaway for your age. Not that that's a bad thing, but keeping your pout plump, shiny, and hydrated acts as a filter of sorts for lines, wrinkles, and loss of volume, which can all intensify as we get older. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998718181-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998728616-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Meyers is a fan of this silky, CBD-spiked gloss that feels soothing on the lips and comes in a variety of photogenic shades. (She's especially fond of this shimmery nude hue called Bliss.)
