6/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998709023-main.1200x1365uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx6/cdn78@2020_6/2020/09/05/08-42-23-921_438ae3ac2f29789a.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998740226-main.1200x1200uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx7/cdn56@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-42-32-479_9e90d4c5cc06b9b5.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998737528-main.1200x1200uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx6/cdn96@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-41-57-686_a02ae58fb30c2b3b.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998733347-main.1200x1200uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx7/cdn66@2020_6/2020/09/05/08-41-59-605_e27635e3a7e97ef6.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998718181-main.1200x1365uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx22/cdn25@2020_3/2020/09/05/08-42-48-215_c5bc3f82649117a9.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287346/how-to-look-photogenic-in-your-50s-287346-1589998728616-main.1200x1200uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx10/cdn83@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-42-33-687_0b29514fff9dbc24.webp","http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~4/DvA-EaMZ97I":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx13/cdn47@2020_6/2020/09/05/08-42-20-871_3c31ed81c0795e7d.webp"},"publishedOrCreatedDate":1599295287269},{"createdTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"Commit These Top Designer Jewelry Brands to Memory","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/q0KvIOKRoN0/designer-jewelry-brands","description":"<p>On the whole, jewelry never goes out of style. No matter the decade or the trend, the unique designs of earrings, necklaces, bracelets, and rings have served as both statement pieces and daily accessories. Whether pearl, gold, silver, rose gold, diamond, or something else entirely,<a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/jewelry-trends-2020\" target=\"_blank\"> a good jewelry piece </a>can stand alone, completing your outfit and adding the right amount of elegance and sparkle. As much as we love our day-to-day pieces, though, we're always on the hunt for new ones to add to our collection, ones we will hopefully be able to pass on as family heirlooms. And so, more often than not, to acquire a piece that will outlast trends and generations, you have to invest in designer jewelry brands.</p><p>Whether it's a renowned Cartier Love Bracelet or a classic Mikimoto pearl necklace, there are so many designers elevating jewelry and creating pieces that are worth every penny. To streamline <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/jewelry-brands\" target=\"_blank\">the best designer jewelry brands</a> in the market for you, we decided to put the 10 best in this article. From brands whose clothing you already love (hi, Hermès and Chanel) to labels who've been perfecting their craft for so many years, make sure you commit them to your memory.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1599239063529-main.1200x1599uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Blame it on the classic Audrey Hepburn film <em>Breakfast at Tiffany's</em>, but there's something undeniably timeless about anything from this age-old jewelry designer.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1544405612055-product.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>If you didn't know, chain jewelry is a big trend for 2020.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1589827941716-main.1432x1432uc.jpg\"><figcaption>A classic Tiffany piece.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1544405612164-product.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Did somebody say sparkle? </figcaption></figure></p><p>Another classic jewelry brand is Cartier. Get yourself one of its iconic Love bracelets or something classic such as a necklace.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1575655482730-main.2474x2474uc.png\"><figcaption>Not a TSA-friendly bracelet, but still very pretty.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1575655406412-main.1720x1290uc.png\"><figcaption>A necklace that will last forever.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1589828146003-main.1200x1300uc.jpg\"><figcaption>So pretty. </figcaption></figure></p><p>David Yurman emerged onto the jewelry scene in 1980, but that hasn't stopped it from creating pieces destined to be in your jewelry box forever. If you're buying your first piece, go for something that feature's the brand's signature rope-style twist.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1589828312838-main.1660x2118uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Silver + diamonds = a combination made in jewelry heaven.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1589828339272-main.1660x1785uc.jpg\"><figcaption>A future family heirloom.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1589828385967-main.1660x1547uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This bracelet is worth the investment.</figcaption></figure></p><p>If you aren't familiar with Mikimoto, it's about to become one of your favorite designers yet. The Japanese jewelry brand's founder is known as the first to create cultured pearls, which means you know that this brand will have some of the best out there.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1589828503970-main.1660x2155uc.jpg\"><figcaption>A true classic. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1544406085712-product.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>We're always down for a good hoop. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1544406086764-product.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>You can never have enough pearls.</figcaption></figure></p><p>If you're looking for something that feels more exotic than your classic gems, Bvlgari's pieces feel like those Cleopatra might wear if she were alive today.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1575656315216-main.1800x1405uc.png\"><figcaption>This is easily one of the coolest rings you'll have.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1575656308466-main.1800x1405uc.png\"><figcaption>We're loving the fan-like pendant on this necklace. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1575656300849-main.1800x1405uc.png\"><figcaption>So colorful and pretty. </figcaption></figure></p><p>Could there be anything more lust-worthy than something from Harry Winston? As the brand responsible for some of the most famous diamonds to date, there's no doubt any piece from the designer is worth the investment.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1544407409047-product.0x800uc.jpg\"><figcaption>The shinier, the better. Price available upon request from the brand.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1544407409305-product.0x800uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Opt for a classic diamond in a pear shape.  Price available upon request from the brand.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1544407409382-product.0x800uc.jpg\"><figcaption>We're in love with these drop earrings. Price available upon request from the brand.</figcaption></figure></p><p>When it comes to luxury, no one does it quite like Hermès. Sure, you know the brand for its signature Birkin Bag, but it also has some amazing jewelry worthy of a spot in your collection, too.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1589829122610-main.1100x1100uc.jpg\"><figcaption>When an iconic bag becomes a bracelet.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1589828993722-main.1100x1100uc.jpg\"><figcaption>How good is this ring?</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1589829061948-main.1100x1100uc.jpg\"><figcaption>You'll never want to take them off.</figcaption></figure></p><p>Perhaps you've become familiar with Chopard with its luxury watches, which feature the brand's signature Happy Diamonds. Well, its jewelry equally as cool. Whether you opt for a piece that features the Happy Diamonds or not, these pieces are sure to stand out.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1589830164215-main.2000x2622uc.jpg\"><figcaption>So cute. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1544407807332-product.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Add this bracelet to your collection.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1589830174046-main.2000x3001uc.jpg\"><figcaption>If you're looking for a pair of jaw-dropping earrings, these are for you.</figcaption></figure></p><p>No matter what you get from Chanel—whether it's a classic handbag, a ready-to-wear piece, or something else, you know it'll be the epitome of chic. If you're looking for something to wear every day, embrace the famous fashion house with a shiny bauble.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1589830410010-main.1240x1240uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Dainty and pretty. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1544408418937-product.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Such a nice statement bracelet. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1589830464435-main.2049x1906uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This ring is a forever piece.</figcaption></figure></p><p>French luxury jewelry and watch designer Van Cleef & Arpels carries a unique, old-school touch to all of its pieces. If you aren't sure where to start, get yourself something that showcases the brand's classic Clover motif, or a simple bracelet to wear with all of your ensembles. There's no going wrong here.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1544408418844-product.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>So is this one. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1589830664111-main.800x0uc.png\"><figcaption>This necklace will make you feel like royalty. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/274612/designer-jewelry-brands-274612-1544408419033-product.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>And so will this but… I can count on my hands how many times I've put on makeup since shelter-in-place orders started in March. In the pre-pandemic world, I had a very subtle makeup vibe anyway: A dab of concealer under my eyes, a stroke of mascara on my lashes, and a swipe of moisturizing lip balm, and I'd be set for the day. So it's not like I've been skipping out on a major look for myself, but that hasn't stopped me from wishing I'd just done those little extra steps whenever I preview my face before logging onto a Zoom meeting. It doesn't seem like that's ever going to happen, though, so I'm looking to alternatives for getting my signature no-makeup-makeup look, without the makeup altogether.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=NngR6iG0OE5B4d9nxiJ-4bBiVQXTEngnZocKruY0kUL6WvDAvA\" target=\"_blank\">Vegamour</a>'s plant-based line of hair-growth products for lashes, brows, and hair is exactly what I was hoping for. Unlike my makeup regimen, my skincare routine has, if anything, improved since going into lockdown, so applying a serum to my lashes, brows, and scalp after showering is as effortless as any rote habit. The brand uses fair-trade and hormone-free bio-active phytomolecules to open more hair follicles on the scalp and for longer periods of time, thus restoring and promoting more visible hair growth. In just four months of continued use, you'll see more hair density, volume, and length. Vegamour also promises reduced shedding and zero negative side effects. So whether you're looking for a way to simplify achieving a no-makeup look or giving more body to your head of hair, you'll want to check out Vegamour's line of hair growth products.</p><section 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"Oprah's Eyebrow Artist Told Us the Best Brows for Every Face Shape","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/rZG9Qd2oZMk/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape","description":"<p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282686/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape-282686-1570409542228-main.1200x900uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Eyebrows are one of the first things people see when they look at our faces. And while many of us spent the '90s and early 2000s doing everything in our power to make our eyebrows as thin as humanly possible, the trend has definitely shifted in favor of fuller, <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/how-to-get-shape-eyebrows/\" target=\"_blank\">more prominent brows</a>. Thank goodness for <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-eyebrow-makeup\" target=\"_blank\">eyebrow pencils and growth serum</a>.</p><p>Now that we've given our handy tweezers a break, we have so many more options when it comes to eyebrow shape. But all brows are not created equal. According to celebrity brow artists <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=KbpVh3C-89RMswcOJwpAfan8LJ56p_GGdBD9V236Wew6ZqtphmxSn5hxP1-aeA\" target=\"_blank\">Damone Roberts</a> and <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=RxKK426_ZcL8UF5SNyRJg4KoUKr2Qf5V_jp7mKaZFjyD9L9Jwwg_0vyUu50X\" target=\"_blank\">Kelley Baker</a>, whose client rosters boast celebs from Oprah to the Kardashians, there's much to consider. One of the most important factors in determining the best direction to take with eyebrows? <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/what-is-my-face-shape\" target=\"_blank\">Face shape</a>. Ahead, get their expert tips for how to pick the best eyebrows for your face shape.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282686/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape-282686-1570492551589-main.1200x1754uc.jpg\"><figcaption>According to the pros, the name of the game for those with square faces is to soften the features with subtle, rounded brows. \"When you have an angular face, we would soften the brows and round them out a little bit, or soften them and give more of a shorter Audrey Hepburn boy brow,\" says Baker, who created lovely boy brows for square-faced goddess Shay Mitchell. Celebs with this face shape: Shay Mitchell, Angelina Jolie, Sandra Bullock</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282686/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape-282686-1570492511428-image.1200x1754uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282686/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape-282686-1570492512357-image.1200x1754uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282686/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape-282686-1570492609681-main.1200x1754uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"Some arching is good here, if we can, to lift and open the eyes,\" says Baker. \"The rounder the face, the higher the arch to add length. But I do caution against going overboard, which tends to make one appear stern and angry,\" says Roberts, who's responsible for Oprah's perfectly round-face-complementing arches.  Celebs with this face shape: Oprah, Chrissy Teigen, Selena Gomez</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282686/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape-282686-1570492513475-image.1200x1754uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282686/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape-282686-1570492514025-image.1200x1754uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282686/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape-282686-1570492639815-main.1200x1754uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Longer, rectangular faces are best complemented with straighter brows, according to our experts. \"As soon as brows start to look too angled, they age people. So I always like a softer shape to keep a more youthful look in the face,\" says Baker.  Roberts agrees, adding that \"full brows leaning more toward the straighter side look beautiful.\"  Celebs with this face shape: Tracee Ellis Ross, Sarah Jessica Parker, Joan Smalls</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282686/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape-282686-1570492515036-image.1200x1754uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282686/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape-282686-1570492515724-image.1200x1754uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282686/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape-282686-1570492669458-main.1200x1754uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Since oval-shaped faces have some similar qualities to both long and round faces, our pros advise going for a subtle shape that adds to the depth without adding more length.\"Obviously, if your face is round, we don't want to give you round brows, because then there's no dimension,\" says Baker. \"We want a defined brow with a subtle arch. Just not too extreme,\" adds Roberts. Celebs with your face shape: Beyoncé, Alexa Chung, Jessica Alba </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282686/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape-282686-1570492516625-image.1200x1754uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282686/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape-282686-1570492517275-image.1200x1754uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282686/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape-282686-1570492716265-main.1200x1754uc.jpg\"><figcaption>For those with heart-shaped faces, the goal is to shorten the face a bit while also creating a brow that's large enough to fill out the ample forehead real estate available. \"A heart-shaped face should have the least of an arch, as you don't want to add more length. Keep it on the straighter side, which shortens the face,\" Roberts explains. Celebs with this face shape: Kourtney Kardashian,Kerry Washington, Reese Witherspoon </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282686/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape-282686-1570492518952-image.1200x1754uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282686/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape-282686-1570492519755-image.1200x1754uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282686/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape-282686-1570492744797-main.1200x1754uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Diamond-shaped faces have a bit more freedom when it comes to selecting a brow shape. Since the forehead tends to be smaller and the face tends to be longer, you might think thin, straight brows would be the only way to go. But since the shape can take on so many different looks depending on fullness, there's a lot of room to play. Roberts just has one pro tip: \"Not too defined, with a nice arch.\"  Celebs with your face shape: Jennifer Lopez, Rihanna, Halle Berry</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282686/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape-282686-1570492520304-image.1200x1754uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282686/best-eyebrows-for-face-shape-282686-1570492518287-image.1200x1754uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Up next, this is how to grow thicker eyebrows. freshen up your wardrobe with clothing that <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-colors-wear-for-skin-tone-light-medium-dark-2014\" target=\"_blank\">complements your skin tone</a>, you’ve come to the right place. We reached out to <em><a title=\"More Alive With Color\" href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=gj2Hi9V35DkFQzmQaFRW76ljqjNvACjNwaPzm4Wn7WAc2dXZpDFWdyOJ-A\" target=\"_blank\">More Alive With Color</a></em> author and Pantone Color Institute Director <a title=\"Leatrice Eiseman\" href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=ev4rGmXKAmT8pMC6DcylW_BvhnE6MuGsGtt_Cri5h2H3G2yabswLPSPZsHvbJ0Y1CqNROJkPHClr2o38HfAsSL_ws22EPU_mshETzjW2WGDkx_WFw6Ut7tGpqUIqkpoeTdkRAINJG9wsn3ou\" target=\"_blank\">Leatrice Eiseman</a> for her expert color-reading advice. Eiseman has written no less than 10 different books on color, so we knew she'd be the perfect expert to tap. </p><p>Of course, anyone can wear any color they please—that goes without saying—but it never hurts to have an especially complementary color to rely on when you're facing a <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/custom-closet-design\" target=\"_blank\">closet full of clothes</a> but aren't sure what to wear. Below, <a title=\"Eiseman\" href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=LDs4DWsyOEpqKTFQiV5qHglNXg0x0K0gi_AJW3SaT6HVjORuU1Hi3M6brPxMJHAHWfuk\" target=\"_blank\">Eiseman</a> tells us how to easily pick out our most complimentary colors. From shades of blue to light ivory hues, she walks us through the best options for a variety of skin tones. 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"The Prettiest Fall Trend Can Cost as Little as $3 But Looks So Expensive","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/tarcLpBV-oI/bows-fashion-trend","description":"<p>Maybe it’s just me, but I happen to think that you can throw a black bow on pretty much any article of clothing and it will look instantly elevated. From tops and sweaters to casual dresses and evening gowns, there’s something about the little—<em>or big, depending on the case</em>—detail that just feels fancy. That’s why I was quite pleased this past February when I noticed countless bows in velvet, satin, and grosgrain going down the runways of so many of our favorite brands and on a range of pieces. A memory I recently revisited while doing another <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/fall-trend-shopping-guide-2020\" target=\"_blank\">deep dive into F/W 20 trends</a> last month.  </p><p>What’s especially great about this one in particular, however, is that while it does look and certainly can be expensive, it can also cost you as little as $3, as long as you’re not opposed to an easy DIY. All you need to do is buy the ribbon or pre-tied bows—<a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=9S3byQQS2riOT_G3zoPp04XSELBl9_KVdfI_SFH0VFaGZ-3xce27ZEnNYj6BaaAGt3Q5oxhavjkmaaVJedxsBytMHDGfxmW0P2cR-YbMsURg_9TekJ7jg8F8NOztNcXCto0PbqR-qkIJ0U80CNcPxqNoM-U0-dgfhTt2b099LgosItCTeoLUSGJeLv-LZaIVzMuonaSrZ-XUsyVTEp82va1TC5gfo6mcHhU\">Amazon is a gold mine of them</a>—and sew or simply pin them to any piece you already own. Voila! An instant upgrade awaits. To see the best runway moments featuring the trend and shop ribbons, bows, and clothing that already features them along the way, just keep scrolling.</p><p><figure><img .com/posts/288983/bows-fashion-trend-288983-1599147389265-main.2000x2000uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx24/cdn23@2020_1/2020/09/05/08-42-38-325_82d8b8140a759406.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288983/bows-fashion-trend-288983-1599146109034-image.1200x1598uc.jpg":null,"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288983/bows-fashion-trend-288983-1599149170766-main.960x1450uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx/cdn61@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-43-03-970_1deac8e4f458e6e6.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288983/bows-fashion-trend-288983-1599149169932-main.960x1450uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx21/cdn53@2020_6/2020/09/05/08-41-45-578_889551f07218b3ed.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288983/bows-fashion-trend-288983-1599146103918-image.1200x1598uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx12/cdn87@2020_6/2020/09/05/08-42-24-627_a857749713f754d6.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288983/bows-fashion-trend-288983-1599147319673-main.1500x1500uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx2/cdn4@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-42-07-341_758e1f177dfdab5a.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288983/bows-fashion-trend-288983-1599148200853-main.2000x2999uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx22/cdn81@2020_3/2020/09/05/08-42-44-976_481b83bf04db98a3.webp","http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~4/tarcLpBV-oI":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx5oss/cdn94@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-42-09-768_36c0c599035a2a23.webp"},"publishedOrCreatedDate":1599295287272},{"createdTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"The Byredo Scents That Are Worth the Money, Ranked by Me","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/L8yba3sCgGY/byredo-perfume","description":"<p>At this point, I've at least smelled almost every <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=q1m7-eZ-sxEDZEfnlPcDVSQiw1QPhIHZSF5C9hVp0upBo23BeyoRVD5XyBWf\" target=\"_blank\">Byredo</a> fragrance there is. It's easy to see why the Stockholm-based brand is so popular; in addition to the incredibly chic and minimal packaging, the unisex scents are as unique as they come yet undoubtedly wearable and intriguing as well. Trust me—everyone will ask you what <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/top-perfumes-for-women\" target=\"_blank\">scent</a> you're wearing when you spray on Byredo, and anything you buy from the brand is worthy of the price tag, but I'm here to help you narrow it down (there are so many good ones to choose from).</p><p>For my own <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/fall-perfumes\" target=\"_blank\">fragrance</a>-buying mission and for <em>your</em> fragrance-buying missions (I'm here to serve), I asked Byredo to send me samples of their best-selling scents, and they kindly obliged. Over the past few weeks, I've been switching up my scent on a daily basis, because variety is the spice of life, and I wanted to give you my honest reviews of the 10 most popular Byredo perfumes.</p><p>There are plenty of fragrance reviews out there, but I find them to be quite technical, speaking to all of the different layered notes in a scent. My reviews are more about how they'll make you feel when wearing them, the best occasions and seasons to wear them for, how versatile they are, etc. Keep scrolling if you're intrigued and be sure to head all the way to the bottom for what I think is the best Byredo fragrance.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1591304512833-main.1080x1349uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Oud Immortel is a beautiful scent, and I was excited to get to try it, but for me, it was just a bit masculine. It was created around a certain type of dark wood that's used in traditional incense, so it's as smoky and complex as you'd imagine. While it may not be right for me, I'd buy a bottle for my husband in a second.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1591305965272-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1591304577651-main.1080x1349uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Mojave Ghost is one of Byredo's buzziest scents, so I was eager to try it. I do see why this one is so popular—it's a lovely option for evening but isn't sweet or overly floral in the least. It's soft and the floral aspect is soft and more woodsy, with a hint of sandalwood and amber. The only reason I don't think I'd adopt it is my signature scent is that it develops a bit of a powdery note on me as the day wears on, but some people may embrace that.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1575487845048-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1591304545045-main.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Byredo's Bibliothèque candles have an intense cult following (I'm a member of that cult), so it was wise of the brand to create a perfume. I honestly couldn't describe this scent to you if I tried, it's so unique. There is a rich patchouli note that is overarching though, so if you like expensive-smelling patchouli, you'll love this. Again, this one was a wee bit too masculine for me (but my love for the candle lives on), and I'd 100% buy it for my husband and require that he wear it every day.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1575488316568-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1591305274007-main.1080x1266uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Flowerhead is definitely the most floral scent in the bunch, and would make the perfect daytime scent in spring and summer. As is the norm for Byredo, it's a very complex floral that feels exotic and fresh. It certainly has signature scent potential but not really year-round.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1591305977629-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1591304920814-main.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Slow Dance is one of Byredo's newer fragrances; it launched just in time for fall. I'd seen it all over several cool girls' Instagrams, so I, too, had to try it. Like Bibliothèque, this one is also a bit tricky to describe. It definitely feels like a rich, cold-weather fragrance to me, and patchouli and vanilla are the base notes, but they're the most sophisticated versions of patchouli and vanilla you can imagine. If you like your scent to be warm and slightly sweet, this one's for you.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1575491346991-main.1034x1033uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1591304966949-main.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>The first of the two rose fragrances (more to come on the other soon), Rose Noir is a bit earthier of the two. Byredo describes it as \"dirty\", and I'd have to agree. It has some depth to it but is undeniably a rose lover's dream.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1591305987091-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1591304156198-main.1080x1080uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>I apparently live on the edge because I bought Velvet Haze without even smelling it a few months ago (the brand had me with the \"coconut water\" description). Luckily, I loved it. I prefer it for evening, as it's a bit musky, but it's also a great anytime scent during fall and winter. When I first sprayed it on, I was struck by the smell of patchouli but it softens beautifully. Highly recommend.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1575491400547-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1591305029987-main.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Bal d'Afrique is another one of the brand's cult favorites that I was so intrigued by. You just feel cool and in the know when wearing it. If I'm putting it simply, the incense is a notable layer, but very expensive and rare incense that you can only get in Africa.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1575493091597-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1591305067315-main.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>I'm always on the hunt for a cool rose fragrance and I really struck gold with this popular Byredo scent. It's subtle and fresh but with a hint of richness (thanks to the white amber base note). This is one of those rare scents that I'd be happy to wear every day, year-round. I'm probably going to have to add it to my collection.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1575493669430-main.1200x1199uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1591305124204-main.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>We've come to the end, friends, and my number one paycheck-worthy pic is Gypsy Water. Sorry, no surprise here! It's the brand's best-selling, most well-known, and most Instagrammed (I checked) scent, and for good reason. It's the one I reached for the most these past few weeks because wearing it just makes me happy. It smells of sandalwood and vanilla, lemon and campfire, and so many other things you would never believe could smell so intoxicatingly good together. It smells so beautiful that I don't even care that it's not particularly under the radar. I want to wear it constantly so that I can smell my wrist every time I need a pick me up.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/284172/byredo-perfume-284172-1575494181909-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><em>Next up: <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-chanel-perfumes\" target=\"_blank\">Every Woman Needs at Least One Chanel Perfume—These Are the 5 Best</a></em></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><em>This post was originally published at an earlier date and has since been updated.</em></span></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~4/L8yba3sCgGY\" height=\"1\" I'm in the mood to cut all my hair off. This is no common occurrence for me; as a <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/tracee-ellis-ross-pattern-beauty-review\" target=\"_blank\">coily-haired</a> queen who routinely heat styles my shoulder-length locks, I'm constantly seeking out ways to <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/hair-masks-for-thicker-hair\" target=\"_blank\">retain length</a>, not get rid of it. But, there's one haircut I keep seeing that is so chic and appealing that it's got me seconds away from scheduling a hair appointment at any given moment: the blunt bob.</p><p>You might be wondering why this particular cut speaks directly to my soul, and the answer is simple. Aside from the fact that <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/celebrity-new-haircut\" target=\"_blank\">every single celebrity </a>currently wearing the stark yet <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/short-hairstyles-for-older-women\" target=\"_blank\">playful cut looks</a> impossibly cool, the time has come for me to cut off some heat damage, and I'd like to do it in style. So, like a true beauty editor, I scoured the internet for the best blunt bobs to add to my \"new hair, who dis\" vision board. Ahead, 27 styles that are absolutely to die for.</p><p>Oh, and I'll be sure to keep you posted on my personal style switch-up, too.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/283105/blunt-bob-haircuts-283105-1571087921002-image.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>No one can rock a blunt bob (or any look, for that matter) quite like J.Lo.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/283105/blunt-bob-haircuts-283105-1571088385838-image.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>The lightness in the ends of this crisp crop keep it youthful and not too severe.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/283105/blunt-bob-haircuts-283105-1571088384957-image.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Kardashian's bob is sharply cut all the way around, but a little extra length in the front adds some more dimension and some more room to play while styling.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/283105/blunt-bob-haircuts-283105-1571083332559-image.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>An earlobe-grazing cut and a side part truly are a match made in hair heaven.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/283105/blunt-bob-haircuts-283105-1571087923450-image.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This side-swept bob has the perfect amount of texture for an effortlessly chic moment.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/283105/blunt-bob-haircuts-283105-1571087922168-image.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Gerber shows us how to soften this cut by adding a soft wave and perhaps a shine serum.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/283105/blunt-bob-haircuts-283105-1571083333929-image.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Bob-length box-braids? href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-fall-colors-to-wear\" target=\"_blank\">French girl</a>'s Instagram account from a mile away. The photos invariably include a plethora of Parisian rooftop views, posing in front of elegant doors, and lounging in the iconic green chairs in the Jardin des Tuileries. Don't get me wrong—this isn't a diss whatsoever. Listen, if I lived in France, I'd also be milking it for all the content it's worth. When it comes to French influencers on Instagram, I come for the Parisian scenery and stay for the <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/brands-french-girls-love\" target=\"_blank\">impeccable style</a>. </p><p>Now that we're inching towards fall, I decided to take do a bit of fun research on how the best-dressed French women on Instagram <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/new-ankle-boots-for-fall\" target=\"_blank\">wear boots</a>. A handful of boot trends emerged as common themes—and it's no coincidence that the women's followers were huge fans of the outfits. ttps://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx31/cdn31@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-41-35-676_72c0f7b5e2dc646f.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/279600/low-rise-bikini-279600-1596836047905-main.1080x1080uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx25/cdn7@2020_1/2020/09/05/08-42-43-662_7d2dc59d2b36da4e.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/279600/low-rise-bikini-279600-1596836222261-main.1128x2000uc.jpg":null,"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/279600/low-rise-bikini-279600-1596836447042-main.800x0uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx4/cdn83@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-41-38-693_54907fa1582c6b32.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/279600/low-rise-bikini-279600-1596836550938-main.2000x3000uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx25/cdn5@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-42-58-469_4a529884c56cfc47.webp","http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~4/8y8CSZsuCUI":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx24/cdn99@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-42-22-880_403affda0b9c403a.webp"},"publishedOrCreatedDate":1599295287276},{"createdTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"I Always Get Compliments on My Hair: Here's How I Do My Signature Waves","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/22_pB3_Qjpc/flat-iron-waves-tutorial","description":"<p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281028/flat-iron-waves-tutorial-281028-1562013948101-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>So here's the tea: I may be a beauty editor, but I <em>suck</em> at <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/section/hair\" target=\"_blank\">hair</a>. French braids? Can't do them. Fishtail braids? Impossible. I can't do updos. I can't do cool vintagey styles. I can't even make a chic chignon work. I only know how to do one thing with my hair and one thing only: flat iron waves.</p><p>Call it a signature hairstyle, call it the only hairstyle I actually know how to do… However we want to frame it, <strong>my relaxed, bendy waves seem to work pretty well for me.</strong> They're effortless and versatile; they take very few materials and very little time. Sometimes I add a <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/claw-hair-clips\" target=\"_blank\">hair clip</a> or a headband, but that's about as fancy as it gets. And yet, they earn me at least one compliment per day. </p><p>Learn this absurdly simple styling technique (which I've nailed down thanks to years of advice from stylists as well as my own personal trial and error), and I hope you'll find it as useful as I have. Keep scrolling for how to create the perfect flat-iron waves in 10 minutes or less!</p><p><strong>The materials:</strong></p><p><strong>- </strong>A 1-inch thick flat iron with adjustable heat settings</p><p><strong>- </strong>A heat protectant</p><p><strong>- </strong>A hair tie</p><p><strong>- </strong>Some texture spray (optional)</p><p><strong>- </strong>A hair accessory (optional)</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281028/flat-iron-waves-tutorial-281028-1562023525088-product.1150x1150uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281028/flat-iron-waves-tutorial-281028-1562023525929-product.1280x1280uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281028/flat-iron-waves-tutorial-281028-1562023526565-product.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281028/flat-iron-waves-tutorial-281028-1562023601954-product.0x800uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281028/flat-iron-waves-tutorial-281028-1562095092836-product.3000x3000uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281028/flat-iron-waves-tutorial-281028-1562095253972-main.1000x1000uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>The instructions:</strong></p><p>This technique will work best on anyone with hair lengths from a chin-length bob to just past the collar bone. (I have naturally straight hair, but I know it works on wavy textures, too.) <strong>All you need to do are the following seven steps.</strong></p><p><strong>1. </strong>Plug in your flat iron and set it to no more than 310 degrees. This is to protect your hair from burning to a crisp.</p><p><strong>2. </strong>Spritz your hair protectant all throughout your hair. </p><p><strong>3. </strong>Gather all the hair above your ears into a loose half ponytail on top of your head to get it out of the way for now. Secure it up there temporarily with your hair tie.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281028/flat-iron-waves-tutorial-281028-1562095494637-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>4. </strong>When you create waves in your hair, you're going to use two alternating motions. This is what gives the final result a more natural, tousled look. For both motions, you'll take a 1-inch think section of hair and place it between the flat iron plates. The first motion goes in an M-shape: with the inch-thick section of hair between the plates, you'll guide the flat ironin toward your face, then out, then back in at the ends. The other motion is simply to twist the flat iron (with hair between the plates) away from your face and hold it in that twisted position for about five seconds. Make sure to leave the ends out of the flat iron so they stay flat. Also, be sure not to brush the wave out while it's still hot, not even with your fingers, or you'll lose the shape.</p><p>When I'm waving this bottom layer of hair below my ears, I'm not super perfectionistic about it, because no one will really to see it when the look is all done. For some strands (like the hard-to-reach ones in the back), all I do is curve the ends inward. This allows you not to heat sections of hair that don't really need it. </p><p><strong>5. </strong>Once you're finished with the bottom layer of hair, let down the top. Part it where you like. Then repeat step four, with more attention to detail this time, all around your head. For the two strands of hair directly on either side of my face, I choose to use the wave motion that goes away from my face, to create a flattering curtain effect.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281028/flat-iron-waves-tutorial-281028-1562095497363-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281028/flat-iron-waves-tutorial-281028-1562023366255-product.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281028/flat-iron-waves-tutorial-281028-1562095042710-product.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281028/flat-iron-waves-tutorial-281028-1562023365316-product.1560x1960uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281028/flat-iron-waves-tutorial-281028-1598986381972-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281028/flat-iron-waves-tutorial-281028-1598986280041-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>6. </strong>For a messier bed head look, spray a dry texturizer throughout your hair. <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=I9tyC4FpVGmELNkLD-AmIJSUwEyvcZCsAhbWrQYJuMH-pH8kv7ULBKjhOMnlEVnULHui5QdKzXFcl461YEtihDxjCgobgm1HYtxezpY_4R9u7wqcA0f_W64rd1oUyuX1Po7FM4spksLkZbs7Q4FmstmBuouMcf_oNea1OXoyFd1X4k1Sa8PV10Ao3lshliqJPZK0XN5H9bLInhzvDZ3nyTmeJw\" target=\"_blank\">Kristen Ess</a> makes a great one that smells lovely and tousles your hair without leaving it crunchy. I also love Amika's beautifully packaged volumizing formula and Sam McKnight's <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=K24t5SoiBjim_KLk8QLhwgqFsqXdxvbJ3C_CM4T5KiN6vjWZ4Lgj2wXuZiAPblsA4nrWl-HI1a6G-Yw5hlbVIYo6WgUB0z-hQj4zPAW2-S53kP-iZFpTMl9P_amyWtCWvNWKeBK39qcIYJOzIvS5znT0SEgwr3uJSqOHumz8hjgy6dzbQULB2toFrOsiOnWUa0Drxu9qsTUCTE0ZwQgbJ6uENBiXvrPe0IdgvIDH4B9xuol4vzPqNOxcXnClQEl4EPzCNOhm9bk-pHI9Hno1klZpHxdyuuGFQCNrr6AYxOhImyHPmy9dNKncRfouvz-a1TOUShco6OWgbmaDdHd8UwOnMeOasHWcrdnpCITIPdGfi4U-p2aDYoJxk8vJk3NWUufJyyDz1g4L06JVmk82Rsn4jGieCa1UyKxZJs-f6YcL2Xyb1S1CzLUk7nAUkFL2d9WdpHQL1SWrH-tGBGdks1hVJ8jwICxzIOKisGSV6H6l1o0x46lB5ZAFbcR5GkK9Fb03v5p-nKEgu1Pi673dEGb72Trkou3S5fEyT_syBmE\" target=\"_blank\">Cool Girl Barely There Texture Mist</a>, whose name says it all. Then <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=f6fKuRzPLYenfmjIdNyfel9MwKQFzQAe8KDd9ZciiR6P44wJi0Y5CzD0V1Hiv4uwyIc4ZCnLjLkZxhXAr-kpO4djXMB5uSGe45yvbFYlrnHdETBc1fbrGdin87lcA62eLsfEjx2NJ7HTtOiT-yH8Tqm5cGNKuQcOAQdM5foGCoz0olARr2-ad4zsSE0ZhPh9UpvyhH3yRHA5Yyw4vj9J7tkRXrUedFPVOhWyAI9SME9xDO3TSGNJ9lBbBN2vPbfBYMg8Rhl_OiV9i7WoP6xVfamXHyG64RGDRQuMvwahuCK-zfcmjfu8VFygWYq-iw5Hhq4jqIO27dCc0wjeBNSudZaGpRTlRgBVJaK_s5UW9neyKEKc5ABnbeD6VQWk06MkO8fwRC8Ivv5ltH27F2ZDJT2ECvfE1VoSEtxar-ZDea3Sbeq5Zza8c_PYDzdjQOvinqJO029K5BfmkXaBflDcu3RIIvlGR61h-OJpFjbzP1qkQoSWAxcq-215w7XkhngOhIpaSjR-wBJtSWdtg7ZCdkbGm_m9uUvhMUc4LBr-Dtbm0WsTvFnvE8PGp28JmtmtRDYVIhSoQJxfYYvrOgqirZbcPxodL7Xr1jrffhLRGWoNhGGhaagGg0TQ6eQFm2RQ22ZBscPa6Q9djhZfokmgcfFcnP_iJnHPcQ1w6aQ1xLqa-ckPVr2F6mzJwFXawx4wW3AwZWr-Hc13nhZljAYHynPDUwg\" target=\"_blank\">Oribe</a> makes what is, in my opinion, one of the best-smelling texture sprays on the market.</p><p><strong>7. </strong>Add a whimsical hair clip, elegant headband, or just let your waves flow free. Once you get this routine down pat, it should only take about five or six minutes. </p><p><strong>There we have it! The only hairstyle I know how to do. At least it's a good one.</strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281028/flat-iron-waves-tutorial-281028-1562095501909-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img //cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281028/flat-iron-waves-tutorial-281028-1598986856440-main.1128x2000uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx11/cdn74@2020_6/2020/09/05/08-41-43-286_21e3d26c628bd46a.webp","http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~4/22_pB3_Qjpc":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx10/cdn95@2020_1/2020/09/05/08-42-47-754_71e7938a160c285d.webp"},"publishedOrCreatedDate":1599295287282},{"createdTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"We Tested the New Nontoxic Foundation That Rivals Giorgio Armani Luminous Silk","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/sKwnZ_aMKJw/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review","description":"<p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288933/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review-288933-1599166172658-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>I'm not going to mince words. Never have I ever (or at least not until a few weeks ago) been able to stomach a clean and/or natural foundation formula. I have painstakingly high standards when it comes to the finish, application, tone, and durability of my foundation, and nothing I ever tried felt up to snuff (or even close, for that matter). In fact, I would likely need another set of hands to count the number of times I excitedly applied a promising new and natural foundation alternative only to be instantaneously scandalized by the sticky or slippery texture, suspiciously off-base undertones, or lack of day- or night-enduring stamina. Simply put, if a foundation makes me look oily, discolored, or downright discombobulated, I will put it down and never touch it again. (The one exception has been Ilia's cult-loved <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=HdIsGXbL3d5agtnW5wyMoxEFIGY0Eb4HB-qvU2pQZVVFcmenmVCS_5cebX2CXY_S6JOU_jpEHDf8\" target=\"_blank\">Super Serum Skin Tint SPF 40</a>, which I'm absolutely obsessed with.)</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288933/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review-288933-1599166179644-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Believe me, I have wanted to love a clean foundation for a long, long time. I've amassed quite a few other natural makeup formulas I routinely use and recommend, but foundation is where I consistently get stuck. Even though consistency and finish have always been problematic (so many natural formulas are very oily or tacky), the lack of shades has been, and still is, completely unacceptable within the clean-beauty space. So when some of my favorite peeps over at clean-beauty retailer <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=ACqFjCOdxblVphn1zrVGXRM-jkZeZwnAcldOQyOcAMIrcWKSLH5PwxIpWCNDIKJVe3_l7c44Hcwe\" target=\"_blank\">Credo</a> popped into my inbox to tell me they were launching its first-ever private-label makeup brand, Exa, I was instantly intrigued. <em>I love Credo, so this one had to be a winner, right? </em></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288933/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review-288933-1599166197363-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Equipped with 43 shades that cater to a multitude of undertones, Exa is officially the most shade-inclusive makeup line in the clean-beauty category. But the magic doesn't end there. At $38, Exa's High Fidelity Foundation is significantly more affordable than most popular clean (and not so clean) foundations on the market, and the ingredients are impeccably dreamy and safe for all skin types. The vegan formula boasts a bouncy, satiny, featherlight consistency that's comparable to some of the most sought-after, makeup artist–approved options on the beauty market. But complexion-loving ingredients like peach extract, aloe vera, microalgae actives, maqui berry, and hyaluronic acid trick your skin into thinking you've just applied the most delicious of facial serums—not a foundation. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288933/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review-288933-1599166201945-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>The foundation is buildable, imparts a luminous result, and can be paired with its strategically designed partner in crime, Exa's Jump Start Smoothing Primer ($34), to take the results even further. Of course, all of this is just fine and dandy to say and promote, but my fellow beauty editor Courtney Higgs and I were skeptical. We were eager and hopeful but were still skeptical—especially because, during a prelaunch Zoom date, celebrity makeup artist Katey Denno revealed the foundation was comparable to her non-clean favorites like Chanel and Armani. So is the new Exa High Fidelity Foundation really as table-shaking as it sounds? Courtney and I are sharing our honest ratings and reviews below. Plus, we're each rounding out our Exa reviews with a quaint list of clean-makeup products (from other brands) that never do us wrong. Keep scrolling!</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288933/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review-288933-1599166184999-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288933/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review-288933-1599166205944-main.1200x1598uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Shade: Hannah 490 (fair with subtle olive undertones). Rating: 4/5 stars. Review: Little did this foundation know when it arrived on my doorstep that it would have to jump through every precarious hoop a foundation can be put through: 100-degree heat and a trying 16 hours of wear. (Yep, I did the most damning thing a beauty editor can do and slept in the stuff.) However, in an epic plot twist that I've never experienced with a clean foundation formula, it passed every test with flying colors. (For the record, nearly every other natural foundation I've tried has melted off my face three hours after application and at even the mere mention of sweat or exercise.) So yes, I'm extremely impressed with this foundation. What I love most about this foundation is how beautifully and smoothly it applies and blends into the skin. It does that \"your skin but better\" thing, which is entirely the point of foundation, right? I'm pretty sure I actually murmured aloud \"holy shit, this is beautiful\" as I used my Beautyblender to buff and press it into my skin. That type of jaw-dropping, immediate reaction rarely happens for me. It smells lovely, which is important (for me) when it comes to makeup because it's sitting right beneath your nose. While the finish is slightly more luminous and dewy than I would normally go for, I found that setting it with a touch of powder easily toned down any areas I felt looked too shiny. And again, let's remember I was battling high humidity and heat, so I'm not sure it would always end up looking quite so glowy. I ended up wearing this foundation overnight (I know, I know), and I was completely surprised when I woke up in the morning to find that it still looked *almost* as good as when I first applied it. Really. It only looked slightly worse for wear than my non-clean foundations that tout super-long, 24-hour wear. I did set it with a non-clean setting spray, which probably helped matters. I've done that before with natural foundations, and they've still looked smudgy and all-around messy a few hours afterward. This foundation doesn't apply, look, or wear off like any other clean foundation I've tried. It's far superior, and it even comes in a beautiful glass bottle that makes it feel really expensive. I'm impressed all around. The only reason I can't give it a full five stars is that the finish is a little too dewy for my taste. But all in all, Exa's High Fidelity Foundation has set a new standard in the industry for both quality and inclusivity. It's time for all of the other brands in the clean-beauty space to level up! </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288933/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review-288933-1599166210117-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288933/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review-288933-1599166452496-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>I'm a ruthless mascara tester, and this is by far my favorite clean mascara. And not only that: It's one of my favorite mascaras, point blank. It's one of the few formulas that effortlessly curls, volumizes, and lengthens my long (but very straight) lashes without weighing them down or creating a gloppy and gloopy look I'm definitely trying to avoid. I recommend this mascara all the time, and I maintain a perfect zero-complaints-received track record. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288933/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review-288933-1599166457363-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Concealer is one of the most important products in my routine. I use (a lot) below my eyes, and I use it to reverse contour my face. So it's important that it blends well and looks natural but will also stay. This skincare-level formula from Kosas does all that and then some. The coverage is amazing, it barely creases (especially if you set it with a touch of powder), and it has amazing ingredients that will actually benefit your skin. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288933/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review-288933-1599166462293-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>I love everything Maya Chia makes (which is mostly skincare), but this shimmering serum-highlighter hybrid is really on an entirely different level. It basically makes it look like you're standing under perfect lighting no matter where you go, and I don't know if I've ever tried a highlighter that blends and melts into my complexion so seamlessly and *actually* looks like my skin. So many highlighters set out to accomplish what this one does but ultimately fail thanks to overly sparkly formulas or consistencies that are too sticky, tacky, or slippery. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288933/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review-288933-1599166469005-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>I've loved Rituel de Fille's Enchanted Lip Sheers for years. Datura, Whitethorn, and Swarm are constants in my beauty rotation. They can be a little drying, but if you apply them on top of a really hydrating balm, you should be good to go. Even though my entire makeup routine is definitely not clean, I try to make sure whatever I put on my lips is. So I'm almost always wearing one of these or something from Kosas. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288933/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review-288933-1599166477854-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>I'm probably as tough on bronzers as I am on mascaras and foundations, but I finally found love and satisfaction when this buttery, super-luxurious bronzer from legendary makeup artist Gucci Westman came into my life. It's easy to blend, the color isn't too pink or too orange, and it's boosted with lots of great ingredients to keep your natural glow alive. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288933/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review-288933-1599166483748-main.1200x1598uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Shade: Paetynn 170 (medium deep with golden undertones). Rating: 5/5 stars. Review: As someone with brown skin, I’m still getting used to the concept of a clean foundation. Up until about a year ago, there wasn’t a single clean foundation on the market I could point to that had the shade range to match my skin. So when Erin sent me an excited message in Slack a few weeks back about Credo’s new in-house makeup brand that was not only clean but was also coming out of the gate with 43 shades, my interest was immediately piqued. Before I go any further, I need to mention that I am mildly traumatized from having to mix foundation shades for so long, and I can acknowledge that I may get overly excited when I get my hands on a single bottle that matches me perfectly. It’s not such a rarity anymore, but a perfect shade match and clean ingredients? That’s not a product I’m used to seeing! I love this foundation. It imparts that quenched, glowy finish that’s taken over Instagram. It’s super dewy... like so dewy it can err on the side of oily if you’re not careful. After experimenting a bit with the application, I’ve learned that layering it on top of a heavy moisturizer will end in disaster (even when accompanied by the Exa Jump Start Smoothing Primer). The key, for me, has been pairing it with a lightweight moisturizer and setting any super-loose areas like my forehead, which is oilier than ever right now, with a thin layer of powder. Overall, I’m very satisfied with this foundation and can’t wait to see how it holds up during a full day of outdoor activities (whenever outside opens back up again).</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288933/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review-288933-1599166493040-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288933/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review-288933-1599166498971-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>I honestly can’t wear foundation without concealer. To me, it’s like eating French fries without ketchup: fine but not as satisfying as I’d like. This clean concealer is great because it’s lightweight and doesn’t overwhelm my skin. But it does tend to move around and settle into creases, so setting it is a must.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288933/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review-288933-1599166504189-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Rituel de Fille is such a fun brand. I love many of its products, but at the top of the list is this cream blush. I like that the color blends down to a really soft and diffused glow that doesn’t even really look like makeup. I also like that the color doesn’t just sit on top of the skin and break up over the course of the day. You can also use it on the lips, which I love, but I recommend topping it with a little clear gloss unless you’re committing to a velvety, almost-matte stained look.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288933/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review-288933-1599166509488-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>There aren’t many highlighters you can wear on bare skin without looking like a misguided glitter bomb went off on you. This highlighting liquid creates a healthy vibration of super-subtle shine wherever you place it. I like to tap it into my cheeks and onto my Cupid’s bow to add extra life to my face.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288933/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review-288933-1599166516711-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This product is solely responsible for my love of colorful eye shadows. I used to stick to neutrals, but this rusty-red shade has helped me create some of my favorite eye looks of all time. It can be worn super sheer to look like a rosy tint or layered to look like a full-impact coppery red. Even on days when I want to be low-key, I still find myself reaching for this pot! Top five forever.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288933/exa-beauty-high-fidelity-foundation-review-288933-1599166523827-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>I’ve been wearing mascara since I was in middle school, but even back then when I was reaching for drugstore picks or ones with wild ingredients like glitter, I never had issues with the varnish irritating my eyes. Recently, I’ve been noticing certain mascaras make my eyes sting after a few hours of wear, so I've been leaning into the clean options on my vanity more. This one from Westman Atelier is just perfect. It volumizes and defines my lashes really well. The packaging is also pure luxury. href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-fashion-trends-look-expensive\" target=\"_blank\">talk shopping</a> quite often. Given my role as a fashion editor and her heightened interest in style, she’s often intrigued with the trends and specific items I’m into each season. And while we certainly have our disagreements (that’s for sure), we do often love many of the same fashion pieces—especially when it comes to <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/fall-basics-capsule-wardrobe\" target=\"_blank\">elevated basics</a> and modern staples. On that note, I showed her a smattering of fall items I’ve been particularly into while doing market research at <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=Za1-qFu6cC0oG37sliHR1iHsPE7khq94fkCMLo9LFXYph7ydG7dG4k499A8h6HqcavZivN1Wjh5uDPzHa15xc3iHM_Vzo0oCdFR4_-BshznIPA86Q0njBhqJ0ZfD7HpFnAwABW1_ymuE12dZy3Hwyf1tj7zHvfbv92h1YJ9r3SrxmIDKKQMiPih2\" target=\"_blank\">Nordstrom</a>, <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=W5i5vQg84bO7d3iqH7nY-j3qp_YlQelVl0_X1Y-p5x0X08w2qZHn1URwmVFYorDHaDzEm7HnZGUjh_-uKdcV_zz37mpHwQjX-WnryzuixSIc0ggjaSOdhRKpP0zwtPeaOyAodPOcjgXugrZ_AjDwI-Xsbq-YgKSl2mHa2rFcxqQRM4c\" target=\"_blank\">H&M</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=F5W2VH2Mo-lATnVVC7XMEDEHIR__BsAlPQNxGPGHT9vbcMD8SXqi\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a> (three stores she shops at). She then gave a thumbs up if she liked the piece. In the end, there were 39 items that got an A+.</p><p>Intrigued? Keep scrolling to check out a smattering of top-notch fall items, separated by category—including sweaters, dresses and skirts, jackets, shoes, tops, and jeans. Popular","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/V9xrSgcs8K8/popular-swimsuit-trend","description":"<p>I don't know about you, but I'm a sucker for a swimsuit that's really dang pretty. In my experience, nothing garners compliments and \"where did you get that?\" inquiries quicker than a <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/pretty-swimsuits\" target=\"_blank\">pretty swimsuit</a>. The trend that <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/fashionable-clothing-basics\" target=\"_blank\">generates the most compliments</a> this summer also happens to be spiking in popularity. According to a recent <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=turyazCC7KDXEGEUJCpAukumWu8ojZaYdCL9CR_t2B2naP4p-_cInGgvt6dxQWPTHO5FKuPljAQ268_q_u0m2QmBPNfT1ufEaA\" target=\"_blank\">Pinterest report</a> on the most-shopped swimsuits, <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/how-to-wear-leopard-print\" target=\"_blank\">leopard print</a> has increased in popularity by a whopping 445% over last year, thanks mostly to a $25 H&M version. (Don't worry. You can shop a similar style further down.)</p><p>I'm definitely not a numbers-oriented person, but that strikes me as a pretty significant jump in interest from shoppers. Since animal print of all kinds is a huge trend this summer (both on and off the beach), it makes sense why this would translate to some of the summer's prettiest bikinis and one-pieces. I have definitely contributed to the leopard swimsuit's popular reputation, as just last week I found myself going out of my way to compliment a woman I spotted wearing the eye-catching print on the beach. It's just that good!</p><p>Ahead, see just how cool the swim trend looks on fashion girls, and pick out a leopard bikini or one-piece to wear on your next beach day.</p><p><figure><img Fall","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/lsQBWImEuZ8/fall-shoes-2020","description":"<p>While there are more footwear trends in any given season than one little roundup could ever do justice, today I thought I’d put together an easy overview of what <em>I </em>think will be the most-worn shoe styles <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/fall-trend-shopping-guide-2020\" target=\"_blank\">among the fashion set in the coming months</a>. Covering boots, heels, and sneakers, I’ve narrowed in on the overarching themes that—even if trendy shoes aren’t your thing—you’ll probably want to buy into and/or wear this fall.</p><p>Why? Because not only are they <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/editor-coolest-shopping-picks-august-2020\" target=\"_blank\">undeniably \"cool,\" </a>but they're also versatile, not too out there, and available at a range of price points. So, really, anyone can get on board. Oh, and there’s a chance they’re already in your closet! To read about each one, get some styling inspiration along the way and, of course, shop them If you please, just keep scrolling.</p><p>From welly-inspired styles to leather lug-soled pairs in both high shafts and low, glaring chunkiness is the most important detail if you're looking for a trendy boot this fall. </p><p><figure><img href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/fall-2020-shopping\" target=\"_blank\">reached out to some of my favorite shopping experts</a> to get the inside scoop on all the best fall items we should be snapping up on the earlier side of the season. From sweater vests to heavy chains, they really hit the nail on the head, but there was one must-have fall item that stood out to me amongst the rest: skater jeans. <a class=\"link link--story\" href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=xK7r6gXxS4_89cgTlen7AgiCsAYGI6cGboqlABhM8djn6oyrnNmdCwuc5ViuyYS_Pg\" target=\"_blank\">Celenie Laura Fleur Seidel</a>, senior womenswear fashion editor at <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=_qeKITgJHaNeGMafc1vwnfN3bLDmzQLT56vrMD4YIuiG-Y7BpbXF8xPCyjpvweyn8KChTFiz3nmFy1rZwsmgMB3kT7r86og1U0utPF6My4RWguqKuhRWuGpZSTgmZGOgWeOex3N_Y_FF3SQC7mYWN2oOFOC-s6HHonAPR-oIio4I9sqASvYe82H--hrSN7LRxvEJ\" target=\"_blank\">Farfetch</a>, identified this denim trend as one to watch out for this season, and I couldn't agree more. \"Big and baggy, the skater jean is a new favorite for fall. Offset with feminine elements like a neat cardigan or a little ladylike bag for an unexpected interpretation of the look,\" she said. </p><p class=\"m_8242331729177948089p1\">This baggier denim trend gives hints to that skater-girl vibe when paired with Vans and oversize striped tees, but as Seidel said, when juxtaposed with a tiny bag, kitten heels, and maybe even some pearls, this casual denim trend can instantly read elegant and forward. But don't be mistaken—this look is taken straight from the late '90s skater kids we all secretly wanted to be, but the style is officially back and it's better. Based on the versatile styling ideas alone, skater jeans seem to be a great denim choice for the season ahead. Throw in the fact that looser clothing, in general, has officially begun to suit our more casual lifestyles due to the pandemic and you've got yourself a must-have new denim trend to try this fall. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288963/skater-jeans-trend-288963-1599166512369-main.1200x1598uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This fall, a pair of skater jeans and a neutral coat could easily become your new favorite outfit formula. The combination of the relaxed fit with the cool-girl oversize silhouette is always a recipe for success. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288963/skater-jeans-trend-288963-1599087221228-main.1128x2000uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288963/skater-jeans-trend-288963-1599089496547-main.1660x2546uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288963/skater-jeans-trend-288963-1599166521480-main.1200x1598uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Take a cue from Hailey Bieber and go for the \"oversize everything\" look. Year","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/ZjxvgTJ9Wns/types-of-lingerie","description":"<p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287339/types-of-lingerie-287339-1589999016060-main.1200x900uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>With each new season comes a fresh batch of trends in every category, from shoes to <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/summer-handbag-trends-2020\" target=\"_blank\">handbags</a> to <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/most-popular-jeans\" target=\"_blank\">jeans</a>, and lingerie is no different. While you might not think to update the types of <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/section/lingerie\" target=\"_blank\">lingerie</a> in your top drawer as often as you would with other items, they're no less important to shop for. I'd even go so far as to say that there's never a better time to invest in quality and stylish undergarments than right now. You know, if chilling at home in a pretty underwear set is your kind of vibe.</p><p>For the record, it's a lot of people's vibes these days and I'd be lying if I said that the current state of the world hasn't had a big influence on the kinds of lingerie that everyone is gravitating towards. More and more, pieces that offer comfort and the ability to <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/new-lingerie-trend-2020\" target=\"_blank\">look cute while lounging</a> around are what's leading the pack. So, nope, no <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/cage-underwear-trend\" target=\"_blank\">complicated lingerie</a> trends to be found here. This year, lounge-worthy materials like <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/skims-rib-loungewear-set-instagram\" target=\"_blank\">ribbed knitting</a> and menswear-inspired boxer briefs are the styles currently flooding my feed alongside a few that are just as wearable as they are pretty.</p><p>Ahead, discover all the types of lingerie that are trending this year, and then shop the best versions of each.</p><p>Nothing against classic lace, but if you're itching for pieces that feel fresher, these mesh pieces are the answer. Playful colors like limoncello and prints like checkerboard make these the kind of feel-good bras and underwear you'll reach for over the basics.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287339/types-of-lingerie-287339-1589922480259-image.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287339/types-of-lingerie-287339-1589918100186-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287339/types-of-lingerie-287339-1589917942463-main.2000x3000uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287339/types-of-lingerie-287339-1589922585768-image.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287339/types-of-lingerie-287339-1589917515646-main.2000x3001uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287339/types-of-lingerie-287339-1589861210370-main.2000x3001uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>I'll admit it: This one is a personal favorite of mine. I'm someone who likes the support of underwire but avoids any excess padding (and I give a hard pass to push-up bras—sorry, they're just not for me), so about 90% of the bras I own are this comfortable style. <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/most-comfortable-underwire-bra\" target=\"_blank\">I've sung the praises</a> of Negative Underwear's lightweight Sieve Demi Bra in the past, but now that more and more brands are offering the style, I thought it was about time I highlight it as a trend.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287339/types-of-lingerie-287339-1589903685544-image.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287339/types-of-lingerie-287339-1589860913739-main.1500x2109uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287339/types-of-lingerie-287339-1589917693838-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287339/types-of-lingerie-287339-1589903683575-image.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287339/types-of-lingerie-287339-1589923104599-main.2000x3001uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/287339/types-of-lingerie-287339-1589917581882-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>It appears that fashion girls are taking inspiration from the men's section by wearing both boxers designed for women (like the ones from Skims) or wearing men's boxer briefs along with boyshorts. I won't lie—this one looks ultra-comfy and styled with a ribbed tank makes for an easy lounge 'fit.</p><p><figure><img
