Space","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/LZb-y2r1yNg/how-to-store-purses","description":"<p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/246602/how-to-store-purses-246602-1592264967575-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Your handbags contain your most essential items, come along with you everywhere you go, and faithfully protect your belongings. But how are you taking care of them? When your favorite clutches and satchels are off duty, it’s essential to have a storage plan for your most beloved bags. There are a variety of ways to store purses, and the best solutions tend to vary by type of bag, as well as how much storage space you have. But whatever your scenario, there’s definitely a better option than shoving your latest purchase into a corner to collect dust. Read on for a few of our favorite tips on how to store purses safely and stylishly.</figcaption></figure></p><p><span>This is a good option for closets with a shelf directly above your clothes. Section off as much space as you need, and then place bags upright, side-by-side, and vertically so that they’re easy to see and grab. One of the best perks about this method for purse storage is that you can see them right next to your wardrobe, making accessorizing easier than ever. For bonus points, consider arranging your bags by color, size, or type.</span></p><p><span>Hooks are ideal for varied purse collections or for the girl who has one of everything. Hooks can typically be easily installed either inside or outside the closet. This method is great if you’re looking to save space. As a tip, consider length when you’re buying hooks (longer hooks will be able to store more purses), and keep in mind that wider is better. Razor-thin hooks can create dents and creases in shoulder straps.</span></p><p><span>A creative solution for purse storage is to stash them in a magazine rack. These can vary by size, from small-scale desktop organizers to full-on columns or space-saving versions that can be attached to the back of a door. This method isn’t optimal for totes or satchels, but it is ideal for organizing your collection of clutches and envelope-style handbags.</span></p><p><span>One of the most universal approaches to storing purses is the use of boxes or bins. When done poorly, this method can be chaotic, but when done right, it can keep handbags beautifully organized and in top condition. If you decide to go this route, there are a few key tips to keep in mind. </span></p><p><span>First, make sure to choose the right size of boxes or bins. Measure your closet and your largest handbag, and take the area you intend to store them into account.</span></p><p><span>Next, make sure you’ve allotted enough <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/closet-organization-amazon\" target=\"_blank\">storage space</a> so that the items don’t get squished or misshapen. For vintage, delicate, and high-end luxury handbags that you don’t use often, consider bins or boxes that completely seal and offer the best protection.</span></p><p><strong><span>Now that you know how to store purses, here are a few of our favorite new things to store: </span><a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-affordable-designer-handbags\" target=\"_blank\">24 designer handbags</a><span> (that are affordable).</span></strong></p><p><figure><img 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"This Anti–Skinny Jean Trend Is Coming Back With a Vengeance in 2020","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/i-r7myYRfJs/flare-jeans-trend","description":"<p>If I opened your denim drawer right now, I bet I could guess some of the key silhouettes stored inside—straight-leg jeans, <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/outfits-with-skinny-jeans\" target=\"_blank\">skinnies</a>, and perhaps even an of-the-moment outlier like those <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/grandpa-jeans-trend\" target=\"_blank\">“grandpa” cuts</a>. But what’s one style that probably hasn’t surfaced to the top of the pile as much as of late? Flares. Sure, cropped flares have been well, cropping up, over the last few years, but the more polarizing bootcut and bell-bottom styles (aka anti–skinny jeans) haven't been as popular again <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/bootcut-jeans-trend\" target=\"_blank\">until recently</a>. Well, get ready—as we continue to see on the runway and streets, flares are officially back and will continue to hold strong through 2020.</p><p>That’s right, designers from Celine to Paco Rabanne reintroduced fresh flared jeans in their S/S 20 collections as the next It denim pick for the forward set. And fun fact, celebrities like Gigi Hadid, Margot Robbie, and Harry Styles have already been following suit in ’70s-inspired flares. Fashion girls are also starting to embrace the vibe.</p><p>To highlight the look further, we broke down how the flare trend is taking over the runway, celeb, and It-girl world for you below. While a particular dress or tailored silhouette is key to that sartorial success, appropriate undergarments are also of utmost importance. After all, dressing <em>does</em> begin with the items you put on first—<a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/naked-lingerie-trend\" target=\"_blank\">underwear</a>.</p><p>While we’ve covered a few of the <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-underwear-celeb-stylist\" target=\"_blank\">specific underwear styles celeb stylists swear by</a> in the past, we thought we’d dig a little deeper into the key brands this in-the-know group recommends (and sometimes wears) not just for comfort but for quality—aka brands that actually <em>last</em>. Because come on, we all get frustrated when we think we invested in a legit pair of underwear, only to find it coming apart after the third time washing it.</p><p>So with all that in mind, keep scrolling to check out how <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/stylist-summer-fashion\" target=\"_blank\">stylists</a> rank the top underwear brands out there in reference to those that actually (truly) last the longest, are comfortable, and have the ability to be unseen and lay flat against the body. Oh, and fun fact—you'll see a lot of similarities among each of their must-have brands below. To help you get started, we’ve rounded up eight of the best waterproof sprays for shoes that really work.</p><p>Some of the best waterproof sprays for shoes are made by Kiwi. It sprays on clear so it won’t alter the appearance or breathability of the shoes.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/251554/waterproof-sprays-for-shoes-251554-1520472743749-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/251554/waterproof-sprays-for-shoes-251554-1579123956732-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Made to work equally well on suede, canvas, and nubuck materials, Crep Protect is the perfect choice for a range of weather conditions. Go-To","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/_qtQmplS4dU/best-clutch-bags","description":"<p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288967/best-clutch-bags-288967-1599095211932-main.1200x900uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><span>If you were to read any of the text chains between me my friends, then it would be abundantly clear how often we discuss one of possibly the most impractical trends of the century: </span><a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-mini-bags\"><span>mini bags</span></a><span>. While some handbags have been </span><a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/most-popular-designer-handbags\"><span>popular for a long time</span></a><span>, it is only within the past few years that the mini-bag trend has risen in prominence. This is due in part to Instagram-favorite designers like Jacquemus, helping to usher the trend into viral territory. And while my mini-bag ramblings have yet to dissipate, I must admit that I’m relieved to see a new, more practical purse is on the horizon. This season, please welcome the clutch bag. </span></p><p>Clutch bags first emerged in the 1920s to address the needs of consumers who, in lieu of a more practical, traditional carryall, were craving small, stylish bags that would compliment specific looks. It’s true that like mini bags, clutches can be a fussier choice; since by definition, these bags require some sort of hand-holding. But that doesn’t mean they’re not practical—some of the best clutch bags actually can hold more than a Tic-Tac, cost less than a fortune, and dare I say, give pockets a run for their money. Don’t believe me? Ahead, I’ve rounded up the 35 best clutch bags in every shape, and at every price point.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288967/best-clutch-bags-288967-1599095301440-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Bottega Veneta ushered in the popular cloud-shaped clutch back in July of 2018; and two years later, it’s clear that this bag and its various iterations are here to stay. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288967/best-clutch-bags-288967-1599095327642-main.850x967uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Not able to yet invest in Bottega Veneta’s cloud clutch? This one should hold you over. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288967/best-clutch-bags-288967-1599095363712-main.850x967uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Redone leather details were all over F/W 20 runways, and what better way to clutch trend than with this faux-leather woven bag? </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288967/best-clutch-bags-288967-1599095416716-main.850x967uc.jpg\"><figcaption>If you’re looking for a more affordable designer version of the iconic cloud shape clutch that won’t be the equivalent cost of New York City rent, Mansur Gavriel’s clutch bag is one of you’ve been dreaming of. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288967/best-clutch-bags-288967-1599171986101-main.850x967uc.jpg\"><figcaption>A crocodile cloud clutch? With new iterations of this clutch shape, including chunky chains and even fringe, Bottega keeps this It bag ever relevant. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288967/best-clutch-bags-288967-1599095453776-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption>The pouch dates back to medieval times, but it has evolved over the years from its original hand-held version to iterations that include zippers, and even handle straps. 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"My Friend Has Now Convinced Me to Invest in This $550 Hair Tool","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/buJPmPB-O-c/fall-hairstyle-inspiration","description":"<p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288725/fall-hairstyle-inspiration-288725-1598048427738-main.0x800uc.gif\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>2020 isn’t shaping up to be the year I thought it would be—and that’s the simplest and nicest way for me to put it. Among many things in life, my hair routine has been disrupted. No salon treatments, no feeling like I'm in a hair campaign thanks to a fresh blowout. Even though salons are starting to open across the country, who knows when things will be back to how they once were, so I decided to take matters into my own hands. </p><p>My good friend and co-worker Natalia Sztyk has been raving about the <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=EfqDssoTJ5bztq56XimdQ-deBtCfxmystaAlsmjy4cAkgS7y379MqkCOkTa62_eotGDCvw\" target=\"_blank\">Dyson Airwrap™ styler</a> the tool that lets you curl, wave, smooth, and dry hair all at once with no extreme heat—all thanks to the Coanda effect, which attracts and wraps hair to the barrel using only air. Honestly I was surprised to hear she was using (and loving) it, since the last I heard she'd given up hot tools. Here’s a little backstory: A few years ago, Natalia dyed her hair ombré, and as much as she said she loved how it looked, the chemicals seriously damaged her locks. So last year, she decided to get her hair healthy again by taking it back to her natural black color and committing to air drying. When recently, Natalia felt ready to invest in a product that would help reduce hair breakage and damage, it only made sense to go with a hair tool from the experts in hair health—Dyson. Dyson has a team of experts that study in detail everything from thermal, mechanical, and chemical hair damage to airflow dynamics. “Before I felt like I had no option other than letting my hair air dry, but the Dyson Airwrap is a way to create hairstyles without extreme heat,” she tells me. “There are also so many different styling attachments [six to be exact], so you can create so many hairstyles and never get bored.” </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288725/fall-hairstyle-inspiration-288725-1598048678406-main.1139x2232uc.gif\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>She had my attention, but a $550 price tag isn't a buy-on-a-whim situation. I really needed to be sure it's worth the investment. So, I did what I always do when I'm thinking about a big purchase: calculate what the cost per use would be over the course of a year and it's impressive. (Take a look for yourself above—even if I'm using it just once a month, it's more affordable than getting a blow-dry.) Natalia took it one step further by sending me pictures of all the salon-worthy hairstyles she created last week and the Dyson styling attachments she used for each. I'm sold and assume you will be, too, after you take a scroll…</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288725/fall-hairstyle-inspiration-288725-1598050709168-main.1260x1600uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>I know Natalia is my friend and all, but how cute does she look? It's crazy how some hair volume and bounce can make a casual jeans-and-tee outfit look way more fun.</p><p><strong>Get the look—soft waves:</strong> Natalia used the pre-styling dryer attachment, then the firm smoothing brush at her roots, and finished with the 1.2-inch barrel to curl her hair away from her face. \"I brushed the curls out with my fingers for a more undone feel,\" says Natalia. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288725/fall-hairstyle-inspiration-288725-1598050714448-main.1260x1600uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Simple yet sophisticated and so easy, Natalia tells me. \"I love that I was able to go from damp hair to smooth and straight so easily without extreme heat.\"</p><p><strong>Get the look—smooth & straight:</strong> Natalia used the firm smoothing brush styling attachment from root to tip and repeated until all her hair was done. \"It helps to section your hair, and focus on the bottom part before moving to the top,\" explains Natalia. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288725/fall-hairstyle-inspiration-288725-1598050720051-main.1260x1600uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>I've known Natalia for years now, and I'm telling you she used to <em>always</em> wear her hair with beachy waves. So, I'm calling it: Now this is going to be her regular style again.</p><p><strong>Get the look—beachy waves: </strong>After using the pre-styling dryer attachment, use the 1.2-inch barrel styling attachment with the arrows pointing away from your face. \"I alternated the way each section was curled by changing the barrel directions because it made the style feel more relaxed and beachy,\" explains Natalia. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288725/fall-hairstyle-inspiration-288725-1598050725793-main.1260x1600uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>If you don't live in Los Angeles, then you might not know we've been experiencing quite a heatwave. It only makes sense Natalia styled a 'do that was completely out of her face for a particularly warm day. It's definitely a nice way to spice up a regular ole ponytail.</p><p><strong>Get the look—pony up:</strong> Natalia says she used the pre-styling dryer attachment and then both the 1.2-inch barrel and 1.6-inch barrel styling attachments to curl her hair before pulling it all back into a ponytail. Super easy and effective.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288725/fall-hairstyle-inspiration-288725-1598050731373-main.1260x1600uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Okay, it legit looks like Natalia got her hair professionally blown out. This is the style that has 100% convinced me I need a Dyson Airwrap of my own.</p><p><strong>Get the look—full-bodied volume:</strong> Natalia says she used the pre-styling dryer attachment and then the round volumizing brush styling attachment. \"For this look it's important to get volume at the root, so lift hair at the crown, shaping and lifting side sections up and outwards.\"</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288725/fall-hairstyle-inspiration-288725-1599090506882-main.1260x1600uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>To me, this looks like it must have taken forever to do, but Natalia assured me it was actually super quick and easy. \"It reminds me of my wedding hair, so I felt super confident and happy all day long,\" she tells me.</p><p><strong>Get the look—Hollywood waves: </strong>Natalia used the pre-styling dryer attachment and the 1.6-inch barrel styling attachment curling toward her face. \"For a more voluminous feel, brush the curls out after,\" she says.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288725/fall-hairstyle-inspiration-288725-1599090493174-main.1260x1600uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>I love this final 'do. It looks like a combination of a few of the earlier ones: not as glam as Saturday's style but not as casual as Wednesday's. It's the perfect middle ground.</p><p><strong>Get the Look—tousled texture: </strong>Natalia used the pre-styling dryer attachment and the 1.6-inch barrel styling attachment, alternating the barrel directions for a more undone, tousled look. \"Don't forget to run your fingers through the curls to loosen them up,\" she says.</p><p>I don't know about you, but Natalia has totally sold me on the Dyson Airwrap. Sure, the price is an investment, but considering there are six styling attachments, the options for hairstyles feel endless. It's the versatility that's got me! Plus, even if I only used it once a month, it'd still be cheaper than getting a blowout. Who is with me?</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288725/fall-hairstyle-inspiration-288725-1598048455201-main.850x967uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><em>Interested in the <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=FWNx5BxqVSZUysnYdvDF61M6Ew1yy-zncNLNLNSVDAlhpMiu5Cz9qPKHcYrkFsnlTkZnRm-6HnVyjkAxFz_LTz7AfJxfYszpbEMnm3my0yUad8_LYZdxoAZLo6qFqi-ZyNZRj9xYm2_p4Z9vqa7jag6f9C25OjK4eKVk5vlD5KeN4NDPnElKX2ubxpcnjDafWEbcYRuTe7uIAUjpOwZ3dWaxyDjQ\" target=\"_blank\">Dyson Supersonic™ hair dryer</a>, too? ","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/7AwnXZzP1M4/best-front-closure-bras","description":"<p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/280383/best-front-closure-bras-280383-1597453626415-main.1200x900uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">After coming home from a long day, there is nothing better than the relief of finally taking off your bra and letting yourself loose from the <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/most-comfortable-bras\" target=\"_blank\">uncomfortable confines</a> you've been subjected to for hours on end. (Sorry to sound so dramatic, but I think you know what I mean). There is nothing worse, however than struggling to wrap your hands around your back while peering over your shoulder into the mirror as you attempt to undo the snag in the clasp in the back. Is a little support and functionality too much to ask for?</span></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The solution to both these problems is simple—front-closure bras. Not only does this supremely comfortable style boast a clasp in the front that is perfectly situated for easy removal, but they also pull your breasts forward and together, which provides the exact support and lift a lot of us look for in our favorite bras. As a result, this bra style is perfect for breasts of all sizes, particularly those with a bigger bust who may frequently <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-bras-for-bigger-busts\" target=\"_blank\">run into the challenge of finding a bra</a> that is both comfortable and stylish.</span></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">From racerback to strapless, keep reading for the best front-closure bras of every kind.</span></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/280383/best-front-closure-bras-280383-1597442068062-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>If you're looking for full-coverage cups and a smooth back this is an excellent option.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/280383/best-front-closure-bras-280383-1559824655951-main.1200x1840uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This T-back bra features seamless, non-padded cups and lightweight knit fabric for comfortable all-day support. It's perfect for large breasts and comes in a wide range of sizes.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/280383/best-front-closure-bras-280383-1597445669415-main.832x831uc.png\"><figcaption>The lace trim adds a pretty touch to this comfortable racerback design that stays hidden beneath your clothing.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/280383/best-front-closure-bras-280383-1597442375064-main.1338x1500uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This is the most convenient bra for larger chests. like the feeling of slipping on a <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-sweatshirt-brands\" target=\"_blank\">sweatshirt</a>. Even in the middle of summer, I crave it. The soft fleece material and slouchy fit can't really be compared to any other clothing item, which explains its enduring popularity. And I have a hunch that since comfort is everything this year, they're going to be even more popular than ever come fall, which I'm already seeing some proof of.</p><p>If you're like me, you've been diligently checking the new arrivals sections of a variety of e-tailers, and have likely noticed a plethora of new sweatshirts. But I found something a bit different while scrolling through H&M and Zara, in particular: <em>Fancy</em> sweatshirts are the style that's going to be everywhere this fall and winter. If you think about it, fancy sweatshirts are the perfect clothing item for fall 2020, as we all want to feel cute without sacrificing comfort, whether staying in or going out for socially distant activities. </p><p>Without further ado, shop my favorite fancy sweatshirts from Zara, H&M, and a few other in-the-know brands.</p><p><figure><img 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"I Asked Our Editors for Their Favorite Face Masks—Here's What They're Wearing","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/iNoczp5hZs8/best-face-masks-from-editors","description":"<p class=\"p1\">I never would have predicted that <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/cute-face-masks\"><span class=\"s1\">face masks</span></a> would become the biggest accessory trend of 2020, but they certainly have as we continue to do our part to slow the spread of COVID-19. As a fashion editor, I’ve had my eye out for stylish face masks to add to my cart and have been looking to <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/fall-shopping-online\"><span class=\"s1\">our team at Who What Wear</span></a> to see which ones they’re been wearing. Curious to find out their top picks, I asked them to share which ones they've been wearing.</p><p class=\"p1\">Ahead, see the exact face masks our editors are buying and get ready to shop them. They’re sharing snaps of how they’re styling them and weighing in about why these 9 face masks brands are their favorites—from <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=wN2bs4P7T-8qs3WSF8ZO4fbeAAPZYaDlqzqmAopTh5jw8Lbk-1YwIBq9ADjZK_nz2OIihir5qN6q\"><span class=\"s1\">cool tie-dye prints</span></a> to <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/splash/zpm2w0AIc?w=3702036\"><span class=\"s1\">bold prints</span></a> to the one our editor in chief <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/splash/zenmJNNTA?w=3703191\"><span class=\"s1\">compares to a luxe silk pillowcase</span></a>. Here, see our top picks, including the affordable face mask I’ve been wearing on repeat.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288905/best-face-masks-from-editors-288905-1598989894481-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>These affordable masks from Evolvetogether are the #1 style I wear on repeat. The simplicity of them means that they'll go with pretty much any outfit I put on, which is probably why they're <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/hailey-bieber-fall-boot-trend/\" target=\"_blank\">a favorite among celebs like Hailey Bieber</a>. Plus, I love that they have a range of masks stamped with the geographic coordinates of some of my favorite cities like Milan and NYC. —Kristen Nichols, senior editor</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288905/best-face-masks-from-editors-288905-1599013732302-main.1350x1800uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288905/best-face-masks-from-editors-288905-1599013743019-main.1374x1800uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288905/best-face-masks-from-editors-288905-1598902886606-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>\"This cotton <span class=\"il\">mask</span> claims to be 'soft, breathable, and comfortable' and I can't help but agree. I love how light it is while still feeling like it's substantial enough to actually be protecting (both yourself and others). Plus, the adjustable ear loops ensure the perfect fit even if, like me, you have a small face. Lastly, I'm a big fan of the subtle eyelet fabric that's neither boring nor too out there.\" —Nicole Akhtarzad Eshaghpour, senior market editor</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288905/best-face-masks-from-editors-288905-1598903437315-main.1600x2133uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288905/best-face-masks-from-editors-288905-1599013033198-main.940x1253uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288905/best-face-masks-from-editors-288905-1598902881769-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>\"This <span class=\"il\">mask</span> is an investment, but let me walk you through why I think it's worth it. First things first, it's pretty and comes in a lot of colors. I am a fashion editor after all, so this is an important consideration! But more seriously, it's made of silk, which is a smart move for a number of reasons. The fabric is known to possess antimicrobial and antibacterial properties, and silk is also much comfier than other materials and slides across the skin, making it less likely to irritate your skin. And just like silk pillowcases are great for not soaking up all your creams and serums, the nonabsorbent nature of the material helps keep skin hydrated and lets all that lovely skincare stay on your skin. (Picture rubbing a cotton swatch vs a silk swatch over your face and you can imagine the difference in how much more drying the cotton would be.) Now let's talk about the disposable filter: it's made from melt blown. If that term is new to you, like it was to me, let me explain. The material is used in surgical <span class=\"il\">masks</span> because it has smaller \"pores\" meaning it can better block particles in the air. Why does it have smaller \"pores\"? Because unlike woven fabrics like cotton, which naturally have more space between the fibers because they are woven together, melt blown is, \"mechanically, thermally, or chemically bound from separate fibers of molten polymers.\" Science. Also, the ear straps are adjustable so you can get the perfect fit for your face. And last, but not least, there is a charitable component. For every <span class=\"il\">mask</span> sold, they will donate five to frontline workers. That's all I've got, and after writing this, I've basically convinced myself to buy another. Let's match?\" —Kat Collings, editor in chief</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288905/best-face-masks-from-editors-288905-1599012929667-main.1000x1000uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288905/best-face-masks-from-editors-288905-1598903584015-main.1000x1000uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288905/best-face-masks-from-editors-288905-1598902891179-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>\"While at first, I was only wearing simple black <span class=\"il\">masks</span>, and the typical filter ones I figured it was time to start getting creative with them as we're going to be wearing them until COVID-19 is under-control, and why not make a cute statement while protecting others? So I waded into the waters of printed/ statement <span class=\"il\">masks</span> with this Van Goh inspired <span class=\"il\">mask</span> from Esty; and I kid you not, the first day I wore it, <em>I got so many compliments</em>. After that, I was sold on not wearing bland <span class=\"il\">masks</span>; so now I'm looking forward to splurging on more unique <span class=\"il\">masks</span> like Gravitas's <span class=\"il\">Mask</span> <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=4qVFDedTxLh5npDbPQRybwrXihlYqevvRPbpKNqDq2CMTGOC7IYV8RHvh2tQSePOOMPU34bE02r4kfNVRgqSZJEcecGj2yeSk0xQtwY1ObGlDuLCBAy5meykwGKGKEXAiZwZcEd32PwL3K-vRiqyfFU4gfJ-cw\" target=\"_blank\">celebrating women's right to vote</a>, or Lirika Matosh's <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=E0iV6JNcB9qhqUtEQxr83aaOdef8bnYhvx3_1G5fBc2HiohuQEtSLRPRhf_ASiH3hM0LLkD6Y6UXVh3st8zHb8c0i11RThyuV5yRvIhukaAjeSuJObExAnM9Zuj__g\" target=\"_blank\">viral strawberry face <span class=\"il\">mask</span></a>.\" —Jasmine Fox-Suliaman, audience engagement editor</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288905/best-face-masks-from-editors-288905-1598904017787-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288905/best-face-masks-from-editors-288905-1599013114752-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288905/best-face-masks-from-editors-288905-1598989721006-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>\"Cotton Citizen’s cool basics are some of the comfiest items in my closet, and their face masks are no exception. This one is is made from 100% cotton, so it’s breathable and lightweight, two claims I can vouch for after having worn it all day in the summer heat. The other aspect that makes this is a really good mask is that it has a bit more fabric than others  I’ve tried so it’s fuller coverage and not too tight against my face. Plus the obvious, which is that the washed-out tie-dye print is just plain fun to wear—highly recommend!\" —Anna LaPlaca, associate editor</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288905/best-face-masks-from-editors-288905-1598989981933-main.960x1450uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288905/best-face-masks-from-editors-288905-1599013208997-main.960x1450uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288905/best-face-masks-from-editors-288905-1598902896570-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>\"I've been wearing two <span class=\"il\">masks</span> as of late. Staples","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/HuVZ6BVhch8/ageless-wardrobe-staples","description":"<p><strong><span>More than ever, we’re feeling a pull to spend our money on pieces that will stay in style for longer. For many of us, it feels refreshing to slow down our consumption and more thoughtfully choose how we engage in the relentless trend cycle. But how does one cultivate a <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/timeless-wardrobe-basics\" target=\"_blank\">timeless wardrobe</a>? One place to start is to pay attention to the types of pieces that you reach for time and again. We can also look to fashion experts like </span><a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=DcBLWAErZtmbboMdmzD8ppxLeBgpx2O_d56WnKBh1b0gaCYZU8r2qIul8VqbkdlvURYBIAeMRg\"><span>Kimara Mitchell</span></a><span>, the woman behind </span><a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=x_l7M5DY9M5aKX-9jBufrMelgdghZf-wkTvTMjMaVzj_wkmpvyn155MJPaGZhmD5xg\"><span>J’Adore Couture</span></a><span> who also happens to be the art director at </span><a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=QWfyZgsW-OghEAYhXvg3Tvk1X1EZYCtHjZQJ7-MxyvKNV_Nb2-jeQlKBn90\"><span>Banana Republic</span></a><span>. Her life centers on aesthetics, so it’s no surprise that she’s nailed the art of dressing. Her fashion philosophy centers on <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/basic-wardrobe-staples\" target=\"_blank\">wardrobe staples</a> that she calls her “any-age” items. She’s worn them for years</span><span>—</span><span>think of them as outfit foundation blocks with no expiration date. Scroll down to see the pieces that made Mitchell’s list</span><span>—w</span><span>e bet you already own many of them! </span></strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288027/ageless-wardrobe-staples-288027-1593652518770-image.1250x1629uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"I have been a graphic T-shirt collector for many years. They're a great way to show off a bit of your personality.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288027/ageless-wardrobe-staples-288027-1593711457008-main.1110x1420uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288027/ageless-wardrobe-staples-288027-1593710437054-main.2000x3000uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288027/ageless-wardrobe-staples-288027-1593710237565-main.3320x5092uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288027/ageless-wardrobe-staples-288027-1593652523096-image.1250x1982uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"There's a reason Levi's have been around for over 150 years. 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"This \"Boring\" Bra Has Become the Most Popular Lingerie Style Among Millennials","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/PlNkz7aWNmo/most-popular-bra-style-millennials","description":"<p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282066/most-popular-bra-style-millennials-282066-1566590431604-main.1200x900uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>If you had told us 10 years ago that the most popular <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-racerback-bras\" target=\"_blank\">bra style</a> in a decade wouldn't be some sort of underwire style, we probably wouldn't have believed it, but here we are. This week <em><a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=BMaFDuLVaxJwYa9ZGtSZ4CgKnqBCeIoupJcr58OtQgadxScxNmAXRovDowZEFNcERZS8A0oMZfMYkLD4i9ue2TTo-0T4TbD5dwIuqKm5BHKisc5UPFk2_tDWa5bknZthqI4unkqfi27oawxVfz5-7mw55tvC3PbRMfse6Eh8bcE\" target=\"_blank\">WWD</a></em> reported that a study done by the NPD Group on women's <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-high-cut-underwear\" target=\"_blank\">lingerie</a> spending habits showed that the most growth over the past three years has been among <strong>sports bras</strong> (and shapewear). NPD Group found that sports bra sales increased by 6% over the past year, and millennials, in particular, spent a third of their bra budgets on this one style last year.</p><p>Marshal Cohen, chief industry analyst at the NPD Group, attributed the rise in popularity of sports bras to athleisure and the desire for comfort in fashion. In addition to that, <em>WWD</em> points out that people's \"increasingly busy lives\" are at play, as well as the \"innerwear-as-outerwear trend.\" So if it seems like popular brands like Lululemon and Marks & Spencer are offering more sports bras than ever, you're not imagining it, and there's clearly a lot of data behind it.</p><p>Scroll on for some of the chicest sports bra examples on Instagram and shop some of our favorites.</p><p><figure><img /2020/09/05/08-41-41-278_095303c87037d460.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282066/most-popular-bra-style-millennials-282066-1599251849716-image.1080x1350uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx27/cdn24@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-41-56-141_3f6b8df396e40c21.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282066/most-popular-bra-style-millennials-282066-1599252427466-main.800x0uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx31/cdn61@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-42-33-503_7b9682e0f7fd01d2.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282066/most-popular-bra-style-millennials-282066-1599252451213-main.800x0uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx13/cdn35@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-41-54-873_6dc8f58fc048c62c.webp","http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~4/PlNkz7aWNmo":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx18/cdn80@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-42-37-939_c2c0b631e7b75e98.webp"},"publishedOrCreatedDate":1599295287270},{"createdTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"Your Face Oil Soul Mate Exists—Here's How to Choose the Best Formula","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/E5gkBvCIAj8/best-face-oils","description":"<p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288993/best-face-oils-288993-1599241025916-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>It could be said that <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-anti-aging-face-oils\" target=\"_blank\">face oil</a> is one of the most controversial skincare products on the beauty market. Walk (or scroll) through any beauty retailer, and you'll find hundreds of options featuring all sorts of oils, <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/types-of-skin-acids\" target=\"_blank\">actives</a>, and other credit card–tempting ingredients. Some people swear by its efficacy for hydrating and healing <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-body-oils\" target=\"_blank\">thirsty skin</a> while others condemn face oil with fearmongering threats of congestion, clogged pores, breakouts, and more. So what are we to believe?</p><p>I'll admit that for years I wouldn't touch face oil with a 10-foot pole. I have sensitive, acne-prone skin, and I was as terrified of face oil as I am of spiders, heights, losing A.C. in 100-degree heat… You get the idea. But then, the tide started to change. I began talking to more and more dermatologists and facialists who told me face oil is largely misunderstood. In fact, pretty much every person with any type of skin can benefit from it. That said, there are some important caveats and things to know when shopping for the best face oil for your unique complexion. As with all skincare, face oils are not one size fits all, and there is some strategy and skill involved in choosing the right one.</p><p>To clear the muddled air surrounding face oils, and in order to gather more intel and advice on whether they're the worthwhile investment the industry wants us to think they are, I reached out to two amazing experts: <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=ehAvl2839JjNaonlUn1ydk1-MflxP6SRjYUIVU5IuAE76xkujruUaoc8jNe0EyBUdcWlOcJe\" target=\"_blank\">Sunday Riley</a>, master formulator, CEO, and founder of her namesake skincare brand, and board-certified dermatologist <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=0xZdou6TDH60yRUWlFFbRz_SVdqAIkGRIyDE-BJPcJTaxO1ls4TJbIwekNzv6X6_QlI0kg\" target=\"_blank\">Shari Sperling</a>, DO. Keep scrolling for everything you ever wanted to know about face oil and to shop some of the best options for every skin type. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288993/best-face-oils-288993-1599241035503-main.1200x1598uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Yes, yes they are. That said, there is one *very important* caveat to this, which is the quality and formulation of the face oil you use. For instance, the oils hanging out in your kitchen cupboards or bodycare collection are (or should be) vastly different from what you're putting on your face.</p><p>\"Face oils are specifically formulated to sink in and moisturize without leaving an oily finish,\" says Riley. \"You might also find they have oil-soluble esters in them, which reduce the greasiness of the other oils and leave a very velvety, dry finish on the skin. Face oils are also one of my favorite ways to get oil-soluble actives, like retinoids, salicylic acid, or vitamin C esters, into the skin.\"</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288993/best-face-oils-288993-1599241042917-main.1200x1598uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>According to both Riley and Sperling, everyone can, indeed, use and reap the moisturizing benefits of face oils. But again, it comes down to using your oil correctly and choosing a formula catered toward your skin type or your major concerns. For example, someone with very dry skin probably won't use the same oil as someone with very oily skin. And yes, even folks with oily skin can use face oil. The right mixture of ingredients can actually help stabilize and regulate the skin's sebum production, which, in turn, will help <em>curb</em> excessive oiliness.</p><p>\"Remember, applying a face oil should not make you produce more oil—quite the opposite,\" Riley confirms. \"If you have oily skin, look for an oil with oil-soluble esters, which help the oil to sink into the skin and disappear.\"</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288993/best-face-oils-288993-1599241056463-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Yes and no. High-quality, strategically formulated face oils should not clog your pores, but not every oil is suitable for your face or every skin type. Steer clear of highly comedogenic oils (like coconut oil), and mind how <em>much</em> oil you're applying. A little goes a long way.</p><p>If you're especially prone to grease or are worried about congestion and breakouts, however, Riley suggests looking for a face oil that contains an ingredient like salicylic acid that will dissolve the sticky, oily buildup loitering around your pores. (Sunday Riley's <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=SUCYUm29gQdOd25ufNM2QFtFP9zOcmTu3zEHR7fvbokY7qzlNR_fqGdbt485F2J9ZNdHqWDt4bJC\" target=\"_blank\">U.F.O. Ultra-Clarifying Acne Treatment Face Oil</a>, $80, is a great option.)</p><p>Of course, if you were to slather your body oil onto your face, it very well may result in clogged pores or a fresh set of blemishes. According to Riley, these types of products usually feature heavier oils that can be too much for the complexion to handle, ultimately trapping bacteria and leading to unwanted congestion. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288993/best-face-oils-288993-1599241082192-main.1200x1598uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>As a rule, your face oil should pretty much always be the very last step in your routine since oils have a larger molecular size. If you apply it too early, anything you put on afterward won't be able to penetrate the skin. </p><p>\"An oil with active ingredients in it (like retinoids, vitamin C esters, or salicylic acid) is more like an oil <em>serum</em>, whereas a pure oil with ingredients like argan oil or jojoba oil is really just a nurturing moisturizer,\" explains Riley. \"I like to apply oil serums first after cleansing and/or toning so that the retinoids or vitamin C can easily sink into the skin. But if you're using a straight oil like jojoba, make sure to apply it as your last step. It's too heavy to go first and could stop your other products, like serums, moisturizers, and treatments, from effectively penetrating into your skin.\"</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288993/best-face-oils-288993-1599241131253-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Tea tree oil, salicylic acid, and black cumin seed oil work together to combat breakout-causing bacteria. Then, additional strategic ingredients like hexylresorcinol and licorice help gently brighten the skin to even out lingering scars or pigmentation.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288993/best-face-oils-288993-1599241114238-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>If you're looking for one of the best oils to help keep breakouts at bay, Sperling recommends reaching for a formula featuring rose hip. This affordable version is one of The Ordinary's best sellers. It's organic and utilizes cold-pressed oils—a must, according to Riley.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288993/best-face-oils-288993-1599241136327-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Herbivore's best-selling Lapis Facial Oil is a game changer for those with oily or pimple-prone complexions. 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"I Was a Perfume Novice, But This Is My New Favorite Scent, Hands Down","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/S2oSWMORPtU/best-musk-perfumes","description":"<p>In case you haven't been following, I've recently started moonlighting as a beauty writer in addition to my day job as the managing editor of Who What Wear's sister site, <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/\" target=\"_blank\">THE/THIRTY</a>. As someone who was always interested in beauty and skincare but never really covered it in my 10-year journalism career, it's been an eye-opening experience. I've learned <em>so much</em>, including what exactly is <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/hyaluronic-acid-benefits\" target=\"_blank\">hyaluronic acid,</a> everything I've ever wanted to know about <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-body-sunscreens\" target=\"_blank\">sunscreen</a>, and the best way to <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-face-exfoliators\" target=\"_blank\">exfoliate my skin</a>. My brain has gotten heavier (in the best way possible) with knowledge, and my skin has never looked better.</p><p>One of the beauty topics I've enjoyed learning more about has been fragrances. I never really gave much thought to it mostly because I don't have a great sense of smell due to an accident a few years ago. (That's a story for another time.) So I didn't know that there is so much to perfumes and scents from all the layers of notes to chemistry to fragrance families. I recently talked to some perfumers about <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/\" target=\"_blank\">how to purchase a fragrance online</a>, and it was one of the most interesting subjects to write about and consider, especially since most of our shopping is being done online at the moment.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599012302067-main.960x1281uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Writing about the topic has really made me rethink my perfume choices. I always stood firmly in the <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-gardenia-perfumes\" target=\"_blank\">florals camp</a>, but now I'm looking to new horizons—mainly the musky scents of the world. I always thought the woodsy, earthy, grounding scent was a little <em>too</em> heavy and not really the vibe I was trying to give off. I've always gravitated toward light, natural, fresh, and sweet-but-not-too-sweet scents.</p><p>While I still love those notes, I'm ready to get a little more mysterious and serious with my fragrances. Maybe it's because I'm getting older and am solidly in my 30s now, or maybe it's wanting to shake things up when we're finally able to get out there and see our friends and family safely again. Whatever it is, I'm ready for a rebranding of sorts when it comes to my perfumes. And I think musky scents are a great place to start because they still have a natural vibe but with a little bit more sophistication and intrigue.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599012382978-main.1010x1347uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>In my quest to find a musky perfume to call my signature scent, I've made a wish list. Take a look at what I'm eyeing below. Maybe you'll be inspired to try them, too.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599014872835-main.2723x3096uc.jpg\"><figcaption>I'm intrigued by the coconut water in this Byredo fragrance. It's an unexpectedly sweet and sort of tropical scent. It has base notes of cotton and wild musks and cocoa absolu, plus middle notes of patchouli leaves.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599015061330-main.5829x6629uc.jpg\"><figcaption>With a name like White Suede, you know you're getting something so chic and a little bit mysterious. This fragrance from Tom Ford is warm and spicy with notes of saffron, thyme, maté, suede (of course), olibanum, and musk. I'm putting this on my list of perfumes to wear on a night out.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599015458001-main.1821x2071uc.jpg\"><figcaption>A blend of florals, amber, and creamy musk, this fragrance is equal parts feminine, warm, and cozy. It also has coconut water, so consider me intrigued!</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599012463244-main.1012x1349uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599015621633-main.2000x2274uc.jpg\"><figcaption>The perfume is described as a love letter to the wife of Vilhelm Parfumerie's founder and is centered around her morning cup of tea. It's both fresh and grounding with notes of bergamot, apple, Ceylon black tea, oakmoss, musk, and black amber.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599015815441-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>An interesting tidbit I learned through my perfume research is that scents can smell differently on everyone, so something that suits me might not be the best fragrance for you. Glossier's You perfume uses that type of chemistry to adapt to the specific user. It has base notes of musk, ambrette, and ambrox and has top notes of green irisroot and pink pepper.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599016031941-main.4920x5595uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Chanel's Chance may seem like an ordinary floral perfume at first, but the jasmine is balanced with vanilla, pink pepper, amber patchouli, and white musk.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599012517290-main.1012x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599016232228-main.2000x2637uc.jpg\"><figcaption>The Nubian Musk perfume is described as \"capturing the healing power of plants,\" so it has fresh scents of rose, jasmine, and Moroccan grapefruit. It's grounded with a musk base.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599016421601-main.2250x2813uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Source1 is where all the perfumes from Hermetica start. It's the base of all of its fragrances. It has scents of bergamot, dry amber, and fresh wood.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599016603331-main.1415x1609uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Clean Reserve's Sueded Oud is warm, woodsy, and spicy. The fragrance is vegan and cruelty-, gluten-, and phthalate-free. Even the packaging is eco-friendly. The cap is made from sustainable wood, and the glass bottle is recyclable.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599012953135-main.810x1080uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599016888389-main.5404x6146uc.jpg\"><figcaption>A classic floral scent is taken up a notch with notes of lavender, orange blossom, and musk accord. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599017098869-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Spicy Sichuan pepper and aromatic basil are combined with florals like iris, rose, and jasmine in this fragrance. And it's all topped off with natural musk. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599017149465-main.6091x6928uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Along with musk, Kiehl's fragrance contains citrus top notes of bergamot nectar and orange blossom; middle notes of rose, lily, ylang-ylang, and neroli; and a base of tonka bean and white patchouli. It's said to be a modern update of Kiehl's signature scent.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599012986698-main.1080x1111uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599017343714-main.2000x2275uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This scent is both fruity and spicy with tangerine, bergamot, and cinnamon. It has a creamy and rich base of vanilla, amber, and musk.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599017569162-main.1802x2048uc.jpg\"><figcaption>If you're looking for something that's fresh but still woodsy and grounding, you'll like this fragrance that is inspired by a day near the ocean. It has notes of cardamom, bergamot, and sandalwood.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599017702767-main.1712x1946uc.jpg\"><figcaption>With a name like \"Lazy Sunday Morning,\" you know you'll get something easy, breezy, and happy. This fragrance combines traditional florals like lily of the valley and iris with white musk.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599012607963-main.1012x1349uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599017884353-main.1682x1913uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Huda Beauty's musk fragrance gives off soft and warm vibes. It has floral notes of lotus flower, freesia, and jasmine. These are combined with vanilla, sandalwood, and musk.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288936/best-musk-perfumes-288936-1599018075481-main.2000x2482uc.jpg\"><figcaption>First: This perfume has one of the prettiest and most unique bottles I've ever seen. Thus, they're bound to accrue bountiful beauty knowledge, and many of them have even debuted their own lines, brands, collections, and collaborations, including one of our all-time favorites, <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/drew-barrymore-style\" target=\"_blank\">Drew Barrymore</a>.  </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281644/drew-barrymore-beauty-tips-281644-1564720090284-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>In addition to consistently wowing us on the red carpet since the early '80s, she's also paid it forward by building her very own cruelty-free makeup brand, <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=EBDjPK3HMTxmrBCtih8FxVspprAl_A-4lu6-KJFNoe1TtlB43WpBfG2X9pQ2yBecsueHWbsIYetueigM\" target=\"_blank\">Flower Beauty</a>, a godsend for those of us who have admired her aesthetic since we were in scrunchies, leggings, and body glitter. So we're celebrating!</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281644/drew-barrymore-beauty-tips-281644-1564720095005-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Ahead, all the best products, tips, tricks, and rituals we've discovered by way of Barrymore's beauty-centric Instagram feed. href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-face-masks\" target=\"_blank\">Face masks</a> are one of those pesky categories of skincare that practically <em>beg</em> us to pull out our credit cards and start swiping with zero abandon. Not only does packaging seem to get prettier and prettier (conveniently in tandem with our bank accounts getting tinier and tinier), but the benefits, technology, and overall allure of face masks are also increasing at a rapid rate. Ingredients are getting more exotic, and suddenly, the tempting nature of additions like crushed diamonds, 24-karat gold, exfoliating acids, superfoods—heck, even things like adaptogens and <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/cbd-beauty-products\" target=\"_blank\">CBD</a>—make forking over $50, $100, or even $200-plus seem like the norm. But of course, it doesn't <em>have</em> to be.</p><p>Sure, there are plenty heart-stoppingly expensive face masks we love and salivate over, but the quality of drugstore beauty offerings has also reached a steep incline in the past few years. For $25 and under, you can still satisfy your craving for lust-worthy ingredients like volcanic crystals, lavender oils, and manuka honey but at a fraction of the cost.</p><p>We're big fans of customizing your skincare routine so you're getting the best, most bang-for-your-buck results regarding your skin concerns, and we're here to tell you that there are some best-selling, high-quality drugstore formulas that we recommend (and use!) as beauty editors and that have the sky-scraping reviews to back them up. So if you're looking to <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-selling-face-serums\" target=\"_blank\">save some extra money this season</a>, we recommend scrolling ahead to peruse 16 of the best drugstore face masks, sorted by skin concern and sealed with their impressive retail rating status.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/279791/best-drugstore-face-masks-279791-1585947352674-main.1080x1347uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/279791/best-drugstore-face-masks-279791-1557531575194-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>I receive face masks for testing and review almost on a daily basis, but I still pick up this mask from the drugstore whenever my acne-prone skin flares up. I used this salicylic- and charcoal-infused formula before I was a beauty editor, and I plan on using it until the day Yes To stops making it, which I hope is never.  Rating on Ulta: 4.3 stars and 134 reviews</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/279791/best-drugstore-face-masks-279791-1557531581974-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>SheaMoisture sometimes flies under the radar, but the brand makes some of the friendliest formulas for our faces and bank accounts. This strategic blend utilizes African black soap and calming raw shea butter to simultaneously rebalance, detoxify, and soothe blemish-prone skin.  Rating on Target: 4.4 stars and 2149 reviews </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/279791/best-drugstore-face-masks-279791-1557531590636-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Spiked with skin-refining ingredients like strawberry and rosemary, this drugstore face mask from Formula 10.0.6 is designed to de-stress clogged pores so you reap an instantaneous and gratifying glow. Rating on Ulta: 4.2 stars and 774 reviews</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/279791/best-drugstore-face-masks-279791-1557531602914-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This clarifying clay mask is one of those underground dark horses that pretty much every beauty editor and celebrity has hiding somewhere in their stash of skin-saving products. Home","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/fHw6M0OfpUs/fall-date-night-outfits","description":"<p>Looking for something to wear on your next date night? Or perhaps every night is date night at your place. Either way, today I’ve got you more than covered with a roundup of 12 easy outfit ideas that will make prepping for your next night out–or, of course, <em>in</em>—almost too easy. From <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/fall-dresses-target\" target=\"_blank\">casual and comfortable dresses</a> to classic jean-and-top combos to of course, a couple loungewear moments, these 'fits will have you ready for whatever your love life throws at you <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/cheap-fall-basics-timeless\" target=\"_blank\">this fall</a>. Just be sure to save or screenshot your favorites to have on hand and copy any time you’re in a pinch. (And don't be surprised if you end up wearing many of them on repeat.) So, what are you waiting for? See and shop the looks that made the cut below and consider your getting-ready time officially cut in half for the rest of the season.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/243400/fall-date-night-outfits-243400-1599069390577-image.1200x1598uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Got a long cardigan? 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"The Coolest Fashion People to Follow in Every Age Group","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/SvhhDKCI44I/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age","description":"<p class=\"p1\">In the constantly growing landscape of fashion influencers, it's an unfortunate fact that the younger crowd significantly outnumbers ladies of a certain <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ageless-wardrobe-staples\" target=\"_blank\">age</a>. But just because there are certainly more of them, that doesn't make them any more relevant or valuable than their more mature counterparts. <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/fall-basics-capsule-wardrobe\" target=\"_blank\">Fashion</a> is universal, after all.</p><p class=\"p2\">The segment of Instagram influencers and bloggers in their <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/hm-shopping-over-30\" target=\"_blank\">30s</a>, <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/places-to-shop-for-clothes-in-your-40s\" target=\"_blank\">40s</a>, <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-places-to-shop-for-clothes-in-your-50s\" target=\"_blank\">50s</a>, and beyond may be small, but it's mighty. We aim to enlighten you, dear reader, about the ladies of <em>all </em>ages who are crushing it in the fashion game at the moment —from the 25-year-old whippersnappers to the 65-year-olds who've been at it for a good while longer. Prepare to be majorly inspired by <span class=\"s1\">all the women showing off their unique (and, frankly, fun) looks</span>. Keep scrolling to meet the best fashion Insta stars of every age group.</p><p><strong>20s</strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/180992/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age-180992-1598984858135-main.1080x1348uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Influencer and fashion market writer at Refinery 29, Alyssa Coscarelli has the most refreshingly unique feed—where she shows her love of vintage and retro pieces alongside all the current trends and brands.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/180992/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age-180992-1598986796125-main.1080x1317uc.jpg\"><figcaption>New York based model and influencer, Amy Lefévre has a minimalist-modern wardrobe we dream of owning. She plays with volume brilliantly and her neutral-hued feed is seriously chic.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/180992/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age-180992-1598987837642-main.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption>From pretty floral frocks to envy-worthy bikinis and stylish activewear looks—plus-size model, activist and certified yoga teacher, Ali Tate Cutler never ceases to inspire us with her charming outfits.</figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>30s</strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/180992/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age-180992-1598988557612-main.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Danish style star Pernille Teisbaek is a regular here on Who What Wear and for good reason: Her modern style is still somehow timeless, and she has mastered the ultimate coup d'état in fashion—she can style pretty much everything with ease.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/180992/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age-180992-1586213687803-main.1200x2083uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Los Angeles–based blogger Courtney Trop was one of the first ladies to bring laid-back yet elevated California style to the front row of fashion week. We love her sensibility for giving the Cali-girl vibe a unique twist.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/180992/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age-180992-1598988766713-main.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Song of Style's Aimee Song has set herself apart as one of the most prolific style stars in the game. The L.A.-based trendsetter mixes casual pieces with designer duds in an easy and seriously inspiring way.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/180992/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age-180992-1598989397428-main.1080x1252uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Fashion cool-girl and former Harper's Bazaar editor, Chrissy Rutherford is always sporting some of the coolest brands, and is a constant source of inspiration for her unique New York style.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/180992/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age-180992-1598989945074-main.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Known for her elevated, minimalist style, Instagram influencer and lingerie designer TyLynn Nguyen is forever inspiring us to invest in chic and timeless classic pieces that will never go out of style.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/180992/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age-180992-1598991505240-main.1080x1349uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Plus-size fashion influencer and content creator, Kellie Brown has an empowering and inclusive Instagram, proving that fashion is for all sizes.</figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>40s</strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/180992/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age-180992-1598992398577-main.900x1125uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Tennille Murphy is a lifestyle influencer with enviable style. She rocks everything from slip dresses to cropped tops and tailored separates with confidence and style.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/180992/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age-180992-1598993160575-main.1080x1349uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Content creator and one of the coolest fashion women to follow, Tamu Mcpherson always wows us with her bold, beautiful, and trend-forward pieces. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/180992/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age-180992-1598994523871-main.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption>A regular on the street style circuit and at fashion week, Yasmin Sewell is an Australian fashion consultant (and former buyer) who styles her outfits to effortless perfection.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/180992/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age-180992-1598992212245-main.900x900uc.jpg\"><figcaption>The San Fransisco–based blogger currently works as an art director at the Banana Republic Factory and is a big champion of wearing what you want, regardless of your age.</figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>50s</strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/180992/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age-180992-1598995826626-main.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption>You can always count on fashion influencer, Renia Jaz to show us the up-to-the-minute trends and gorgeous designer pieces from our favorite brands. Just one scroll of her feed and you'll be instantly hooked.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/180992/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age-180992-1598997507472-main.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption>The Montreal-based Insta-star, Grece Ghanem has a loyal following who flock to her feed for cool styling tips and of-the-moment fashion pieces (that we all want to get our hands on!). </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/180992/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age-180992-1598998051725-main.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Content creator, Melissa Meyers shares her Cali-cool style and must-have beauty tips to help you look and feel your absolute best no matter what your age.</figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>60s</strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/180992/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age-180992-1598998529264-main.863x1079uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Susan Feldman is the co-founder of One Kings Lane and In the Groove, a style destination where she shares her age-defying outfits and shopping tips. (She's also our resident style expert here at Who What Wear). </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/180992/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age-180992-1598998778641-main.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Lyn Slater has earned herself plenty of accolades and press (including from us at Who What Wear) for her vivacious spirit and similarly poised sense of style. Her blog, Accidental Icon, is aptly titled: Slater had a successful career as a university professor before she embarked on her blog, which started as a fun hobby and launched her into the sartorial stratosphere.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/180992/best-fashion-bloggers-at-every-age-180992-1598999490312-main.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Mel fashion.</figcaption></figure></p><p><em>Up next, <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/denim-outfits-over-50\" target=\"_blank\">we're in our 50s and rely on these 8 jean outfits</a>.</em></p><img
