dburner.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~4/SvhhDKCI44I":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx29/cdn83@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-41-59-825_c9fee263f297e0fe.webp"},"publishedOrCreatedDate":1599295287281},{"createdTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"9 Fall Wardrobe Investments I Regret Not Making in My 20s","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/GtB70x1hsgI/fall-shopping-in-your-20s","description":"<p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598989568122-main.1200x900uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>So I figured I'd give this story a go before I forget what I even wore <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/fast-fashion-brands-for-your-30s\" target=\"_blank\">in my 20s</a>. (Given that I spent several minutes the other day trying to remember if I'm 35 or 36 (it's 36), it's certainly possible.) But just as important as remembering what I did wear is what I <em>didn't</em> wear. For much of my 20s, I spent my clothing budget on trendy, inexpensive items that I'd quickly tire of. There are certainly exceptions but for the most part, I wasn't particularly worried about <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-fashion-investment-buys\" target=\"_blank\">longevity</a> when I'd decide what to buy. I've spent the first half of <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/clothing-brands-in-your-30s\" target=\"_blank\">my 30s</a> making smarter wardrobe investments that I wish I'd started making earlier on. </p><p>Since fall is on the horizon, I've been thinking lately about the types of pieces I wear the most this season, year after year, and they're not the same trendy accessories, going-out tops, and dresses (to name a few) I was wearing 10 years ago. This is partly because my style has changed since my 20s and partly because I wasn't making that many lasting purchases. My budget was certainly more limited then, as is the case with many 20-somethings, but I regret not living by the 'ole less is more/quality over quantity adage a little more. </p><p>With that, keep scrolling to shop the nine wardrobe investments I wish I'd made in my 20s, that work for every age group.</p><p>I'm someone who's always on the hunt for the next denim trend, which is all well and good, but the jeans I wear the most are those that can't be classified as a trend. They have a straight leg, a high waist, and a medium wash, and no other defining qualities, and that's what I love about them.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986590314-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986584733-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986583201-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Coats can be pricey, so I tend to wear the same ones for several years in a row at least, which is why I think outerwear is a very worthy investment. You can really tell the difference between a cheap and a high-quality wool coat, for example, so this is an area that's worth more of a splurge.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986575394-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986581307-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986579199-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>While this is certainly more of a year-round investment than a specific fall one, when summer ends, I always want to put on more nice jewelry. And unlike when I was in my 20s, there are so many good DTC fine jewelry brands on the market now, so high-quality pieces are more affordable than ever. I can say with confidence that I wear very few of the costume jewelry pieces I bought in my 20s, if any.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986577025-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986585287-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986582772-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>While I wore button-down shirts differently in my 20s (i.e. not with bike shorts), I wear them now as much as I do then, so it would've been worthwhile to invest in some nice ones in classic colors and prints, especially since they're not that big of an investment. You live, you learn.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986577992-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598996139271-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986586928-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Seems like a no-brainer, but I too often avoided investing in \"boring\" items in my 20s. Sure, a black blazer may not be the world's most exciting thing, but think of all the non-boring things you can wear with it! My advice is, save up for a nice one made with quality material that will help it to drape nicely and last.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598996226208-main.900x900uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986590943-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986576341-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>When I got my first office job in my 20s, I quickly realized that I was going to need a big bag to transport everything I'd need in an 8-hour+ day. I recall going through a lot of tote bags that would eventually get beat up and be forced into retirement. If only I'd put that money that I used on many tote bags to one really nice one...</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986579985-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986586111-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986588282-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>There's nothing worse than a thick, itchy sweater, am I right? I've suffered through my fair share of those, and I'm not sure why when you can get cashmere sweaters for a good price, and they're just as warm as their thick, itchy counterparts.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986583847-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986582004-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986587528-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Belts are one of those accessories that I just forget to buy, but if I had more nice, neutral ones, I'd wear them more and my outfits would be better for it. A high-quality leather belt can last for years and be worn almost every day, if you so please. When you think about it that way, the cost per wear makes even a designer one seem like a steal.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986580659-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986585613-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986591794-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Warm accessories are not only essential—they can really make an outfit look expensive. Just think of what the below scarf and leather gloves would do for a sweatshirt and jeans. I used to stock up on cold-weather accessories for cheap at Zara, and while they were cute, I regret not investing in some nicer ones that I'd still use at age 36.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986593417-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986588587-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288930/fall-shopping-in-your-20s-288930-1598986592604-product.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><em>Next up, <a Longer","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/Tvu8f-Bz4xo/best-high-cut-underwear","description":"<p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/267874/best-high-cut-underwear-267874-1537154812306-main.0x800uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>“The newest <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/naked-lingerie-trend\" target=\"_blank\">trend in underwear</a> is definitely the high-cut French brief.” Boom. You heard it here first, courtesy of <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=wJWdCteSN2XU4pU0GNAvVQZMvHBxnTkcWrU5CsLLhNd4MRJkciHDJ8ef522imbda_S-bCb-V54BsxCj-_N5L43QqZVRw1A8rFKHHGz5WNff8NlW-9stqLLQb64TKFnUlww\" target=\"_blank\">Journelle</a> Head of Product Development Sandra Rose, aka the woman in charge of knowing what’s new and next in the underwear space for one of the U.S.’s most-loved lingerie retailers. There are a couple of reasons to get on board with the trend, but my primary motive? The underwear style makes your <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/how-to-make-legs-look-longer-thinner-2014\" target=\"_blank\">legs look way longer</a>.</p><p>“With the band sitting at your natural waist, it gives you legs for days!” says Rose. <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=_BLgqzb6mbkVpfxQPyl5obXEg1Hg_wYZ4aLYk47GTSygkWFMJdGelMvI3A\" target=\"_blank\">Fleur du Mal</a> founder Jennifer Zuccarini agrees: “High-cut styles elongate the line of your leg and emphasize your waistline because they sit higher, on a smaller part of your waist, than, say, a hip-hugger style.” Another, more practical plus of the high-cut underwear trend? “With a higher rise, they are less likely to bunch when you’re wearing high waisted pants and skirts,” says Rose.</p><p>As for where the re-emergence of the high-cut French brief trend came from, Zuccarini attributes it to Instagram It models like Kendall Jenner, Bella and Gigi Hadid, and Emily Ratajkowski as well as ’90s supermodels. Just like with any trend, “it takes time and the right people wearing it again and again, for people to adopt a new look like this,” says Zuccarini.</p><p>Since the look has been gaining steam for a moment, the time is now to hop on the high-cut underwear trend. To help you with that aim, we rounded up the best options along with some visual inspiration to get started.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/267874/best-high-cut-underwear-267874-1565376089765-main.1200x1500uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This mossy hue is just what your underwear drawer needs.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/267874/best-high-cut-underwear-267874-1537151834134-main.0x800uc.png\"><figcaption>Rihanna made a pair of is.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/267874/best-high-cut-underwear-267874-1537151286405-main.900x1227uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Pair these with your favorite black bra.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/267874/best-high-cut-underwear-267874-1565376378405-main.800x800uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Rihanna does it Our classic staples serve as the backbone of our wardrobes—always on hand to get us through each season and practically every occasion in style. r-fashion-basics-288964-1599084216949-main.1080x1248uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx5oss/cdn82@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-42-42-367_41190d6a27d2fd22.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288964/popular-fashion-basics-288964-1599103341128-main.800x0uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx12/cdn43@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-42-08-675_1a1bf0a6f499eb39.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288964/popular-fashion-basics-288964-1599084306777-main.1080x1350uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx21/cdn9@2020_1/2020/09/05/08-43-00-641_0b64671850813068.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288964/popular-fashion-basics-288964-1599103438813-main.800x0uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx18/cdn52@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-42-09-523_89476eec8f820d7a.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288964/popular-fashion-basics-288964-1599084766866-main.1080x1350uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx21/cdn75@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-41-55-553_f881b840fabb6dee.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288964/popular-fashion-basics-288964-1599103569265-main.1560x2392uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx/cdn9@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-42-10-882_f7ea01b38289925b.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288964/popular-fashion-basics-288964-1599084996797-main.1080x1331uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx19/cdn16@2020_6/2020/09/05/08-41-40-734_9010beedaae7d147.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288964/popular-fashion-basics-288964-1599103798888-main.800x0uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx25/cdn71@2020_3/2020/09/05/08-42-21-118_b7a5c481cdd6e79a.webp","http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~4/qduFyJXetcw":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx8/cdn74@2020_1/2020/09/05/08-42-59-989_c08f91b8fc2293c4.webp"},"publishedOrCreatedDate":1599295287279},{"createdTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"We Tried The Nue Co.'s Latest Topical Skincare Supplement, and It Might Be Magic","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/IbxZt2FHOmo/the-nue-co-the-pill-review","description":"<p>It's no secret <a href=\"https://thethirty.whowhatwear.com/cyber-monday-supplement-deals\" target=\"_blank\">the supplement business</a> is booming. (And honestly, \"booming\" could be considered an understatement.) According to <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=9yyASBadCRSGtFbu76HUiW8XR3TC3igiCcK581dEwrT32E1rrKAmNndji91ZxFBt2YlXkLvnU8dtjlxbsfmLFyLYwBAJZgyDMxX4C_4o4cvdgXbPfreq_blKmcd770TRYw\" target=\"_blank\">a report</a> executed by <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=89liVZ8tyPQjPfvAzGLMDlhnPNo1diPoBWk7ofI0TkAO-8mDWW_hGsLkDBjOeopgf0iIjbmPGxIosr5b6mLr-n_HFC4r0NQyQxcN6GQG6kQTb-0GNJZTYoteiw6MTmVh4A\" target=\"_blank\">Grand View Research</a>, experts predict the demand for dietary and nutritional supplements across the globe will continue to rise with a projection for the market to reach $230.73 billion by 2027. So no, the economic weather forecast shows no sign of a tide change where our obsession with vitamin- and mineral-spiked tablets, capsules, liquids, and powders is concerned.</p><p>Of course, we also know that not all <a href=\"https://thethirty.whowhatwear.com/supplements-nutritionists-actually-take\" target=\"_blank\">supplements</a> are created equally and that investing in high-quality, truly <a href=\"https://thethirty.whowhatwear.com/best-supplements-to-take-daily\" target=\"_blank\">efficacious formulas</a> requires research, patience, and, yes, a consult with a trusted physician. (For the record, we never recommend starting any kind of new supplement regimen without speaking to your doctor first.) One brand, in particular, that has catapulted to fame—especially among the beauty and fashion set—is <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=xHKb9l69QVk1T0uzBQLCSyonzrM0pybwzN2OTBr42VtFzXy1iMp4pCz02SJpfgXfBOMsewHkpc7p_43xNaukPYg5g6zJJpTgSwqF4o4t06Tig82z8AjyB8ALArQIFccYEag\" target=\"_blank\">The Nue Co.</a>, a sleek, chicly packaged label dedicated to \"redefining\" the world of supplements. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288896/the-nue-co-the-pill-review-288896-1598981444481-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Founded by <a href=\"https://thethirty.whowhatwear.com/jules-miller-morning-routine\" target=\"_blank\">Jules Miller</a> (whose grandfather was an English scientist committed to developing vitamins and supplements), <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=flP-VFaNqiq90tPTsoOMT82xIdl1GFkMbEP906Pd132ZcwuSMurX0yHZlHZo_erb2QSP0gQDIrOBIvQV8pboqvkM1zshYCQPAlKZxeuJqzzn8DViweIqIel8DBbusObbhqhGsNfqDL9yJ-uW3ydfPTmilg\" target=\"_blank\">The Nue Co.</a> came to life in 2017 with the specific goal of redefining the relationship we have with our health, shouting a collective nay to the disturbing fact that most supplements contain <a href=\"https://thethirty.whowhatwear.com/how-to-choose-vitamins\" target=\"_blank\">ingredients</a> that are 50% chemical preservatives and fillers. <em>Welp. </em></p><p>According to my research and a quick perusal of The Nue Co.'s website, the brand takes pride in melding the two *often* divergent worlds of science and natural innovation to strategically concoct effective yet body-kind supplement formulations. The brand's products feature clinically proven ingredients and follow long-honored practices from Ayurvedic and Chinese medicine. The Nue Co. chooses specific vehicles like tinctures, time-delayed capsules, and powders to enhance the absorption, quality standard, and sustainability of its carefully composed products, and each and every one of its well-being elixirs is free of toxic preservatives, additives, and flavorings/sweeteners. Additionally, the specialized ingredients are responsibly sourced, with 95% of materials being infinitely recyclable. (The brand notes <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=pasqmpWsRY-LTE4umyvos-bP5vLklXCVmGLOoY-qxQ7iPQanMUMPxVXgRG32EuGfO8Rj9dikyFaZ\" target=\"_blank\">on its website</a> it's hoping to reach 100% soon!)</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288896/the-nue-co-the-pill-review-288896-1598981449157-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Until recently, and with exception to a few beloved products like the <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=P6pasmmJkQ02X7NYxKL303dZvwNBszZD9VIkm_nvabn_YKhrD5itkTzDjV56CvfQXU7yt16AosCL6FwofxyRcArpeic4DLwx_qpUYKOZ_R62_l_eRsQWJ1tXCyDVvVdn0RNzd7ENYYx4auyn2wJDeaYElq3X7mPo4mwKz7mj2AaU41uInWngG4IjjIAgTm29-9L4Ua4\" target=\"_blank\">Functional Fragrance</a> ($30), <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=lYfkryRXIQuGgRC6xsLANUDypMFbsOIMpi-ce5BfTGwGsmsrpGK8JT30c6xO4rhFkRPHzzumedy6lHhkjm15hixLGC1pXeCjrjRmBWHcsrJG0tfQH5xvs3en2FOdwH1k8dbcfjmMqLBiZoMS2AEBlv73eewzwOjGGTtJ1z4H6_DSiQG7olAY8tMl\" target=\"_blank\">Topical - C</a> ($70), and <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=qN5_0AVVDBmfplGb4HNr-hGCp76aZLpQeR09Kx4GaXQ9K-d-BFQRNpgdhdyfair22jQOD6_-4vEks3mWSs0c4yJaap3tFNIcKCxCng_vfRXN8dflWHGBOX7gQBmUyUkHue_plje7k_U-ZPnHzl9BOEVWhSfri7NaqPulQf2yFbzVoJ6GsFMvzJrsxGq8YzA\" target=\"_blank\">Magnesium Ease</a> ($55), The Nue Co. singularly carried digestible supplements in the aforementioned forms of tinctures, capsules, and powders. However, with its foray into topical skincare, the brand has launched an exciting, new skin supplement in the form of a serum designed to be applied every morning after cleansing and before moisturizing. Conceptualized as a one-stop-shop skin antidote, The Nue Co.'s latest innovation is called <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=gfKtzawS34KzGjViuP96MKCIBojAqLKd-Cyft0Dn3bez4o_zr-SxZAchgKRzSF75VhROctPuq8-gjQIjae4tNdebpP3HHHNHKFu6v5p8H1axHpLHdfN0rWrON2kSrkd5WoHU38N7mZ9G2XzcJcg0gSUvsX0fk6ZHvRs8qAl-dce5SC5WMgiR0Sg\" target=\"_blank\">The Pill</a> ($85), and truth be told, it just might be the brand's most exciting launch yet. Keep scrolling to learn everything you need to know about the latest addition to The Nue Co. family and to see our editor-tested reviews and selfies. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288896/the-nue-co-the-pill-review-288896-1598981456026-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288896/the-nue-co-the-pill-review-288896-1598981459931-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>As we mentioned, one of the unique pillars of The Nue Co. is its unique new-age-science-meets-old-world-medicine formulaic philosophy. Just like the brand's preceding roster of clean supplements, The Pill combines the best of both clinical and natural skincare findings in the form of a single-dose serum brimming with 27 nontoxic actives. These actives are skillfully brewed, so you're able to effortlessly layer all of the most skin-efficacious acids on the market sans confusion, thought, or potential safety or skin risks. For anyone who has ever felt flustered or unsure when it comes to layering skincare products, The Pill ($80) will be a regimen-streamlining dream come true.  Another positive side effect is that you'll notice both instantaneous and long-term results. The formula specifically targets puffiness, inflammation, and complexion-dulling dehydration in three unique ways to ensure you enjoy the delightful buzz of instant gratification alongside enduring, long-lasting results. Essentially, The Pill has the addictive appeal of a quick-fix complexion solution but with buildable, long-lasting, skin-improving powers as well. Dreamy, eh?  \"The Pill instantly brightens, exfoliates, hydrates, plumps, and tightens to create a ‘second skin’ effect,\" notes an official press release we received from the brand. \"Then, long-term, consistent once-daily application will also support the production of collagen and procollagen, reduce breakouts, increase skin hydration, and decrease fine lines.\" On its website, The Nue Co. provides the following findings in terms of results: In three minutes: \"89% of consumer testers reported instantly tighter, less puffy skin within three minutes of using The Pill. 95% of consumer testers reported instantly smoother and brighter skin within three minutes of using The Pill.\" In six weeks: \"87% of consumer testers reported more hydrated skin within six weeks of using The Pill daily every morning. 94% of consumer testers reported more radiant skin within six weeks of using The Pill daily every morning.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288896/the-nue-co-the-pill-review-288896-1598981462812-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Tightens and Decreases Inflammation: The Pill precisely targets skin inflammation using specific plant actives and proven calming compounds like grape-seed extract, glycyrrhizinate dipotassium (aka licorice-root extract), CBD, caffeine, and plant-based isoamyl laurate. They work harmoniously to reduce irritation and damage while tightening, hydrating, soothing, and softening the skin to keep the complexion's important lipid barrier intact and happily balanced.  Plumps and Moisturizes: Dew- and hydration-inducing humectants like hyaluronic acid, glycerin, galactoarabinan (GA/larch extract), and sodium PCA (the skin's natural moisturizing factor) tag team to ensure your skin can maintain healthy levels of moisture long-term while delivering smooth, ultra-plump results to the skin immediately.  Brightens and Exfoliates: The gang's all here! A dream-team complex of plant-derived AHAs like lactic, glycolic, mandelic, citric, malic, and tartaric acids come from lush sources like passionfruit, bilberry, and pineapple to gently resurface and brighten congested and dull skin. As a reminder, AHAs offer a chemical method of exfoliation as an alternative to physical exfoliation (e.g., scrubs) that can sometimes be harsh and irritating—especially for those with sensitive, easily provoked skin. The magic of AHAs happens when said acids dissolve the gummed-up bonds between skin cells, removing all of the dead stuff and, in turn, revealing softer, super-smooth skin.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288896/the-nue-co-the-pill-review-288896-1598981469196-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>As far as your application protocol, the brand recommends a once-daily, morning-only dosage. Simply cleanse, apply two hearty pumps of The Pill all over your face, allow it to soak in for about two full minutes (brush your teeth!), and then moisturize. Since this serum contains everything except the kitchen sink in terms of skin-loving ingredients, there's no need to add any additional toners or serums into the mix. That said, the brand notes on its website that The Pill can safely be used alongside its holy-grail, ingestible formulas Skin Filter ($60) and Skin Hydrator ($45) daily. You can also safely use The Pill in conjunction with Topical - C ($70). Just start slowly and work your way up to your normal dose of C to minimize any potential skin irritation. Remember, vitamin C is another highly active ingredient, so we recommend sticking by the brand's best practices for optimal results. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288896/the-nue-co-the-pill-review-288896-1598981486655-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Rating: 4.5/5 stars. \"I'm not new to super-active serums, so any new product that claims to be more effective than the ones already on my vanity gets an immediate side-eye from me. Usually, I find that any company trying to push a 'miracle product' is really just pushing a bottle full of buzzy ingredients at percentages so high that they do make a significant difference right away but can also cause long-term damage to the skin barrier. As such, I tread lightly when it comes to serums that contain a ton of acids. \"On the other hand, everything I know about The Nue Co. leads me to believe that the brand really prioritizes research and the use of clean, bioavailable ingredients that call in science and ancient medicinal practices for full-spectrum support. I think this serum represents that ethos perfectly. While it's meant to resurface and renew the skin for big results on the outside, the formula also targets underlying issues like inflammation and hydration that super-active serums don't always take into account. \"I've toyed with using it both at night and in the morning, and even though the texture does remind me more of a daytime serum for some reason, I typically prefer to use my actives at nighttime. One evening, I layered the potent blend as the first step after a physical exfoliation, and the next morning, my skin looked so plump and smooth I could hardly believe my eyes. I have to admit that layering a formula with lactic, glycolic, citric, malic, and tartaric acids after buffing my skin probably isn't something I'd do again (that's just too much exfoliation!), but the results were so dreamy and proved to me just how potent and effective this serum is. I've been using it for over a week now and am really loving the results so far. Plus, it's clean! The only reason this serum doesn't get five stars from me is that I've found the recommended dose of two pumps isn't enough to spread evenly over my face and neck, so I can see it running out pretty quickly. At the price point, that's not ideal.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288896/the-nue-co-the-pill-review-288896-1598981505721-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288896/the-nue-co-the-pill-review-288896-1598981521819-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Rating: 4.5/5 stars. \"I'll start this out by saying the one and only reason this serum isn't getting a full five-star rating from me is I simply haven't tried it long enough to provide a completely fair and objective review (especially considering the brand says half of the touted magic will be noticed more long-term, after about six full weeks or so). That said, I can very happily report a review on what I have noticed in the mere one week I've been slathering my face with the stuff: a new plump, bouncy, ultra-supple skin texture; a refined yet visible dewy glow (no oiliness or greasiness!); and an undoubtedly smoother, more refined skin texture.  \"While I'm very open about trying new haircare, bodycare, and makeup products with abandon, I'm annoyingly picky and scrupulous when it comes to what I put on my face. I read every last ingredient in anything that comes within a three-foot proximity of my complexion, and I'm wary of anything with lots of different actives or with fluffy marketing that makes a product seem too good to be true. So even though I've been a longtime fan of The Nue Co. and many of their ingestible supplements, I was immediately suspicious of a serum that's marketed to basically erase the need of my cabinet full of serums and tonics. The sheer number of acids and plant-based ingredients also made me nervous because my skin is incredibly sensitive and acne-prone, and anything with too much vim and vigor, or anything too natural, never typically sits well with my finicky complexion.  \"However, this serum has forced me to eat my worry. Courtney and I both vowed to apply the serum daily for a week straight, and I swear we ended up texting each other almost every morning of our experiment exclaiming how surprised and very much infatuated we were with The Pill. Thus far, I've experienced zero irritation (not even a sting!) from the potent formula, and the botanical ingredients have led to nary a pimple. Instead, I've only noticed completely positive results. Soft, luminous, plump, dewy, completely healthy-looking skin. \"Acid- and active-containing serums are infamous for their signature funky smells (think apple cider vinegar, decaying garbage, rotting flesh… kidding, kind of), but other than an ever so slight tinge of something slightly ACV-ish, there is no overwhelming odor to this, which makes it super tolerable and, heck, even enjoyable to apply each morning. All in all, this serum is super yummy, and my skin has been noticeably happier and well-behaved since I started using it. Again, I can't report on the purported long-term results, but I can vouch for all of the instantaneous, sparkly ones. I've been applying it after I double cleanse each morning (I swipe my face first with Sephora Collection's Triple Action Cleansing Water - Cleanse + Purify before going in with Shani Darden's Cleansing Serum) and before I apply my moisturizer for the day—usually Renée Rouleau's Skin Recovery Lotion ($44).\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288896/the-nue-co-the-pill-review-288896-1598981542388-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288896/the-nue-co-the-pill-review-288896-1598981593782-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>These skincare-supplement capsules feature a patented blend of vitamin C, zinc, champagne grape seed, and melon to improve the severity of sun damage (hello, luminosity!), pigmentation, acne, and skin elasticity. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288896/the-nue-co-the-pill-review-288896-1598981598098-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>The brand's clinically studied phytoceramides play nicely with hyaluronic acid, hydrolyzed collagen, and aloe vera and come packaged in easy-to-swallow capsules. src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/285337/best-chanel-perfumes-285337-1580941594650-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Growing up, my mom had the most enchanting collection of beauty products that took residence in her bathroom. (My dad's electric shaver, bare bar soap, and a lone bottle of 2-in-1 shampoo and conditioner didn't stand a chance and were banished to a different bathroom downstairs.) Atop my mom's porcelain vanity sat her jars of creams and powders, and along the wall, deep drawers were lined with rows of sophisticated lipstick bullets. Atop gleaming glass shelves sat her collection of Chanel perfumes. Even at a super-young age (and knowing nothing of Chanel's iconic name), I understood with an inherent knowledge there was something supremely special about the gilded bottle stoppers and black lacquer detail. The name \"Chanel\" was effortlessly etched into my subconscious as the epitome of glamour and covetousness. Nearly 20 years later (and now me being a beauty editor), that etching hasn't faded. Of course, Chanel makes loads of holy grail beauty products that anyone with an affinity for nail polish, lustrously glossed lips, or glowing skin would want to hoard, but it's the brand's collection of iconic fragrances that will always represent the upper echelon of anything and everything pertaining to beauty. So because everyone should own at least one Chanel perfume in their life, we're paying homage to the brand by featuring its five best fragrances ever, followed by additional (similar) perfumes from other brands you definitely need on your shopping radar as well. Keep scrolling to see the five best-ever Chanel perfumes and their similar addicting counterparts.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/285337/best-chanel-perfumes-285337-1580941598159-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/285337/best-chanel-perfumes-285337-1580941603145-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Fragrance Family: Floral. We're always on the hunt for the best <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-nail-growth-products/\" target=\"_blank\">nail-growth products</a> and expert practices for achieving extended talons, but that doesn't mean we don't love a good <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-nail-colors-for-short-nails\" target=\"_blank\">short-nail</a> moment from time to time. After all, there are few things more liberating than the carefree attitude that comes along with <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/olive-and-june-studio-manicure-kit\" target=\"_blank\">freshly chopped nails</a>. Opening cans and picking up coins are just a couple of simple pleasures that become infinitely easier.</p><p>Though keeping your claws cropped means having a little less real estate to use for <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/fall-nail-designs/\" target=\"_blank\">nail art</a>, there are still tons of short-nail designs that will satisfy even the most adventurous aficionados. Ahead, we've rounded up 13 decorative ideas to try on short nails, along with all the supplies you'll need to get the job done at home.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288839/short-nail-designs-288839-1599004268324-image.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Incorporate all your favorite colors and designs into one easy composition. Add as many or as few elements as your nail length will allow.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288839/short-nail-designs-288839-1599069113009-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>We love the neon shades in this polish set.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288839/short-nail-designs-288839-1598497938209-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>No matter how short your nails are, there's always enough space to create a reverse French-manicure design. This spin on the classic nail-art style is modern and oh so chic.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288839/short-nail-designs-288839-1599008503289-main.2560x2560uc.jpg\"><figcaption>The key to getting this design right might already be in your desk drawer. These hole reinforcers are perfect for creating that crescent-moon shape at the base of your nail. Simply stick it on slightly above the cuticle and fill in any nail space between the sticker and your skin with nail polish.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288839/short-nail-designs-288839-1598497910155-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Fine, curved lines are an easy nail look that brings in an ultra-cool design element without being too flashy. The best part? You can paint your lines in any color you want.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288839/short-nail-designs-288839-1599069141219-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>These skinny paintbrushes will help you achieve the fine lines of your dreams. Each brush comes with a cap, so you won't have to worry about frayed bristles.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288839/short-nail-designs-288839-1598497749610-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Can you imagine a dreamier nail design than fluffy clusters of cumulus clouds? Cloudy days are on the horizon.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288839/short-nail-designs-288839-1598497758427-main.1200x1365uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Looking for a bit of hardware to add to your manicure? target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a> fell into your lap just like that. What would you buy? This is the question I posed to my fellow editors, and with our imaginary money, we all found different yet equally thrilling (and useful) gems. While senior market editor Bobby selected some quality <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-racerback-tank-tops\" target=\"_blank\">wardrobe basics</a> to refresh his stash, editor in chief Kat has her eye on an easy fall top that will <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/new-jeans-outfits\" target=\"_blank\">look chic with jeans</a>, and senior news editor Erin is cluing us into the haircare products that will breathe life into your tresses. As for myself, I blew my entire budget on one standout piece: a warm chestnut brown pair of wide-leg trousers which I'd style with the <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=rHrU65XwIAHZIBTMr_94TORoLeNyQyQhfav_U235M1ypxtI1OGY8x6ymC0mBladdHLN_XnABQvcRXunerZykIuy5RuXcxvrI_0fJhAEOscWd0YXXuYVnLbXMq5MufhocSjBl9vHiQ2N3uv50vnpF9L64sJ0bWRPg15R6WDu0-AZjfLg9KbfsJCikEUUacrnS9BDc0wCHMZpwr-MG6oEUcGKapOjKxml_54xFL8RCtA\" target=\"_blank\">matching utility-inspired top</a> (sadly the top is outside of today's budget but is saved for another time). <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/trendy-clothes-for-fall-editor\" target=\"_blank\">Relaxed trousers</a> are the only wardrobe basic I really care about for fall, and I already have so many outfit ideas stored in my brain with this pair. Scroll on to see and shop all of our picks, knowing you can shop any editor's wish list without spending over half a Benjamin.</p></div></div></div><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288966/editor-amazon-shopping-288966-1599077767015-image.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288966/editor-amazon-shopping-288966-1599077523716-main.850x967uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"I love the basic tees from Amazon Essentials. href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/hailey-bieber-fall-boot-trend\" target=\"_blank\">Hailey Bieber</a>, you know exactly what I'm talking about when I say \"oversize everything.\" But if you aren't as familiar with <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/hailey-bieber-leopard-face-mask\" target=\"_blank\">her style </a>as some of her biggest fans are, then let me fill you in: Hailey is definitely considered a major fashion icon as far as celebrity style goes, but one look in particular that she has nailed is anything oversize. We're talking everything from a head-to-toe baggy suit moment to a hoodie so big, she can wear it as a dress. In theory, re-creating that vibe seems simple, but unless you've tried to pull off an oversize T-shirt–and–baggy-jean moment à la Hailey, you haven't come to terms with just how difficult it actually is. </p><p>While it might seem like she just throws together a bunch of baggy clothes and calls it a day, the reality is that there is a method behind the madness, and today, I'm here to decode it for you. Ahead, I have rounded up some of my favorite \"oversize everything\" Hailey moments and shopped out exactly what you'll need to get the looks in addition to a brief explanation of why each ensemble works. After reading through and shopping accordingly, you'll leave here feeling ten times more confident in your ability to embrace loose clothing this fall. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288907/best-oversized-clothing-288907-1598921403320-main.1200x1598uc.jpg\"><figcaption>On Hailey Bieber: Vans Old Skool Sneaker ($60). Yesterday, the couple visited the <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=QProjaNTvqX7Uu5Y9swNIQDHaI8mTpf_qdAawjfAAt19djWJ4w8TjOzS15Gy6Rg\" target=\"_blank\">Assistance League of Los Angeles</a> to replant the preschool's garden and speak to the kids about healthy eating.</p><p>For the casual outing, Markle wore a denim button-up shirt with skinny jeans and her favorite Rothys <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/splash/z6BWjFXrm?w=3702937\" target=\"_blank\">Black Solid Flats</a> ($145), which she also wore during her much-publicized <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/meghan-markle-australia-royal-tour-outfits\" target=\"_blank\">tour of Australia and New Zealand</a>. The appearance also had a significant meaning: It fell on the 23rd anniversary of Princess Diana's death, so Meghan and Harry planted her favorite flowers, forget-me-nots, in her honor. How sweet is that? biggest fashion pieces of the moment, which included many of the major ‘90s trends we still remember today. Recently, I was watching an episode when it occurred to me that her maxi tube skirt was very <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/fashion-to-buy-for-fall\" target=\"_blank\">on-trend for 2020</a>. In fact, I’ve been seeing the long, slinky skirt all over Instagram recently and have started to see the piece landing in the new arrivals sections at my favorite retailers.</p><p>Poised to make a huge comeback this fall, tube skirts are without doubt a Rachel Green-approved trend to keep your eye on in the coming months. Not only is it a great comfortable yet stylish <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/relaxed-suiting\" target=\"_blank\">anti-loungewear</a> option to swap in for sweatpants, but it’s very versatile. Paired with a matching tube top, you can instantly recreate one of the most iconic looks from the ‘90s. However, you can also style one with an off-the-shoulder cropped cardigan or a one-shoulder tank to make it feel very 2020. Ahead, see inspiration for how to wear the trend and then shop my edit of the best tube skirts on the market.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288915/best-tube-skirts-288915-1598938218853-main.1000x1500uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Snapped on the set of Friends in 1996, here, Rachel Green wears the tube skirt trend. 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"Why Didn't Anyone Ever Tell Me This Crucial Step for Buying a Foundation?","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/mIf7IE4kQI4/best-foundations-for-combination-skin","description":"<p>When shopping for a <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-foundations-for-mature-skin\" target=\"_blank\">foundation</a>, there are a couple of things to keep in mind. Most importantly, you want to find one that matches your <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-lipsticks-for-every-skin-tone\" target=\"_blank\">skin tone</a><em> just so,</em> right? The goal is to choose a shade that looks like a second skin but better and that blends in with both your skin tones and undertones. And while you're searching, you'll also want to consider the type of coverage you need. Do you need something full? Or do you want to go with a sheer option?</p><p><strong>But there's one factor that I had never really given much thought to when shopping for a foundation: my skin type.</strong> It turns out choosing a product with your specific skin type in mind can make a difference when it comes to application and the finished look. Maybe you've been in the same boat as me. Don't worry, though. We're about to get a foundation 101 session courtesy of the experts.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599155014903-main.1000x1333uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>If you want to choose a foundation for your specific skin type, where do you even start? The experts gave me these tips for each type:</p><p><strong>Normal:</strong> \"Normal skin types are usually the easiest to use with foundation,\" says <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=8dYiw3Q59jqnDgMbRd2kzD85zaUnSxKW2N6Fhpn3QcvSHlpEnkvIbj42Zh1sFghlIMGk2E537A\" target=\"_blank\">Robert Sesnek</a>, makeup artist for <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=UMLN5N43Qt35LZhzy5gFUVT-EB-vePusMmQA6gC8uQ09Pklf4mdYAQc9zFN8anWtzQ\" target=\"_blank\">Catrice Cosmetics</a>. \"You can buff foundation with a damp natural hair foundation brush for an overall easy and even finish.\" So you can pretty much choose any foundation here, and Sesnek recommends a liquid foundation for all skin types because he says they look the most real on skin and can look \"invisible\" when applied properly.</p><p><strong>Combination:</strong> You'll want to look for oil-free and/or water-based foundations, according to our experts.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599009394308-main.851x969uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong>Oily/Acne-Prone:</strong> \"You should look for an oil-free foundation if you have oily or combination-oily skin,\" recommends board-certified dermatologist <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=O6XW_Og2tuckGJCzI746cbWc2nNt6jsShrnG9IcgOiY0lnpxyq8XJYHbtXyS8lhFM3ccMpc6\" target=\"_blank\">Elyse Love</a>, MD, who practices at <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=Pfu5iRAlkSQZTR6Kjd-ujs6syt21LF3bHSwqu33m5LK-_4FyOw\" target=\"_blank\">GlamDerm</a> in New York City. \"Foundations can clog pores, which may cause bumps on the forehead and worsen dilated pores on the nose. Powders are great for all-over oily skin but can sometimes come off as drying on drier skin.\"</p><p><strong>Dry:</strong> Board-certified dermatologist <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=biqIHOlQFWAPS7cqjyo96oA5eTGsNaiXiGWY4BY-wUsPZg-p6qouz1A6zop-9w5yabWm\" target=\"_blank\">Karen Chinonso Kagha, MD</a> suggests looking for a foundation with a hydrating finish.</p><p><strong>Sensitive:</strong> \"For more sensitive skin, avoid products with fragrance, which is commonly used in makeup but can cause allergies in those with more sensitive skin,\" Kagha says.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599008491123-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Now that we're up to speed on foundations and skin types, we're going to focus on how to choose and apply products for people with combination skin, which is probably the most common skin type. \"Combination skin is used to describe those who have significantly different oil production on different areas of the face—typically oilier skin in the t-zone and normal or dry skin on the cheeks and chin,\" Love explains.</p><p>When you have combination skin, the biggest concern there is managing the <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-drugstore-foundations-for-oily-skin\" target=\"_blank\">oil production</a> of your t-zone without irritating or drying out your cheeks and chin.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599009451793-main.800x910uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Before applying foundation, you're going to want to prep your skin so the product goes on smoothly and looks flawless. But <em>how</em> you prep can depend on... you guessed it, your skin type. Across the board, you should make sure <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-drugstore-face-washes\" target=\"_blank\">your skin is clean</a>, no matter your type, says makeup artist <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=WDkFW1pJw8MWiyVIRHGK0MgLN2SizPqBTPx4V1bzDcoy_s6e5qMy8ygYzJf2quleRzFwXSlvz-9O\" target=\"_blank\">Georgie Eisdell</a>, whose clients include Gwyneth Paltrow and Sophie Turner. She particularly loves IS Clinical's Cleansing Complex for combination skin.</p><p>After cleansing, you'll have to work on controlling some of the oil-prone areas if you have combination skin. \"My secret is to double up! In addition to a moisturizer best for combination skin, use a textured cotton pad with micellar water to scrub off any buildup on the skin's surface. This is key to preventing congestion from oil buildup under the skin,\" says <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=KrYxfOxgPIC-ouxP2GpoJxZADPPWrhCr64gkgwfQ-B1sE2LZkJ00_gKj9zOS-Gk9l7A3z74ToSFSlkH_MUte\" target=\"_blank\">Christine Cherbonnier</a>, who is Yoko Ono's personal makeup artist.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599009515600-main.879x999uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>When it comes to applying foundation, formulation choices are important to keep in mind. \"If you use a foundation that is too moisturizing when you have combination skin, you may find you get shiny very quickly,\" Eisdell explains. \"It's also not ideal to use a foundation that is all about moisture, as it will be too much for the combination skin and could cause breakouts.\"</p><p>Makeup artist <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=vq7ARnRrFkfeWhxX_xKVo2fzX-SHySHkbcM0pYszlWaO9YoLCNWbl9dkUKIteHQU1o4biJVTsrU\" target=\"_blank\">Tamah Krinsky</a> suggests going with a matte formula and a <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-powder-foundations\" target=\"_blank\">little bit of powder</a>. \"You don't want your skin to look heavy, so a sheer-matte formula with a touch to no powder should do the trick. You want to keep the powder light to let the natural oil in your skin keep the matte formula from looking too heavy,\" she says.</p><p>And now that you know what to keep in mind when shopping, you might be ready to add to your cart. Below, we've got foundation recommendations for combination skin from the experts and our editors.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599004564223-main.4969x5650uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"You are less likely to break out from it, and it leaves a nice glow to the skin but isn't greasy,\" Eisdell says. \"I like to conceal using Laura Mercier's Secret Camouflage cream. [It's] excellent directly on spots—covering any issues one might have like sun damage, brown spots, melasma—and mixed with an eye cream. It is great as an under-eye concealer or brightener, too.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599004910175-main.1819x2069uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This liquid foundation is perfect if your combination skin is on the oilier side of the spectrum. It's formulated with salicylic acid to fight acne and blemishes and control shine.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599005143032-main.1000x1137uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"It gives a flawless finish, [has an] amazing shade range, and it's matte, so it looks natural and not shiny!\" Eisdell says. And she's right about the shade range. There are 50 to choose from. The oil-free formula won't clog pores and reduces shine.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599010144495-main.1500x1706uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599005345503-main.857x975uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"Combination oily-dry skin may prefer an oil-free liquid formula as a compromise,\" Love says. \"Dermablend's Flawless Creator foundation is my favorite foundation for that reason.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599005646799-main.1730x1968uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"I really love the Koh Gen Do Aqua Foundation,\" Krinsky says. \"While they aren't 'matte,' they control oil, and they don't sit on the skin in a way that is dewy. They look realistic without adding shine.\" The formula is sweat- and oil-resistant and leaves a glowy finish.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599005839573-main.1562x1776uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Maybelline's medium-coverage foundation is buildable and leaves a matte finish. It's formulated for normal to oily skin types.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599010235324-main.1500x1706uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599006167229-main.1565x1780uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This is one of Cherbonnier's picks. The medium-coverage foundation is lightweight, stays on for up to 24 hours, and blurs any imperfections. There are 50 shades to choose from to get an exact match.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599006345583-main.879x1000uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"When I have a client with combination skin, I personally like a foundation that has a sheer, liquid-like texture and is incredibly lightweight,\" Sesnek says. \"Look for a foundation like Catrice’s HD Liquid Coverage Foundation. It’s ultra-light and has great coverage, and it’s alcohol-, oil- and gluten-free.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599006639318-main.1195x1360uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Ilia Beauty's serum foundation is a favorite with Who What Wear editors. The clean product offers light coverage and SPF protection. It leaves a dewy, natural finish.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599010308166-main.1831x2081uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599006862977-main.4478x5092uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Both Eisdell and Cherbonnier vouched for this water-based foundation. \"This is an oil-free foundation, so it will naturally be less shiny,\" Eisdell adds. \"[It has] buildable coverage, and it is fantastic for irritated skin, too, as it has chamomile and aloe in it.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599007016490-main.5530x6290uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"I also really love the Armani Beauty Maestro and Face Fabric foundations,\" Krinsky says. \"They leave a beautiful powdery finish. The key to all of the matte foundations is to really use your powder sparingly so that the texture of your skin isn't completely gone.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599007053926-main.5176x5886uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599010359268-main.1682x1912uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599007236665-main.5270x5994uc.jpg\"><figcaption>\"it is a water-based foundation with light to medium coverage,\" Eisdell says. \"It lasts really well throughout the day but isn't chalky on the skin. I love this and use it often on myself and my clients.\"</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599007508417-main.1609x1829uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Another recommendation from Cherbonnier, this foundation from Charlotte Tilbury not only provides long-lasting coverage, but it also has ingredients that reduce the appearance of wrinkles and hydrate the skin.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599007639261-main.921x1047uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This drugstore find has an oil-free and water-based formula that leaves a matte finish.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599007810573-main.1836x2088uc.jpg\"><figcaption>This is a personal pick from Kagha: \"I prefer loose mineral-based powders such as the BareMinerals Loose Powder Foundation, especially during the summer when I am more oily.\" It has SPF protection, too.
