07016490-main.5530x6290uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx27/cdn20@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-42-24-257_a76d3710973061a4.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599007053926-main.5176x5886uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx18/cdn12@2020_1/2020/09/05/08-42-14-141_f58cb57c421dad36.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599010359268-main.1682x1912uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx3/cdn41@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-42-02-374_ffd412eff1ff2e8a.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599007236665-main.5270x5994uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx7/cdn94@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-42-28-711_d1315e43438a6070.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599007508417-main.1609x1829uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx11/cdn24@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-42-09-157_2f633e7ffd1f1033.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599007639261-main.921x1047uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx12/cdn65@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-42-43-123_47a46ee1946ddc5a.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288926/best-foundations-for-combination-skin-288926-1599007810573-main.1836x2088uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx18/cdn6@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-41-51-341_9cf48f0b429e3400.webp","http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~4/mIf7IE4kQI4":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx33/cdn42@2020_6/2020/09/05/08-42-55-217_063d766b58102694.webp"},"publishedOrCreatedDate":1599295287278},{"createdTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"Beyoncé Has Been Slaying Us With Her Style for 39 Years—These Pics Prove It","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/7QtkjgKv1I0/beyonce-style","description":"<p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566416998734-main.1200x900uc.gif\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong><span>Do you know who’s magical as fuck? Beyoncé. Anyone who disagrees can catch my side-eye because there’s no denying this woman. No other artist has quite dedicated themselves to their own evolution in their career, their art, their performances, their community, and their personal style all while being unapologetically themselves. </span></strong></p><p><strong><span>Being witness to a black woman living embodiment of excellence, not to mention witnessing the slayage, is a blessing, which is why I did not take rounding up Beyoncé’s best style moments of all time lightly. I did my journalistic duty and looked through every decade (around 2000+ images' worth) and spent hours debating each image. </span></strong></p><p><strong><span>Hold onto your edges, people. These looks might hurt you.</span></strong></p><p><strong><span>Baby Beyoncé? Yes, please. As an avid member of the Beyhive, I'm always scouring the internet for pictures of <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/beyonce-birthday-2018\" target=\"_blank\">Beyonce as a child</a>, and this was a great find. Not only is she rocking a timeless tie-dye look, but she and Solange are so damn cute. </span></strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566058457343-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong><span>Oh, there are so many things wonderful about this look. First off, all of Destiny’s Child's notorious matching sets were to die for. Secondly, this look is in many ways a time capsule for the trends of the 90s (hello platform boots). It’s around the time the group released their second album, </span><em><span>The Writing's on the Wall, </span></em><span>which gave us all the iconic bops. </span></strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566243838457-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong><span>Let’s be real here, the culture’s piping tea moments and most</span><em><span> extra </span></em><span>looks can always be found at MTV’s Music Video Awards—and the 2000s were no exception to this fact. From J.Lo baring it all in her </span><span><a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/jennifer-lopez-viral-outfits\">Sean John crop top</a> </span><span>to Destiny’s Child taking a bedazzler to their leather corsets, the 2000s has never disappointed my insatiable desire for </span><a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/mtv-vma-red-carpet-2000s\"><span>wild looks</span></a><span>. </span></strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566244058051-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong><span>The launch of the BET awards in 2001 was historic, and so was Destiny’s child look for the red carpet. Someone, please give Beyoncé an award just for looking this good in a <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/see-through-dress\" target=\"_blank\">sheer dress</a> before it was chic. </span></strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566244263827-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>While Michelle Williams took the stage performing in the Broadway play <em>Aida,</em> Beyoncé took to the show’s the red carpet in an all-denim look. Beyoncé is that really you? In all denim? So very 2002 of you.  </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566244536604-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong><span>Beyoncé stole the stage during the 2004 Grammy Awards. Not only did she perform with Prince, but she took home not one, but </span></strong><span>five</span><strong><span> awards for her album, <em>Dangerously in Love</em>. If that weren't enough, she also stole our attention in this golden silk dress designed by Tina Knowles herself.  </span></strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566244763484-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong><span>Some may think of Beyoncé’s most recent street style looks as proof of her slayage, but don’t get it twisted—she’s been serving looks since 2004. This green beret with a blackberry phone in Paris is no exception. </span></strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566245034857-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>The moment Beyoncé stepped onto the 77th Annual Academy Awards red carpet in this rich black velvet floor-length dress, I lost my breath. Leave it to a Virgo—yes, that's Beyoncé's zodiac sign—to make a classic strapless black dress even posher. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566245239711-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong><span>Let us not forget the moment that Destiny’s Child stunned us all at the 2005 BET Awards with their performance of </span><em><span>Cater 2 U</span></em><span>—Beyoncé giving a lap dance to Terrance Howard? Iconic. And though Terrance never had the baddest woman in the game up in his sheets, he was able to appreciate this full-length body-con nude dress. </span></strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566245246073-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong><span>Yes, I’m fully aware this is her second full-length floor gown in this list, but it’s to prove a point. Point being that Beyoncé comes to slay every damn time. It just so happens to be that this time she was slaying in a stunning Ellie Saab gown at the 64th Annual Golden Globes. </span></strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566245326589-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong><span>Nothing has ever been the same since the 2009 MTV Music Awards. In case you were living in outer space at the time, let me bring you up to speed: Back in 2009, Beyoncé blessed us with every single girl’s anthem, </span><em><span>Single Ladies (Put a Ring on it), </span></em><span>which was nominated for MTV’s best video of the year. </span></strong></p><p><strong><span>When the iconic video was snubbed by one of Taylor Swift’s mediocre videos (sorry Taylor fans, it’s not her best work), Kanye stormed the stage to interrupt Taylor Swift’s speech and proclaim his love for Beyoncé’s video. For worse, this ceremony started Taylor and Kayne’s infamous back-and-forth relationship, but for the best, it established Beyonce's go-to onstage look as embellished leotards.  </span></strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566245420272-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>What does one wear to accept their Grammy nomination for the best female pop vocal performance? Giorgio Armani of course—or at least that's what Beyoncé choose to wear in 2010. And while I love seeing her in a Privé dress, I’m also here for her in 3D glasses.  </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1567780003348-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong><span>There are so many moments that have defined Beyoncé as a force to be reckoned with, but none sit as close to my heart than her singing at Barack Obama’s inauguration in 2013. While Beyoncé wasn’t the first black woman to perform at a presidential inauguration, she did join the ranks of iconic black artists like Arthea Franklin, Marian Anderson, and James Brown. Not only did she stun us with her incredible performance of the national anthem, but she did so in an equally as stunning black Pucci dress paired with a Christian Dior coat. </span></strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566245514641-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><span>Beyoncé is constantly a <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/beyonce-style-cult-gaia-by-far-marine-serre\" target=\"_blank\">champion for new designers</a>, in fact for the 56th Grammy Awards in 2014 she wore this stunning floor-length dress designed by former project runway contestant Michael Costello. Leave it to Beyoncé to not only lift the voice of new talent but to look damn good while doing so. </span></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566245646117-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><span>If the dictionary added an image next to the word \"flawless,\" it would </span><em><span>have</span></em><span> to be a picture of Beyoncé in couture Givenchy at the 2014 Met Gala. Not only is it one of her best looks, but </span>It’s also the look she wore in the infamous elevator scuffle where Solange popped off Jay Z for allegedly cheating. Frankly, if I were to witness a fight over trifling matters, I too would want to be dripping in Givenchy sequins just as a reminder to Becky that she ain’t even half of me. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566245741308-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong><span>If your heart didn’t melt when Blue Ivy and Jay Z presented Beyoncé with the Vanguard Award in 2014, you’re not a true beehive member. Not only was Blue saying, “Good job, Mommy” iconic, but this moment encapsulates all of the albums and ensembles that lead up to this point. It was Beyoncé not only getting the recognition she deserves but showing the world success and motherhood aren't anomalies.  </span></strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566245906549-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>How do I describe my love for what Beyoncé and J.Lo wore to <em>Vanity Fair</em>'s post-87th Annual Academy Awards party? I can't—it's too much, this much pretty hurts. From Beyonce's bob to her full-length Stella McCartney dress, this look makes me want to sign a non-disclosure right now just so I can party with these two.  </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566246025776-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong><span>This look kills me. Not only does Beyoncé prove yet again that her style game isn’t limited to the stage, but she’s rocking a polished all-denim look at Yeezy’s first fashion show next to our other queen, Rihanna. Consider me dead—the cause of my premature death? Too much fashion.  </span></strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1599151151300-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>I ain’t sorry for the following statement: Kim Kardashian West wearing a naked dress pales in comparison to Beyoncé’s 2015 Met Gala look. No one can re-create the queen; she’s just too much for all of us, and the moment she proved it is when she showed up late to the 2015 gala in this barely-there bejeweled Givenchy. Moments like these fill me with infinite gratitude to be living in the time of Beyoncé. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566246156845-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong><span>The wonderful thing about art of all forms is that it makes people uncomfortable. It can pose questions and raise awareness—and Beyonce’s performance at the 50th Super Bowl did just that. She performed </span><em><span>Formation</span></em><span> on the field in a black military-inspired leotard alongside her backup dancers rocking afros adorned with black berets. </span></strong></p><p><strong><span>Their looks paid homage to the Black Panthers 50 years after the group’s formation, and to say people were upset over these berets is an understatement. Granted they weren't actually upset about the style choices, the running joke happened to be that people forgot she was black until this performance. During it, they were clearly reminded. </span></strong></p><p><strong><span>But just to be clear, Beyoncé has always been black; she just also has happened to be beloved by all, which is why this style moment was one for the books. She used her platform to stand up for communities of color—to bring forth an important conversation around police brutality, and to reinform about the misconceptions of the Black Panther Party—via her performance and styling choices. Frankly, nothing is more stylish than that. </span></strong></p><p><span>There’s no denying that Beyoncé has created the tracks every self-proclaimed feminist bumps post-breakup. But one of the best gifts to the world was when she released her visual album, </span><em><span>Lemonade, </span></em><span>in 2016. In many ways, this is Beyoncé’s most unapologetic work; it gave us a raw glimpse into her reckoning with infidelity but was filled with visual moments that were unapologetically black and unapologetically stylish. While Beyoncé has always used her performances and music to represent her identity as a black feminist, each look within the visual album was calculated, chic, and most of all a call to action for all women of color to get in formation, throw their middle fingers up, and slay.  </span></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1599151128894-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong><span>After releasing </span><em><span>Lemonade</span></em><span>, Jay was banned from being Bey's </span></strong><strong><span>date for a while, which is </span><em><span>totally </span></em><span>okay because we were blessed with seeing 4-year-old Blue Ivy show up to the 2016 MTV Video Music Awards with her mom, both in matching gowns. Beyoncé broke records by taking home eight awards that night, but Blue Ivy wore an <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/blue-ivy-dress-vmas-2016\" target=\"_blank\">$11,000 gown</a>—basically, it was the best girl’s night ever. </span></strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566246349061-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>If you're not sure what the phrase \"Guccied down\" means, look no further than when Beyoncé was spotted in New York in this full all-pink ensemble. Beyoncé dripping in Gucci on a casual day in October is the living embodiment of being decked out.  </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566246379332-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><span>The best Beyoncé news we’ve ever received is when </span><a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/celebrity-pregnancy-announcements-instagram\"><span>Beyoncé announced </span></a><span>she was having twins in early 2017. Eleven days later she gave us arguably one of her most iconic performances, and looks, to date. Wearing a Peter Dundas creation (the same designer who created her the iconic yellow dress she wore in her </span><em><span>Hold Up</span></em><span> music video), she paid tribute to all the African, Hindu, and Greek goddesses that represented not only fertility but divine feminine energy at the 2017 Grammy Awards. In essence, Beyoncé was not only a literal goddess, but she was making a tribute to the goddess within all of us.  </span></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1599151115720-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong><span>You better believe that Beyoncé didn’t share the first picture of the twins in any basic fashion—she actually broke the internet with this iconic photo of her holding them in an equally internet-breaking dress by Palomo. It made every month waiting for Queen B updates so very worth it. </span></strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1599151097310-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><span>Leave it to Beyoncé to look this fabulous post-pregnancy—she’s proof that we’re smart enough to make these millions, strong enough to bear the children, and then get back to business. And Beyoncé meant </span><em><span>business</span></em><span> with this custom Walter Mendez dress that she wore to Jay’s Tidal benefit concert in 2017.  </span></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1599151069673-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>The custom Nicolas Jebran black gown Beyoncé wore to the 2018's Grammy's is by far one of the best looks of her life. Sure, she was late for the ceremony, but can you blame her? When you have a dress like that, it will take you 45 minutes to get all dressed up, and you still might not make it… </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1566246535663-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>While this isn't the first time we've spotted Beyoncé and Blue in <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/beyonce-blue-ivy-matching-gowns\" target=\"_blank\">cute ensembles </a>together, it was great to see them casual together at the 67th NBA All-Star game. Not only does Beyoncé per usual kill with a <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/beyonce-nba-all-star-game-outfit\" target=\"_blank\">chic courtside look</a>, but she left us wondering how far we'd go to photobomb this selfie situation.  </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1567780255151-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong><span>Beyoncé made history by being the first black woman to headline <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/beyonce-coachella-outfits\" target=\"_blank\">Coachella</a>, and if you haven’t seen Homecoming, her Netflix documentary,</span><span>about it yet then your life is incomplete. Her performance at Coachella could be defined as one of the best of her entire career—and the costumes are up there too. The clothing she wears for the performance not only pay homage to HBCUs and steppers, but those custom Christian Louboutin boots with holographic fringe are historic in and of themselves. </span></strong></p><p><span>Let it be historically recognized that 2018 was the year of Beyoncé. If Coachella wasn’t enough, </span><span>in Jay and Bey fashion, mid-tour they released their first joint album, </span><em><span>Everything Is Love</span></em><span>. </span><span>It was a response to their previous famed albums (</span><em><span>Lemonade </span></em><span>and </span><em><span>4:44</span></em><span>) to tell the story of their love. But what made it even more epic is the fact they released their music video for the single entitled \"Apeshit\" <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/beyonce-jay-z-everything-is-love\" target=\"_blank\">filmed in the Louvre</a>. Casual, right? I’m not sure if it gets any better than seeing Beyoncé and Jay in matching suits in front of the Mona Lisa.  </span></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1599150956766-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><span>Speaking of their tour (and from personal experience), I can attest to saying that the outfits Beyoncé wore for their <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/beyonce-on-the-run-ii-tour-outfits\" target=\"_blank\"><em>On The Run II</em> </a>tour were some of her best looks onstage. Not only was it incredible to witness the compilation of two incredible artist’s work over a decade, but I may have shed a few tears in the presence of all the amazing looks from designers like Balmain, LaQuan Smith, Gucci, and Dunas.  </span></p><p>Beyoncé made history with this look—<em>quite literally</em>. Not only was Beyonce's <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/beyonce-vogue-september-issue\" target=\"_blank\">feature in Vogue</a> photographed by the first African American photographer to ever shoot a cover in its 125-year history, but the image of her wearing the sequin-covered Valentino dress with the gold Philip Treacy headpiece will be part of the Smithsonian's National Portrait Gallery’s permanent collection.  </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1599150942538-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Anytime I'm feeling particularly down, I just remind myself to look at this picture of Beyoncé in Italy celebrating her birthday while wearing a stunning Caroline Constas set. It is the only mental vacation I need. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1599150928656-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><strong><span>Who runs the world? Beyoncé. Because even in the midst of serving the most iconic tour looks and cover shoot to date in her career, she managed to make time to perform at the <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=nACjWAuT6Jgz379J1Sfzk4C0TcqKGQsPu7rF_Ht8WQm_-dKXN-EgROnb5A\" target=\"_blank\">City of Hope</a> Gala in this breathtaking </span><span>Ralph and Russo couture dress from the brand's fall 2018 collection. Beyoncé outdid herself again with this look—but are we even surprised? </span></strong></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1599150907901-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Beyoncé does not just serve looks or sing songs; she uses her platform to advocate for what's right, which is why it came as no surprise that she and Jay headlined the inaugural Global Citizen Festival in South Africa honoring Nelson Mandela's legacy. Don't get me wrong here; her looks were phenomenal because they highlighted a diverse set of <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/beyonce-global-citizen-festival-outfits\" target=\"_blank\">African designers</a>. But don't let it detract from the fact the concert brought in over $7 billion dollars to help the United Nations’ <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=l9OxysnS-TloS3Wf34ji4bfBVe1xXlf2MA4s2UXQSr8ul-oKotXhmLDXhj1K2xvk-lgoZrH3hPy2Pp60qCxMZxf2wBk\" target=\"_blank\">anti-poverty effort</a>. If that ain't legendary, I don't know what is.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1599150893799-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Honestly, there not a more badass moment than when the Carters won a grammy at the beginning of 2019 for <em>Everything is Love </em>and still didn't show up to the ceremony. But them not attending didn't mean we weren't blessed with a bomb look—they showed up in their best possible brunch looks for Rock Nation. Can I get away with wearing this Balmain dress to brunch too?</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1599150884404-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>While the hive lost it over the whole potential Becky situation at the 2019 NBA finals, I lost it over this look. Let's be real, Jay ain't gonna risk losing his wife again, especially when she pulls up in an all-nude Alexandre Vauthier set. So please, Beehive, let's remember that RBF doesn't mean the new Becky has re-emerged. Let's focus our energy not on death threats, but on Beyoncé wearing this <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/beyonce-nba-finals-by-far-purse\" target=\"_blank\">By Far bag</a>. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1567780835286-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Beyoncé served multiple looks for <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/lion-king-premiere-red-carpet\" target=\"_blank\"><em>The Lion King</em>'s red carpet</a>, but she made the world stop when she was spotted with Megan Markle in this floor-length yellow dress by the under-the-radar brand Cong Tri. Beyoncé never ceases to amaze. She takes our breath away with every song, and every look and then say says, \"Now carry on.\"</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/281901/beyonce-style-281901-1599150864117-main.850x1275uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>While 2020 has slowed down the rest of the world—Beyoncé has continued to outdo herself. More recently she blessed us with the film, <em>Black Is King</em>. Styled by <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/beyonce-black-is-king-costume-designer-interview\" target=\"_blank\">Zerina Akers</a> the film features over 60 looks honoring the Black diaspora, from emerging designers. Basically. Beyoncé proved yet again, she's the queen. </p><p><em>Next: <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/summer-lip-color-trends\" target=\"_blank\">3 Lip Colors Beyoncé's Makeup Artist Would Remove From Your Vanity This Summer</a></em></p><p><em><em>This post was previously published and has since been updated.</em></em></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~4/7QtkjgKv1I0\" href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/comfortable-fall-fashion-trends\" target=\"_blank\">comfort</a> has always been important when shopping for shoes, it's risen to the very top of our priority list when considering any new pairs right now. Whether it's flats, sandals, or as we'll dive into today, boots, there's no reason why our shoes shouldn't feel just as good as they look. And with fall fashion on the brain, I know there must be other people who, like me, are on the hunt for the most comfortable boots to wear all season.</p><div class=\"widget text\"><div class=\"text text__wrapper text__wrapper-default\"><div class=\"text--inner\"><p class=\"p p--story\">With that in mind, I reached out to friends, family, and coworkers to see which boots they recommend, then also spent a good amount of time scrolling through sites like <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=pJ4BBAvlnlxI409ENDrYZJBSKXBuSVta1hF2mfubar26Y8BBTwq9uDyhfdyRTL9FNsN8UXGre7rsq8UiHBOfZYKIQDfDob3lO1BNkRiWD30QZrk1ISnD07Y0sVT8lrOyra6MHqDkkIL35MsgciZXTLDMKWRR8zribKY3_f8ezSCNyIoVxoXL_9uIyR8QK0sTkxtyAWBBqowYNy8jNFVemt2yGZeleOPt0oOaA6OAsycHBnc-phXZsaOE-TYCIJ_VdglxD9lJO3BR-IfgI2qEX9wjja2JDtJb\" target=\"_blank\">Nordstrom</a>, <a class=\"link link--story\" href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=KPntbxKsMrdtOkDt-OPCyGm_vr3fBnyYx6sIymM7jYmF6VBKk9as\">Amazon</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=tfFF_gbtFwErbKc7zSV7BkoW0q3hwWgLPNTayx6MaHGOYe-H0wh8Ee0Dw3gDVjXRGK6HBEc2t0ed0-8ac9m-zLay3Nib-eyeBWyEGL7Rfd2255pWQxcE8RXssooJEJUh2ya5vX2Y7zxg2o4jiQeYDe8HbQkbuOuJ9woOJmF_SgI4PtuMwFOiJQGlPbw6ePkr6qANbnyiTdjZ\" target=\"_blank\">Shopbop</a> for the most comfortable boots that have the best reviews with comfort specifically mentioned throughout. The results are in and it comes down to the following eighteen can’t-go-wrong options at every style, heel height, and budget. target=\"_blank\">boho dresses</a> that we'll always love. Maybe it's that they're a whole outfit in one, maybe it's their effortlessness, or maybe it's that they encourage us to twirl around. Whichever the reason, we're always down to wear pretty boho dresses. However, sometimes the weather isn't in our favor (hello, 90-degree heat) and long-sleeved maxi dresses just don't add up.</p><p>That's why <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-fall-dress-trends\" target=\"_blank\">when fall rolls around</a>, our boho dreams come alive. Not only can we wear them with a pair of <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/most-comfortable-boots-for-women\" target=\"_blank\">boots</a>, but we can also have fun layering them and contrasting their fun prints with the fabrics of our favorite jackets.</p><p>So to share our excitement, we've rounded up 24 boho dresses that were made to be worn in fall.</p><p><figure><img 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"13 Reasons January Jones Looks Half Her Age","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/_JIiZxkoDDo/january-jones-instagram-beauty-tips","description":"<p>We're not sure exactly when it was that we first became fans of <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-violet-grey-products\" target=\"_blank\">January Jones.</a> Was it her most iconic role to date as Betty Draper? Or smaller \"Oh my god, it's January Jones!\" roles in classic films like<em> Love Actually </em>circa 2003? Either way, we have major love for the actress's quirky real-life demeanor and, of course, amazing style and beauty aesthetic. (We have dozens of screenshots on our camera rolls to prove it.) Between her practically <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/how-to-minimize-pores\" target=\"_blank\">pore-less complexion</a>, playful approach to makeup, and <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-drugstore-hair-products\" target=\"_blank\">super-shiny strands</a>, we desperately want to know all her beauty secrets, especially considering she looks roughly half her 41 years.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282841/january-jones-instagram-beauty-tips-282841-1570041395212-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>We're super appreciative that we're not alone in our admiration, and Jones regularly listens to her fans' Instagram requests by posting ample intel about her beauty routine—from the supplements she swears by to the extensive skincare rituals she credits her glowing skin to. We did some major digging (the kind of digging that takes us from 8 a.m. to 2 p.m.) to compile a 13-point list featuring all of Jones's best beauty tips, secrets, and favorite products. Keep scrolling! Ahead, 13 reasons January Jones looks half her age. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282841/january-jones-instagram-beauty-tips-282841-1596494382840-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282841/january-jones-instagram-beauty-tips-282841-1570041402354-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Take a scroll through Jones's Instagram, and you'll immediately notice the actress has a flair for a pretty punch of pink makeup—be it on her eyes or lips. The juicy hue brightens her complexion and definitely supports her youthful glow. We're not sure of the exact product ID here, but the latest Norvina launch from Anastasia Beverly Hills is the only palette people can talk about at the moment. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282841/january-jones-instagram-beauty-tips-282841-1596494472320-main.1080x1349uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282841/january-jones-instagram-beauty-tips-282841-1596494647423-main.800x0uc.jpg\"><figcaption>Jones knows that SPF is only one part of the equation for ample sun protection. She's always decked out in sun-shielding hats and sunglasses.</figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282841/january-jones-instagram-beauty-tips-282841-1596494745961-main.1128x2000uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282841/january-jones-instagram-beauty-tips-282841-1596494804014-main.1080x1279uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282841/january-jones-instagram-beauty-tips-282841-1570041434353-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption>According to Jones, she's always changing her mind regarding her cut and length, which not only keeps her look fresh but keeps her strands healthy and bouncy thanks to the regular trims. Plus, the A-list and beauty editors alike are obsessed with this cult-loved cream from Virtue Labs. The smell is intoxicating, and it's an amazing fix for rough ends in between your salon appointments. </figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/282841/january-jones-instagram-beauty-tips-282841-1596495055580-main.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>After perusing her Instagram, we noticed she stays loyal to her skincare treatment plan and regularly visits <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=Oeaa67X951x8EtClcSq_9Nl_n5wFWMWqwI01DuTzx_NTm0-UPUb8k739c0B9zNTur19Y5hQVexF0\" href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=t99Y1v_4AuBLw6BCjeSKDeJcctGoD9lYQhahf6hLAMsWPhLqBe-tg9V0UeARIVfA69knrc7X3OeQnaFSvAlVT6HB4gnQDw\" target=\"_blank\">Diamond InstaFacials</a>, which entail lasering, injections of platelet-rich plasma (from the patient), micro-needling, and a soothing mask to finish. </p><p>\"I just recently tried the PRP blood facial or 'vampire facial' by <a class=\"notranslate\" href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=OZxUK9sfeC62LEftw6bksbl-g-pOFmjmCzyD-NN5llCSaRL9rffx55T7RTzqI2cQlJxjfhaOvvSL\">@drjasondiamond</a> and am starting to see the results of that, it was fascinating, I’m trying to decide if it was worth the $$. I'll let you know,\" she explains in <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=wd1QagyL7j2XG39piOGtckcDCS_uaZjeZ2RAXO71xArv3MVUDeYUsmhr15FO7SqbFdzKJ0CGM08\" target=\"_blank\">this post</a>.</p><p><figure><img href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=aNjKhapDb1pPE-JQOzcyBKJq6KXARD38pVH8TJL-Tw8W1WN6Dqj0A4qWk9oc9Ily_Hf0AVhKoBhMgvPiPX8\" target=\"_blank\">Kristen Nichols</a>, highlighting on-the-rise fashion brands we have our eye on.</em></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1597868922571-image.1200x900uc.gif\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p class=\"p1\">As a fashion editor, every so often, a brand really grabs you that you simply can’t stop thinking about it. That’s exactly what happened when I first discovered <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=1pYsI5QnV-qGAjwha6-EoioIRUMZx-RCy0qHA-MbSlEqDbfaJrLe\" target=\"_blank\">Isa Boulder</a> back in January this year. Eager to find out more about the brand after spotting some photos of their stunning, ruched swimsuits on Instagram, I hoped to place an order, only to realize they hadn’t officially launched yet. My instincts told me they were about to be big, though.</p><p class=\"p2\">Fast-forward a few months and the brand is now <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=mH9vLNPt9mDuceNT6SyJDUxQ0gqyIpy9lNEt9ECgdI7UdTsF0sJ-M6DdeXDzoE6V4py3CZA9t_B1pb__EW3eiikozr_9CvY0KGtg5LHkTpJFILeq5udJZOgfJ0qhncvWypPvuAUOPVe83VAjuSK-ILbjb5NxyXHcGTgO-NaErbzerIaJizQEd0vkPamDGdHr2-JgRBmnmkhrn0nv3fpABb1BaF52wR1KeVMc60uJ67WVojgrynuc0Wl0zLyn2IrvL4yvenBdxMQJ0RbI12O2OoZwGyq0J4XBJnhJt-ZuQpP7p5tgUR3Oy4SVqToJTjlLZU58K0PmjpyOVAwh6Ii9BHFZbHSUdsDQvILVBgQMsK0DbBJvgFvcb6OdKKrKnrqbp4p2eoE2SIAmhtxD\" target=\"_blank\">sold on Matches Fashion</a> and has become a favorite of <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/fashion-to-buy-for-fall\" target=\"_blank\">insiders</a>. Interested to find out about Isa Boulder’s quick rise to cult status amongst the fashion set, I reached out to founders Cecilia Basari and Yuli Suri to find out more about the Bali-based brand. Ahead, read our interview as they dive into how they started out in swimwear, why local artisans are key to the brand, and the most popular pieces from the collection.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1597785634870-image.1080x1345uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028201863-main.1148x1643uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028784634-main.1226x1772uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599077810554-main.1103x1683uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p class=\"p1\"><strong>Tell us about yourselves and your background in fashion.</strong></p><p class=\"p2\">One of us worked for a few years in the Bali garment industry as a pattern cutter, and the other graduated in womenswear from Central Saint Martins. We both wanted to create a business together which infused both our expertise and passion in garment making.</p><p class=\"p1\"><strong>What inspired you to start Isa Boulder?</strong></p><p class=\"p2\">We are very interested in the craft of making clothes and find joy in the continual process of discovering new ways to do so. Be it through a tactile method like crochet or something more technical like through experimental pattern cutting.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1597785780620-image.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028115847-main.1050x1407uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028104393-main.1145x1481uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p class=\"p1\"><strong>I read that you’ve never been photographed in swimsuits. Why did you decide to design swimwear?</strong></p><p class=\"p2\">We were acquaintances with a group of seamstresses who were dismissed from their jobs where they had been working in swimwear manufacturing for almost a decade. Hence, we were compelled to design our first collection swimwear-focused to make sure that while highlighting the skills of our colleagues, we were able to produce very high quality garments (or at least the best that we could). It wasn’t necessarily our idea to simply revolve our designs around this swimwear specialism. It was a good experience to familiarize ourselves with swimwear, as even though it’s small pieces of garments, they are actually a lot more tricky to perfect/sew well than people think. </p><p class=\"p1\"><strong>How would you describe the brand?</strong></p><p class=\"p2\">There is an emphasis on craftsmanship and whatever we design, we just want to make sure it’s the best possible quality pieces we feel we can achieve, and our items are not necessarily led by a certain trend or style, but coming from a starting point of technique and materiality. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1597785516385-image.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599077817565-main.928x1566uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028239505-main.1283x1806uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028853866-main.1162x1660uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p class=\"p1\"><strong>Isa Boulder has established itself as a must-know emerging brand that has been a favorite among fashion insiders. How have you grown so quickly?</strong></p><p class=\"p2\">We feel very blessed that the women who have responded well to our items have since told friends of theirs, who then told friends of theirs, with the genuine desire to show support and love for our company. </p><p class=\"p1\"><strong>What is the inspiration behind your signature swimwear designs?</strong></p><p class=\"p2\">It started with the fabric, draping, and then figuring out what silhouettes would work well for the female form. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1597785548416-image.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028023099-main.1160x1415uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028035093-main.1100x1405uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p class=\"p1\"><strong>Why is it important to you to focus on sustainability and handcrafted pieces?</strong></p><p class=\"p2\">There are already so many garments in the world, it doesn’t make sense to rehash designs just for the sake of it. Even though in an ideal world we would steer clear from the fashion industry completely (since, at times, we do find that we’re in conflict with our moral values when noticing all these waste that we are contributing to the world especially after/during garment production), we are continually finding ways to minimize our negative impact on the environment through our bespoke approach to production and eventually focusing into knitwear. </p><p class=\"p1\"><strong>As an Indonesian brand, how does the local culture influence your company and designs?</strong></p><p class=\"p2\">We work very closely with local artisans and usually, our design process revolves around using techniques and production methods that have been passed down in generations. Through constant communication and a truly symbiotic relationship with the small manufacturers we work with, we have learned a lot from their technical experiences and skills. Most importantly, our aim is to ensure that while we grow as a small company, these small manufacturers also get to benefit from our growth.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1597785588272-image.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028337635-main.1073x1309uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028319027-main.1086x1332uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599077836927-main.1167x1556uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599077835063-main.1112x1558uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p class=\"p1\"><strong>What are your must-buy pieces from the collection?</strong></p><p class=\"p2\">We feel that the ruched tops are very flattering for all cup sizes. We have heard many positive comments from women who are more flat-chested—they feel the ruching gives them volume which makes them feel very confident.</p><p class=\"p1\"><strong>What are the fresh ways to style your swimsuits this summer?</strong></p><p class=\"p2\">It’s nice to see swimwear outside of the context of the beach and also worn layered with casual clothes to downplay the fanciness/shininess of the satin swim fabric.</p><p class=\"p1\"><strong>Tell us about what’s next for Isa Boulder.</strong></p><p class=\"p2\">We hope to continue making clothes that make women feel good. </p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1597785717023-image.1080x1350uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028613693-main.1033x1457uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028652222-main.1058x1435uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599077890875-main.1078x1330uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599077854825-main.1084x1425uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><em>Next, discover <a 8x1566uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx13/cdn61@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-42-35-273_34a2a441e36af49c.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028239505-main.1283x1806uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx2/cdn100@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-42-13-907_56fc26a09380bc80.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028853866-main.1162x1660uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx4/cdn71@2020_3/2020/09/05/08-42-54-656_0b7a26fd0bef8eb2.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1597785548416-image.1080x1350uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx12/cdn21@2020_6/2020/09/05/08-41-44-445_e88feaa3002efa64.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028023099-main.1160x1415uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx18/cdn40@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-42-56-330_61d5ba7cf0e57a41.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028035093-main.1100x1405uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx12/cdn99@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-42-18-644_c2a19beb10c0924a.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1597785588272-image.1080x1350uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx/cdn13@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-42-59-449_081c3cd6313438c6.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028337635-main.1073x1309uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx29/cdn67@2020_3/2020/09/05/08-42-12-280_228a39ba84a4687d.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028319027-main.1086x1332uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx25/cdn81@2020_3/2020/09/05/08-42-15-336_d322093d89de5e2c.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599077836927-main.1167x1556uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx1/cdn83@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-42-19-687_deedfbeb888f63ec.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599077835063-main.1112x1558uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx3/cdn9@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-41-44-367_66fc38f320815297.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1597785717023-image.1080x1350uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx7/cdn32@2020_6/2020/09/05/08-42-51-347_1ef168bd0814619c.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028613693-main.1033x1457uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx25/cdn75@2020_6/2020/09/05/08-41-38-680_57c044a6085b8e0d.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599028652222-main.1058x1435uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx25/cdn69@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-43-04-118_2b73f8b75a6d560e.webp","https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599077890875-main.1078x1330uc.jpg":null,"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/288696/isa-boulder-brand-review-288696-1599077854825-main.1084x1425uc.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx5oss/cdn60@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-43-20-349_816e8bd0bf2e105f.webp","http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~4/Q0UiLbQVmRA":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx1/cdn53@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-41-48-380_72d6cfc2e57d821e.webp"},"publishedOrCreatedDate":1599295287275},{"createdTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:41:27","title":"5 Tips for Surviving the Heavy-Earring Trend","link":"http://feeds.whowhatwear.com/~r/WhoWhatWear/~3/FOJNR615lRE/heavy-earrings","description":"<p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/251558/heavy-earrings-251558-1599154164818-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Abstract shapes and architectural inspiration are dominating some of our <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-everyday-earrings\" target=\"_blank\">favorite earring designs</a> this season. A pair of statement-making earrings can instantly dress up a <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/easy-outfit-ideas\" target=\"_blank\">casual outfit</a> or make for an eye-catching accessory during a night out. However, heavy earrings can also take a massive toll on the shape and condition of your ears. But before you toss out your favorite pair of oversize <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/best-earrings-for-sensitive-ears\" target=\"_blank\">earrings</a>, we recommend taking a look at what you can do to sport the trend without sacrificing comfort. Here are five essential tips for how to wear heavy earrings.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/251558/heavy-earrings-251558-1599155974876-main.1200x1598uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>One of the major problems with heavy earrings isn’t just their weight but the way it’s distributed. The way earrings are designed, they can put an extraordinary amount of pressure on a very small portion of the ear. Try adding a small, near-invisible patch on the back of the ear, like Lobe Wonder <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=z-wJrAhgqZGss8k8UMDUXaQk-P7h5nKmdJxmNctJWRtfK60RBS0\" target=\"_blank\">Ear Support Patches</a> ($7), to alleviate the stress. This will distribute the weight of the earrings over a greater portion of the ear.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/251558/heavy-earrings-251558-1599156019170-main.1200x1598uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>One of our favorite ways to bear the weight of heavy post or stud earrings is converting them into clip-ons. The process is incredibly simple and will keep you from wanting to remove your earrings midday. Keep a pack of converters on hand like Clip-Ease <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=PflKxL2kA-QYWAE7qJsczh-KctPZBEo0PJcXZfWa7ZoYxtOA28E\" target=\"_blank\">Clip-On Earring Converters</a> ($11), which are inexpensive and easy to apply. They also come in shades of gold, silver, and copper to match the metal of your earrings.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/251558/heavy-earrings-251558-1599156174389-main.1200x1598uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Regardless of how heavy your earrings are, get into the habit of removing them once you’re back home. This is an especially important tactic with heavy earrings, as it can minimize the extent to which the earlobes are stretched and strained.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/251558/heavy-earrings-251558-1599156119753-main.1200x1598uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>Odds are you already have a couple pairs of heavy earrings you can’t live without, but it may be worth opting for <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/earring-trends\" target=\"_blank\">lightweight options</a> in the future. Many heavy-looking earrings are crafted with hollow wood or lightweight metals that give you the look without the discomfort.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/251558/heavy-earrings-251558-1599156230721-main.1200x1598uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p>If you already have extensive lobe damage from wearing heavy earrings, a mild plastic surgery operation to strengthen your earlobes is available. It typically involves the injection of a filler like <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.com/ext?tl=u5KJNyyl44G1qS71a8PDnpCxQ8KNQ2GEWpTRljaE41Gtx8puiGUnmdx8zgCYodxc84SB9rYL\">Restylane</a> into the lobes to make them stiffer, plumper, and more durable. While this approach is more high-maintenance and expensive than other options, it’s worth considering if lobe damage is a concern.</p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/251558/heavy-earrings-251558-1599157644033-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/251558/heavy-earrings-251558-1599157174452-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/251558/heavy-earrings-251558-1599156661325-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/251558/heavy-earrings-251558-1599157021701-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/251558/heavy-earrings-251558-1599156716444-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cliqueinc.com/posts/251558/heavy-earrings-251558-1599157119073-main.1200x1200uc.jpg\"><figcaption></figcaption></figure></p><p><figure><img
